title: pumpkin bread
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, shortening and pumpkin.
Add additional ingredients alternately with water. Bake for 1 1/4 hours at 350°.

title: scripture cake
directions: Follow Solomon's advice for making good boys and girls and you will have a good cake (Proverbs 13:24).
A very old recipe.

title: luncheon salad
directions: Heat tomato soup; add gelatin softened in cold water.
Cool. Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add mixture to the gelatin mixture. Chill until firm.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: lemon capri salad
directions: Grate whole lemons before squeezing for juice; set peel aside. Combine Miracle Whip, lemon juice and capers; mix well.
Fold together water chestnuts, tuna and dressing.

title: easy raspberry sprize
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water; add tomatoes.
Chill until firm (in ice cube tray).
Serve on lettuce with dollop of mayonnaise and enjoy!
(Isn't it good?)

title: bourbon and pecan pie
directions: Soak pecans in bourbon.
Mix eggs with sugar until smooth. Slowly add corn syrup, melted butter and vanilla.
Let stand for four minutes.
Add chocolate chips and bourbon soaked pecans. Pour into the pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes, or until the crust is golden brown.

title: apple pecan oven pancake
directions: Preheat oven to 350° (325° for glass pie pan).
Combine apple, pecans, 2 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon each cinnamon and vanilla in a small bowl; set aside.
Stir baking mix, milk, eggs, remaining sugar, remaining teaspoon cinnamon and 2 teaspoons vanilla in a large bowl until blended.
Gently stir apple mixture into batter.
Pour batter into a greased 9 or 10-inch pie pan. Bake 40 minutes, or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Serve with syrup.

title: grecian orange cake
directions: Place all ingredients in bowl and beat on low for 2 minutes. Pour in greased tube pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: enchiladas verdes
directions: Flour tortillas may be used for layers but I prefer to use slightly warmed (in hot oil) white corn tortillas.

title: "heart healthy" raisin oatmeal cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast oats in preheated oven until crisp and fragrant, about 10 minutes; set aside.
Spray 2 large cookie sheets with nonstick spray.

title: tropical chicken
directions: Heat oil; add onion and garlic.
Saute 5 minutes until soft. Remove and save onion and garlic pieces.
Reserve 2 tablespoons orange juice.
Combine remaining orange juice, lime juice, chicken broth powder, salt and red pepper in bowl.
Add onion mixture. Brown chicken in same skillet in olive oil.
Add juice mix to skillet.
Simmer covered 10 minutes until tender.
Remove chicken to serving platter.
Combine cornstarch and reserved orange juice in small cup.
Stir in skillet, stirring until thick 2 minutes. Spoon over chicken and sprinkle with parsley.

title: pie crust
directions: Combine flour and salt. Cut in shortening. Add water a little at a time until it handles good.

title: s'more brownies
directions: Prepare the box brownie mix as directed. In the last 10 minutes of baking, remove from oven. Sprinkle a layer of chocolate chips and miniature marshmallows on top. Place graham cracker squares on top and press down. Put the brownies back in the oven for the remaining time. Allow to cool and cut into squares.

title: mints
directions: Mix all of the ingredients very well with hands.
Make small balls and flatten slightly with fork.

title: banana nut chocolate chip cake
directions: Mix powders in bowl.
Add eggs and oil.
Stir, do not beat with mixer.
Stir in vanilla, pineapple, nuts and chocolate chips. Spoon into well-greased and floured 9-inch round cake pan (2). Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
(Cool 10 minutes in pan, then turn onto cooling rack.)
Cut into 4 thin layers and fill.

title: cheese rice ring
directions: Cook onion and bell pepper in butter until tender.
Add tomatoes and rice.
Slowly cook until rice has absorbed liquid. Add seasonings and cheese.
Pack into buttered ring mold.
Unmold onto serving plate and fill with scrambled eggs.
Makes 6 servings.

title: low-fat chicken delight
directions: Combine cheese and mayonnaise, beating until smooth.
Add onion, pickle juice, celery, curry powder, salt, pepper, pimento, hot sauce and garlic powder; mix well.
Stir in chicken and 2 tablespoons broth.
Coat a 2-cup mold with nonstick cooking spray. Pour chicken mixture into prepared mold and chill.
Unmold onto serving plate; serve with Melba toast and raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix chicken soup and mayonnaise.
Add rest of ingredients. Pour all in a greased casserole dish.
Cover with crushed potato chips and bake at 425° for 25 minutes.
This can be prepared ahead all but potato chips.
This is good served with cranberry orange jello.
Add 2 boxes orange jello and a small can of crushed pineapple to frozen Indian Trail cranberry relish.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Butter pan well and cook as you would regular cornbread.

title: german baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients. Turn into greased casserole. Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°. Makes a quick lunch.

title: pumpkin nut cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs and pumpkin.
Then add all dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Add nuts and raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Roux:
Brown oil and flour until "chocolate" color.
Stir constantly on medium heat.
Add chopped onion, green pepper, celery and garlic.
Saute until tender (3 or 4 minutes).
Add tomato sauce and water.
Cook 30 minutes.
Add shrimp.
Cook 12 to 15 minutes longer.
Serve over cooked rice.

title: dawson's famous chocolate chip cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream butter and margarine; add brown sugar, white sugar, vanilla, water and eggs. Add chocolate chips and chopped pecans.
Bake at 375° on ungreased cookie sheet for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sliced sweet potato pie
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Place in a pot.
Cover with hot water and bring to boil; simmer for 5 minutes.
Drain; place in a deep dish lined with pastry.
Sprinkle each layer of potatoes with sugar and spices.
Dot with butter.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Top with strips of pastry.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 325° and bake for 45 minutes more.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Combine ingredients stirring over double boiler until thick. Pour in pie shell that is cooked.
Deep dish 9-inch pie shell is best.

title: wagon wheel salad
directions: Cook pasta and drain.
Rinse with cold water.
Cook vegetables as directed on package.
Cut these into bite size pieces, if needed. Drain and rinse with cold water.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl.
Toss gently. Cover and refrigerate 2 hours before serving.

title: no bake cookies
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first 4 ingredients.
Boil for 1 1/2 minutes on medium fire.
Add oats, then peanut butter. Mix well.
Spoon out on waxed paper or a buttered pan.
Cool before serving.

title: almost perfect lemon cream cheese bars
directions: Mix dry cake mix with 1 egg and 1/3 cup oil until crumbly; reserve 1 cup.
Pat remaining mixture in an ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 12 to 15 minutes at 325°.

title: easy party punch
directions: Mix all in a punch bowl, except sherbet.
Add sherbet after thawing slightly (enough to push it out of container) and serve. Makes 50 (1/2 cup) servings.

title: pecan tassies
directions: In a large bowl, beat 1/2 cup of butter and the cream cheese until creamy. Add the flour, beating until well combined. Cover and chill the dough for 30 minutes.

title: zucchini dish
directions: Take
all ingredients except zucchini and mix together. Add zucchini.
Put
in greased casserole. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until zucchini is tender.

title: oatmeal pancakes
directions: Mix oats and buttermilk.
(Let stand 10 minutes.)
Combine dry ingredients, then add egg.
Put on greased griddle on low heat.

title: pork chops and mushrooms beaumont
directions: Trim pork chops of excess fat.
In a large skillet, heat oil. Add pork chops (3 at a time) and brown about 5 minutes on each side.
Remove chops and set aside.
In skillet, combine soup, soup mix and 1/2 cup beer.
Cook over low heat, stirring to scrape drippings from bottom of pan.
Return chops to sauce in skillet, spooning some of the sauce over the chops.
Bring to the boiling point.
Reduce heat and simmer, covered, until chops are tender, about 30 minutes.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add the remaining ingredients.
Roll with palms of hands into finger lengths.
Bake on greased cookie sheet in a moderate oven at 325° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Roll in confectioners sugar while warm.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Combine milk, lemon rind and juice in a bowl.
Fold in Cool Whip and blend well.
Spoon into crust and chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: nachos
directions: Spread nacho chips on a microwave-proof plate.
Sprinkle with shredded Monterey Jack cheese.
Spoon green chiles over top of the cheese and chips.
Microwave at Medium (50%) for 1 1/2 to 2 1/2 minutes.

title: german apple pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pie pan with pastry.
Slice apples in thick slices, about 1/4-inch thick.
Place sliced apples in overlapping position.
Sprinkle sugar, nutmeg, cinnamon and salt over apples.

title: no-bake nut rolls
directions: Mix milk, nuts, cherries and wafers together thoroughly.
Make into rolls, 1 1/2-inches in diameter.
Roll in powdered sugar and wrap individually.
Refrigerate for several hours, overnight, or freeze.
To serve, cut across roll into 1/4 to 1/2-inch thick slices.
Makes 24.

title: burgundy beef stew
directions: In a large saucepan or Dutch oven, combine tomato soup, beef broth and Burgundy wine; mix, then blend in the flour, salt, pepper and basil.
Add meat and vegetables; stir to distribute through gravy, then cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Right before serving, place biscuits on top. Cover.
Put in oven until biscuits are done.
Serve and enjoy.

title: seafood salad
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: festive appetizers
directions: Open crescent rolls and roll dough out flat onto very lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake until light brown in color.
Let cool. Chop peppers very fine.
Spread layer of cream cheese onto cooked rolls, then sprinkle on the peppers; cut into appetizer pieces. Very festive and pretty for the holidays.

title: double crispy chicken
directions: Crush corn flakes in a pan.
Mix flour, salt, pepper, milk and margarine all together; dip chicken in the batter.
Roll in corn flakes good.
Grease a baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour until chicken is tender; do not cover while baking.

title: golden onion rings
directions: Cut onions into slices 1/4-inch thick; separate into rings. Combine remaining ingredients, beating together just until all dry ingredients are well moistened.
Coat onion rings well with batter.

title: vidalia onion casserole
directions: Melt butter in large frypan and saute onions over medium heat until clear.
Save 3 tablespoons cracker crumbs for top and place balance of crumbs in bottom of lightly greased 2-quart dish.
With slotted spoon, dip out onions and place on crumbs.
Mix soup, milk and beaten eggs and pour over top with cheese and remaining crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: 1-2-3 peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.

title: cinnamon batter-dipped french toast
directions: Heat oil in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat until hot. Beat remaining ingredients except bread with wire whisk until only small lumps remain.
Dip bread into batter; drain excess batter back into bowl.
Cook over medium high heat until golden brown, 1 to 2 minutes on each side; drain.
Serve warm with syrup or powdered sugar if desired.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix together all ingredients and pour into a greased 2-quart baking dish. Bake at 350° until lightly browned.

title: jean rainone's oven stew
directions: Place the stew meat into stew pan and season.
Add carrots, onions and celery (the amount you desire).
Pour chicken soup and water over all the ingredients.

title: nutcrackers
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Sift flour and 1 tablespoon sugar in medium size bowl.
Cut in shortening with pastry blender. Sprinkle water over mixture; blend gently with a fork.
Press mixture into a ball.
Roll out on a well floured board to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut out 12 rounds with 3 1/2-inch biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake for 10 to 12 minutes, or until golden brown.
Transfer to wire rack.
Cool.

title: no fuss tuna casserole
directions: In a medium saucepan, mix soups, tomato sauce and cream cheese.
Heat until cheese melts; stir well and season with salt, pepper, garlic and oregano to taste.
This may seem like you are overdoing it but remember you are seasoning for the entire dish. Boil macaroni in a Dutch oven.
Drain tuna, peas and mushrooms. When noodles are almost done, drain and mix all ingredients together.
Top with grated cheese and cover with lid; continue to heat at 350° for 30 minutes.
Serves 6 hungry people.

title: dallas pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, one at a time, then add flour, then pineapple juice and flavoring.
Start in cold oven. Cook 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Preheat oven to
Lightly grease 2 baking sheets.
In a medium bowl, combine and cream the sugar, margarine, egg and vanilla.
In a small bowl, combine and mix the flour, baking soda and cream of tartar.
Blend the flour into creamed mixture.
It will be very thick.
Using hands, shape into balls.
Roll each ball into a mixture of cinnamon and sugar and place on baking sheets.
Work quickly and lightly to keep heat of your hands from making the dough sticky.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes. Remove from pan and cool on wire rack.

title: corned beef and cabbage(casserole)
directions: Place potatoes in shallow 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Cover with onion, salt and pepper.
Add cabbage; crumble corned beef and spread over top.
Cover with soup diluted with milk.
Cover and bake at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: super duper potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes in jackets; cool, peel and grate.
Mix butter, half and half and cheese and heat in a pan, stirring constantly. Pour over grated potatoes.
Use small, oblong, greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except last two.
Blend mayonnaise with lemon juice and add to macaroni mixture; mix well.
Yields 6 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix bran flakes, skim milk, honey, oil and egg.
Let stand for 5 minutes, then add flour, baking powder and dates.

title: minute boil frosting
directions: Place in saucepan and bring slowly to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil briskly 1 minute (on rainy day boil 1 1/2 minutes).
Cool to lukewarm.
Add vanilla and beat.

title: mock veal
directions: Slice roast very thin.
Dust with seasoned flour.
Dip into beaten eggs, then coat well with breadcrumbs.
Fry quickly in hot oil until brown.
Drain and set aside.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and cook on medium heat until potatoes are tender.
Then add the can of evaporated milk.
Serve hot, garnished with parsley, if desired.

title: broccoli supreme
directions: Combine egg, broccoli, corn, onion, salt and pepper in bowl in small saucepan.
Melt margarine.
Add stuffing mix; toss to coat. Stir 1 cup of mix in vegetable mixture.
Put in casserole and top with remaining crumbs.
Cook in 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: chicken salad
directions: Boil the fryers and take skin off and the bones out.
Cut up in fairly large bite-size finger length pieces.
Add the pecans and grapes.
Mix in the salad dressing and chill.

title: albondigas soup
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Form into 3/4 to 1-inch balls and cook in a frypan.
Set aside to drain on paper towels.

title: yeast biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl, add oil egg and water and mix well.
Place in covered bowl in refrigerator.
Remove as much as needed and knead on floured surface.
Roll 1/4 to 1/2 in. thick. Cut with floured biscuit cutter.
Bake at 450 degrees for 10-12 minutes.
Keeps two weeks in refrigerator.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions.
Add other ingredients.
If you prefer, add Velveeta cheese (1/2 cup).

title: rhubarb crumble pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pat mixture into a 9-inch pie plate, reserving enough for topping.

title: stuffer's crunch
directions: Mix together and bake in an open pan for two hours at 225°, stirring occasionally.
Makes 8 quarts.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Fry the bacon.
Set aside.
Cook Taters O'Brien in the same pan after draining most of the grease.
Once the potatoes are cooked, add the eggs and continue cooking until the eggs are done.
Brown sausage in separate pan.
When brown, add it to taters and eggs. Everyone create their own burrito.
Start with flour tortilla, meat and egg mixture, cheese and salsa.
Crumble bacon over meat and egg mixture or leave it to be added by each person.
Leftovers, wrap for freezer and freeze until needed.
Pop in microwave for a delicious quick breakfast.

title: ruby christmas slush
directions: Combine thawed orange juice concentrate and water, mixing well. Stir in fruit punch, pineapple juice and cranapple juice.
Freeze in a large container stirring occasionally.
Remove from freezer 3-4 hours before serving, stirring occasionally as mixture thaws. Stir in ginger ale just before serving.
Yield:
about 2 1/4 gallons.

title: broccoli bread
directions: Mix together.
Put into a greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: e-z coffee cake
directions: Combine well all ingredients.
Pour into a buttered pie tin. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: apple brownies
directions: Dice apples in mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix together and put into 8 x 8-inch pan.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Nuts can be added, if desired.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Refrigerate for at least 2 or 3 hours, covered.
Before serving, garnish with chopped tomatoes, ripe olives or grated cheeses.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: hot dog sauce
directions: Put a small amount of shortening in a stew pot.
Add beef, salt, pepper and chili powder.
On medium heat, cook until the beef is in small balls.
Put tomato paste or sauce and a small amount of water into mixture.
Simmer 2 to 3 hours.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix all (but chips) and put into 8 x 12 pyrex pan.
Cover with crushed potato chips.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes at 450 degrees.

title: special mashed potatoes
directions: Mash potatoes with butter, salt and pepper.
Do not use milk! Add cream cheese and egg and beat together.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Cook spinach just until ice is gone.
In a bowl, combine soup, milk and any other seasonings, if desired.
Gently stir in spinach.
Spoon half of mixture in a 2-quart greased casserole or a 12 x 8-inch dish.
Sprinkle half the onions on top.
Spoon remaining spinach mixture over onions.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining onions on top the last 5 minutes of baking time, or until onions are brown and crispy.
Yields 8 to 10 servings.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes stirring occasionally. Cook noodles in large amount of boiling salted water until tender; drain and rinse.
Beat eggs; add remaining ingredients, except Mozzarella.
Layer half the noodles in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Spread with half Ricotta filling; add half Mozzarella cheese and half meat sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix egg, butter and cream of chicken or mushroom soup.
Add squash, bread crumbs and onion.
Stir well and place in a square 9 x 9-inch Pyrex dish or pan of your choice.
(Glass cooks a little quicker.)
Cook until almost done, then sprinkle cheese on top and let brown.

title: crunchy chicken cheese bake
directions: In 3-quart oblong baking dish place chicken, top with cheese. Stir soup and spread over cheese; top with tomato.
Combine butter and stuffing, sprinkle over tomatoes.
Bake at 400° for 25 to 35 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Garnish with fresh oregano if so desired.
Can be served over rice.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Arrange asparagus in oblong casserole. Combine soup, reserved asparagus liquid, salt and pepper. Pour over asparagus and sprinkle with cheese.
Combine margarine and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake at 300° for 45 minutes.

title: buttermilk meat loaf
directions: Mix ground beef with egg; add remaining ingredients, except flour, in order listed.
Mix well; form into loaf and place in baking pan.
Rub small amount of flour on top of loaf.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for about 45 minutes or until done.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes and drain.
Mix with soup, eggs, mayonnaise, salt, pepper and onion.
Place in 1 or 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Melt oleo and pour over stuffing mix.
Spread this on top of cheese.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour or at 325° for 1 hour.

title: blender peach ice cream
directions: Slice peaches into blender or food processor.
Add juice, sugar, syrup, extract and salt.
Whirl until pureed.
Add sour cream and whirl until smooth.
Pour into 8-inch square metal pan. Freeze, uncovered, about 2 hours or until set at edges.
Turn into medium bowl.
Beat until smooth.
Return to pan.
Cover airtight and freeze until firm.
Makes 8 servings.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Snowdrift and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add flour and milk alternately.
Add coconut and flavoring.
Bake in tube pan for 1 1/2 hours at 300°.

title: banana punch
directions: Bring water and sugar to a boil then set aside to cool.
Mix bananas and lemon juice in blender.
Add orange juice, water and pineapple juice.
Add sugar water; mix well, freeze in plastic gallon jug or plastic bag.
When ready to serve, partially thaw to a slush and add 4 quarts of ginger ale.

title: corn bread chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken and break apart.
Combine chicken, mayonnaise, water chestnuts, soup and celery.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish then put on stuffing mix and spread all over the top.
Pour melted butter or margarine over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: flaky pie crust
directions: Divide shortening in half.
Work 1/2 into the dry ingredient mixture, until smooth.
Work other 1/2 into the mixture until just about the size of a pea.
Make well in center and add the ice water, 1 tablespoon at a time.

title: jo's ranch style rollsnederland, texas
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix all ingredients in order adding yeast and water last.
Keep in ice box and spoon batter into muffin tins as needed.
Let rise 1 hour.
Cook at 275° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: purple meatballs
directions: Mush first 10 ingredients together; roll into small balls (cocktail size).
Bake on tray in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour, until golden brown.
When cool, store in airtight containers in freezer until Christmas or the next big party.

title: ambrosia salad
directions: After draining fruit, combine with grapes, marshmallows, coconut and nuts. Mix sour cream and sugar. Stir into fruit mixture. Chill. Serves 6.

title: mexican style appetizer
directions: In a small bowl combine soup, taco seasoning mixed with hot pepper sauce, stir until blended.
On large serving plate, spread mixture into a 6 inch round.
Spread sides and top of bean mixture with sour cream to cover. Layer chiles, olives, cheese, sprouts and tomatoes over sour cream.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours. Surround with tortilla chips to serve.
Makes 10 appetizer servings.

title: baked eggs
directions: Make white sauce of first 7 ingredients.
Add 1 pound grated Cheddar cheese.

title: joy's crab cakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bread crumbs.
Form into cakes and roll in bread crumbs.
Fry until brown on both sides.
Drain on absorbent paper.
Makes 7 to 8 crab cakes.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Mix
sugar,
cornstarch and water;
bring to a boil and continue
for 1 minute, stirring constantly.
Add fruit;
pour in baking dish;
dot with butter.
Mix rest of ingredients and drop by	spoonfuls onto hot fruit.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes in 400° heated oven.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift sugar and flour into mixing bowl. In saucepan, blend Coca-Cola, butter, shortening and cocoa; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat and add to flour mixture.
Add eggs and beat with mixer until blended.
Add buttermilk, baking soda, vanilla and marshmallows.
Mix well.
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan for 40 minutes.
Spread frosting on warm cake.

title: angel hair pasta with asparagus, tomatoes
directions: Trim asparagus and rinse in cold water.
Remove the tips; set aside. Bias-slice remaining asparagus stalks into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pieces and set aside.

title: chocolate chip oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream together shortening, peanut butter, sugars, eggs and vanilla.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for about 10 minutes.

title: buzzards' nests
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a small mixing bowl; beat at high speed with electric mixer until soft peaks form. Gradually add sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until sugar dissolves.
Stir in crushed cereal.
Drop by level tablespoons onto lightly greased cookie sheet.
Make indentation in center with thumb.
Place 3 peanut candies in each.
Bake at 275° for 30 minutes, or until set.
Remove quickly onto wire rack to cool. Yields 3 dozen.

title: crock-pot soup
directions: Brown ground chuck and drain. Put browned chuck and all ingredients (except spaghetti) in 3 1/2-quart crock-pot and cook on low for 6 hours. Add spaghetti during last 2 hours of cooking.

title: pork ribs
directions: Trim fat carefully.
Mix all ingredients. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes covered and then uncovered for 30 minutes.

title: marilyn mcconnell's beef casserole
directions: Mix the browned hamburger, spices, onion and tomato sauce in a large pot and simmer 15 minutes.
Mix the cooked noodles, cream cheese and sour cream; stir into the meat sauce.
Turn into a deep, greased casserole.
Top with mushrooms and grated cheese. Bake 45 minutes at 300°.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat slowly. Spoon off excess fat.
Add next 5 ingredients. Simmer, uncovered, 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: tostada dip
directions: In 13 x 9-inch pan, layer ingredients in order shown.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, cornstarch and cornmeal together.
Add slightly beaten eggs.
Add buttermilk into which a pinch of soda has been stirred.
Blend all ingredients together and fill pie shell.
Bake until done, approximately 45 minutes, until just lightly set.

title: florentine salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water.
Cool.
Just before it sets, mix in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 8-inch square pan or individual molds.
Chill until set.
Cut into strips or squares and serve on lettuce leaves.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: cherry crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8-inch square baking pan.
Mix oats, flour and sugar.
Cut in butter with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse crumbs.
Spoon half of the mixture into prepared pan.
Top with pie filling.
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Bake for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve warm with sweetened whipped cream or ice cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot blueberry tea bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together; add eggs. Beat vigorously. Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Add, in about 3 portions, alternately with milk. Beat only until smooth. Fold in blueberries. Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Bake at 400° about 25 minutes. Makes 9 to 12 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Remove skin and debone.
Cut into small pieces.
Pour rice into chicken broth and cook as directed on rice box.
Mix the chicken soup, mayonnaise, onion, rice, pepper, margarine and chicken into pan and stir.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Pour in.
Place almonds on the top.
Cook at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss ham ring around
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crescent rolls, in bowl.
Place crescent rolls in circle, point facing out.
Put filling on fat end.
Bring point towards center and tuck under.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Drain the zucchini and rinse thoroughly with cold water.
Add the vinegar, sugar, turmeric, dry mustard, cornstarch, celery seed, pepper, and bell peppers.
Mix well and cook together for 30 minutes in a large pan.
Ladle into hot, sterilized jars and put the lids on.
Process in a hot water bath about 10 minutes.

title: frozen fruit cake salad
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in mixer, then combine last 4 ingredients with first 6, then freeze.

title: cheese potato
directions: Combine potatoes, soup and sour cream in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Cover while baking.

title: cream of mushroom pork chops
directions: Turn oven on to 425°.
Wash pork chops, pat dry and salt and pepper very good.
Put chops in a large baking dish.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Take out, add cream of mushroom soup and spread evenly over chops.
Cook until done.

title: lemon pie
directions: Combine sugar, cornstarch and water in top of double boiler. Stir constantly, cook until thick and smooth.
Add egg yolks, butter, salt and lemon juice. Cook 2 minutes.
Pour into one 9-inch pie shell and top with meringue.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain; put into casserole dish with other ingredients.
Stir and top with cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: apple cheesecake
directions: In a small bowl, soften gelatin in water; let stand for 2 minutes. In a saucepan over medium heat, cook and stir apple juice, sugar, egg yolks and gelatin mixture until gelatin is dissolved. Cool to room temperature. In a large mixing bowl, beat the cream cheese, cinnamon and nutmeg until smooth. Gradually beat in gelatin mixture until smooth. Chill until slightly thickened, about 20 minutes. Fold in cream. Pour into an ungreased 9 inch spring form pan. Chill 4 hours or overnight. In a saucepan over medium heat, brown peanuts in butter for 2 minutes. Add applesauce, brown sugar and cinnamon; cook and stir for 5 minutes. Cool. Spread over top of cheesecake. If desired, garnish with whipped cream, cinnamon and peanuts.

title: super sweet potatoes
directions: Mix together sweet potato, butter, vanilla and sugar.
Pour into a 6 x 7 x 2-inch buttered pan.
Top with brown sugar, flour, nuts and 1/3 cup melted butter mixed together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: wild rice and shrimp creole
directions: Melt butter or oleo in a large saucepan.
Add onion and green pepper; saute until tender.
Stir in next 7 ingredients.
Bring to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer 20 to 25 minutes.
Stir in shrimp.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes, adding water if necessary. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: rice cakes via 1800
directions: Combine rice, eggs, vanilla and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add enough flour to make a dough that folds together.
Drop by teaspoonfuls into hot fat (360°) and fry until golden brown.
Drain on paper.
Sprinkle or roll in sifted powdered sugar.
Serve hot.

title: corn casserole
directions: Combine all together in casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: refried taco beans
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add taco mix, sauce, sour cream and beans.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: coconut pies
directions: Mix all ingredients and blend well. Bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until firm.

title: oven steak and potatoes
directions: Melt butter.
Put potatoes in butter.
Completely cover. Remove; salt and pepper.
Toss steak in remaining butter until covered.
Spray pan with pan spray to avoid sticking.
Lay steak and potatoes in pan and bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes until done.
Meat and potatoes come out tender and delicious.

title: broccoli lasagna
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Bring a large pot of lightly salted water to a boil.
Add pasta and cook for 8 to 10 minutes; drain. In a medium saucepan over medium heat, melt butter.
Cook onion and garlic in butter until tender.
Stir in flour, pepper, 1/2 tsp. salt and nutmeg.
Stirring continuously, pour in milk, a little at a time, allowing mixture to thicken.
Bring to a boil for 1 minute, then remove from heat and stir in parsley.
Set aside.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In a medium mixing bowl, with a wire whisk, blend the mayonnaise, parsley, shallots, chopped pickles, hard egg and green pepper.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add sufficient lemon juice or wine vinegar to thin the sauce slightly and to point up the flavors.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: butter icing
directions: Cream butter until soft and add sugar, blending well.
Moisten with cream to consistency desired.
Any flavoring may be used.

title: potato stew
directions: Boil potatoes until done.
Drain.
Add milk.
Boil slowly. Add 1/2 stick butter.
Melt in pot with potatoes; add salt and pepper last.
Add cornmeal.
Stir constantly for next 2 to 4 minutes, then simmer for about 30 minutes.
Serve warm alone or with cornbread.

title: pound cake
directions: Measure flour in sugar box.
Cream butter.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating vigorously.
Add sugar.
Add sifted flour and salt. Add almond extract.
Bake in 275° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pork roast
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients in bowl.
Rub all over roast. Double wrap in foil; let set overnight.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs, pumpkin and vanilla, beat well.
Combine dry ingredients, then add to batter.
Stir in nuts.

title: lillies fudge
directions: Put sugar, Pet milk, marshmallows and margarine in heavy pot. Bring to a boil; lower heat and cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and morsels; stir until mixed.
Pour into buttered pan.
Cut while slightly warm.

title: becky's banana cake
directions: Slice bananas in mixer bowl and beat well.
Add rest of ingredients; beat 2 minutes.
Pour into well-greased, floured tube pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Use any frosting.

title: dirty rice
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a greased pan layer rice, ground beef and margarine.
Pat out the margarine so that it is evenly distributed over mixture.
Pour onion soup over all.
Then pour consomme soup over that.
Bake about 40 minutes or until brown.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Grease oblong pan.
Sprinkle coconut and pecans on bottom of pan.
Mix cake according to directions.
Pour cake mixture over pecans/coconut.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and butter.
Pour over cake mix.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: quiche
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cube the bread (no crust) and place in bottom of pan.
Brown and drain the sausage and then stir in the cheese.
Layer this mixture over the crust.
Beat together the eggs, mustard and 2 1/2 cups milk.
Pour this on top.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.

title: west haven cake
directions: Cut dates in half and pour over them the hot water mixed with the soda.
Let cool.
Cream the sugar and shortening.
Add the dates to the creamed mixture and add the salt. Add eggs, vanilla and flour (that was sifted with the cocoa).
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan and sprinkle with the nut meats and 1 bar of German sweet chocolate and Hershey candy bars over the top.
Bake 40 minutes at 350°.

title: gumdrop orange slice fruit cake
directions: Chop
all
fruits, nuts, coconut and candy.
Mix in one bowl and
mix
1/2 cup flour with fruit.
Cream the margarine and sugar;
add eggs.
Sift soda with flour.
Add alternately with buttermilk.
Add
vanilla.	Mix
alternately
with fruit mixture. Pour
in
greased tube pan.
Bake 2 hours at 300° or less.	Remove from pan and ice while still hot.

title: raw cranberry sauce
directions: Put cranberries, apples and orange peel through food chopper. Cut oranges in small sections with scissors.
Add sugar and stir well; set in icebox.
Will keep for several days.

title: shrimp ball
directions: Drain and mash shrimp and combine with the rest of ingredients.
Mold into ball and chill.
Serve on plate with Halland cocktail sauce poured on the center.
Serve with favorite crackers placed around plate.

title: meat balls
directions: *One pound beef, pork and veal mixture is best, but hamburger, or chopped steak will do.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Delicious with tortilla chips or crackers.

title: bacon onion pinwheels
directions: Prep time: 10 minutes. Ready in: 25 minutes.

title: texas pecan candy cake
directions: Preheat oven to slow (250°).
Grease and flour 9 x 3-inch tube pan with removable bottom; set pan aside.
Cut cherries in quarters.
Chop pineapple coarsely.
Coarsely snip the dates. Combine cherries, pineapple and dates in very large bowl. Sprinkle with flour; toss to coat well.
Add coarsely chopped pecans and coconut; toss to
mix.
Add sweetened condensed milk; stir to mix well.
Spoon evenly into prepared pan, smoothing top. Bake in preheated slow oven (250°) for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan on rack. Remove from pan.
Wrap tightly in foil.
Refrigerate at least 2 weeks.
Cake cuts best when cold.
Slice very thin with serrated knife.

title: lemon bread
directions: Combine in large bowl the first 5 ingredients, adding eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Set aside.
Whisk together dry ingredients.
Add to creamed mixture alternating with milk. When all is added, add canola seeds and nuts.
Spoon into sprayed and floured bread pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes or until done. Simmer together 5 minutes and pour over warm
bread pierced with fork the lemon juice and sugar.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Mix the cocoa and food coloring.
Add Crisco, sugar and eggs; cream well. Sift flour and salt, adding dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Blend in vanilla and almond extract. In a small bowl, stir soda into vinegar and add to mixture quickly. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: fudge cake
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and set aside.
Take oleo, cocoa and water and bring to a hard boil.
Pour over mixture of flour, sugar, baking soda and cinnamon.
Add eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes until done.

title: fig berry preserves
directions: Mix together and cook on medium heat until thick (after first bubble, no longer than 8 minutes).
Pour in heated jars or use the melted wax method.
Tastes like real strawberry jam.

title: tex-mex tofu lasagna(eating light)
directions: Saute tofu, garlic and onion in oil.
Stir in Mexican or taco seasoning packets.
When onions begin to soften, add tomato sauce and frozen vegetables; mix well.
Bring to a gentle boil, then reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.

title: play dough
directions: Mix and cook on medium heat.
Stir constantly until right consistency.
Knead in food coloring.

title: soft sugar cookies
directions: Mix as a cake.
Batter will be very soft.
Drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375°.

title: fruit dip
directions: *Especially good with apple slices and strawberries.
Also can be used with cookies.

title: stuffed shells
directions: Boil shells per box instructions; drain and run under cold water, then drain again.
Saute the meat until done.
Drain and add sauce.
Heat and set aside.
Combine Ricotta cheese, 1/2 pound Mozzarella (shredded), 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, beaten eggs, basil, salt and pepper to taste and garlic powder to taste.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Cook sugar, flour, cocoa and milk until thickens.
Add egg last; cook 1 minute longer.
Add vanilla.
Pour into baked pie crust.
Put Cool Whip on top.

title: chickpea salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients in a bowl.
In a small jar, shake together the vinegar, salt and pepper. Add the olive oil and shake again.
Pour dressing over chickpea mixture and toss.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Pop approximately 2 gallons of unsalted popcorn.
Bring oleo, brown sugar and Karo to boil.
Boil 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir hard.
Pour over already popped corn; mix well.
Pour onto lightly sprayed cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.
Break apart as it cools.

title: sicilian supper
directions: Brown meat; add onion and cook until tender.
Boil chopped green pepper until tender.
Add tomato paste, water and salt and pepper to meat; simmer 5 minutes.
Heat milk and cream cheese; blend well.
Stir in green pepper, 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese, garlic powder and cooked noodles.
In casserole, alternate layers of meat sauce and noodle mixture, ending with layer of meat sauce.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle on remaining 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese.

title: tang punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in order listed.
Pour over ice cubes or chips in punch bowl.
To serve later, freeze, but add the club soda or ginger ale just before serving.

title: chocolate chip fruit muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease or paper-line 18 (2 1/2-inch) muffin cups.
In large bowl, combine bread mix, eggs, milk and oil.
Beat with spoon 30 seconds.
Stir in chocolate chips and fruit bits.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 full with batter.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Serve warm.

title: italian chicken
directions: Combine crumbs, parsley and Parmesan cheese.
Dip chicken in egg; coat with crumb mixture.
Spread 1 cup spaghetti sauce in 8 x 12-inch baking pan.
Arrange chicken in sauce.
Spoon remaining sauce over chicken.
Bake covered at 400° for 1 hour or until chicken is tender.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake uncovered until cheese melts.
Garnish with additional parsley.
Yields 6 servings.

title: custard blender pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; blend.
Pour in 9-inch pie plate. Sprinkle with nutmeg.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until done. Test with butter knife.

title: sweet deviled eggs
directions: Slice eggs in half lengthwise and remove yolks.
Mash yolks; add sugar, mustard, half and half, vinegar and salt, stirring until smooth.
Spoon or pipe into egg white halves.
Sprinkle with paprika and parsley, if desired.

title: tomato soup cake
directions: Grease and flour pan. Mix all except cream cheese until moist. Mix on medium speed for 2 minutes. Bake cake at 350 degrees until golden brown. Let cool then spread on cream cheese.

title: quick cocoa cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients by hand in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan (do not butter or grease pan).
Mix in liquid ingredients until smooth.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes at 350° (325° for glass pan).

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a large casserole and mix well.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple raspberry crumble
directions: Arrange apples in buttered 8 x 8-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice.
Drain raspberries.
Sprinkle over apples.
Mix flour and sugar in bowl.
Cut in butter until crumbly.
Add nutmeg.
Sprinkle over fruit.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: delicious coffee cake
directions: Put mix, sour cream, eggs, oil and ginger ale in mixing bowl. Beat 2 minutes.
Fold in sugar with cinnamon and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Cool on rack 20 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Freezes well.

title: cheerios fudge
directions: In bowl, combine frosting dry mix, butter, water and vanilla with a fork or fingers until thoroughly blended.
Add Cheerios and mix well.
With hands, shape into one-inch balls.
Roll in 1/2 cup crushed Cheerios.

title: carrot-pineapple-raisin salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Serve on lettuce leaves.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Stir together beaten eggs, oil, sugar and zucchini.
Sift together flour, baking powder, salt, cinnamon and baking soda. Add to zucchini mixture.
Stir in vanilla, orange rind, and nuts. Pour into greased loaf pans.
Bake at 325 degrees for one hour. Makes 2 loaves.

title: one-two-three-four cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add one egg at a time and mix. Add sifted flour and milk alternately; mix well, then add chopped nuts.
Pour into a greased large tube pan.
Sprinkle top with cinnamon-sugar, if desired.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes. Makes 12 servings.

title: crusty coconut pie
directions: Pour milk over coconut and set aside while creaming butter and sugar.
Add eggs, beat well.
Then add milk and coconut and flavoring.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and firm.

title: enchiladas
directions: Make chili of your choice.
Remove some of the chili meat from the pot with a slotted spoon.
Chop onion; set aside.
Grate American cheese; set aside.
Fill a 2-quart saucepan about 3/4 full of water, let come to a boil.
Place tortillas, one at a time, in the hot water for 1 second.
Keep water very hot.

title: sunday nite salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add strawberries with their juice, pineapple, bananas and nuts to Jell-O.
Mix well.
Place 1/2 of mixture in a flat pan; put in refrigerator to set.
When set, spread the sour cream over set Jell-O, then spoon the rest of the Jell-O over the top of the sour cream.
Chill.

title: grandma leary's doughnuts
directions: Mix together and beat until smooth, about 30 seconds.
Place dough in refrigerator and chill.
Roll out in a small portion of dough at a time on a lightly floured board to 1/4-inch thickness. Cut out doughnuts and let stand on board for 20 minutes before frying.
Fry a few doughnuts at a time in 370° fat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Makes 2 dozen small doughnuts.

title: mock pineapple
directions: Peel and seed zucchini; grate.
Squeeze excess liquid from zucchini.
Mix ingredients well with zucchini; simmer 20 or 30 minutes.
Stir frequently.
Ladle into hot sterilized jars (3 minutes at 5 pounds pressure or 30 minutes water bath).
This is excellent in upside-down cake!

title: vera's hot apple cider
directions: Heat apple juice and red hots until melted and serve.

title: banana tea loaf
directions: In mixing bowl, combine flour, baking soda, cream of tartar and salt.
Set aside.
Into blender put remaining ingredients. Cover.
Press high button; blend about 20 seconds.
Pour over dry ingredients and mix just until all flour is moistened.
Turn into greased 8 x 4-inch loaf pan.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: icebox fruit cake
directions: Melt marshmallows in 2 cups of milk.
Add rolled crackers and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well with hands.
Pat in buttered tube pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from pan; wrap in foil. Store in refrigerator.
Very rich, slice very thin.

title: quick red velvet cake
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Bake in Bundt pan that has been greased well.
Cook at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Then cool and frost.

title: carrot custard(for babies)
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and cover.
Run or whip until smooth.
Pour mixture into 4 small custard cups.
Place cups in shallow pan of hot water and bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until it is set.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix ingredients; shape into 20 (1 1/2-inch) balls.
Cook over medium heat, turning occasionally, until brown, about 20 minutes. Or cook in ungreased oblong pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch) at 400° until light brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fried squash fritters(this recipe will serve 12 people)
directions: Combine all, except oil, in bowl and mix well.
Shape in small patties and fry in hot oil until brown on both sides.
Serve hot with butter.

title: rice timali
directions: Fry onion in a little fat; add peppers, then mushrooms and chopped bacon.
Cook until done.
Add rice, sweet corn and sliced Wurst sausage, previously heated through.
Mix well.

title: mini pecan tarts
directions: Let the cream cheese and margarine soften at room temperature.
Blend and stir in flour.
Chill slightly for about an hour.
Shape into 2 dozen 1 inch balls.
Place in tiny ungreased 1 3/4 inch muffin cups.
Press dough against bottom and sides of cups.

title: fire roasted hot salsa
directions: Preheat your barbecue grill to a high temperature.
Remove any stems from the tomatoes and rub olive oil over each tomato. Rub olive oil over the jalapenos.
Place the tomatoes and jalapenos on the hot grill.
Turn tomatoes and jalapenos after 10 minutes.
When the pepper skins have turned mostly black, they can be removed from the grill.
The tomatoes can be removed when their skins are partially black and begin to come off.
Put tomatoes and peppers on a plate to cool.

When cool, remove most of the skin from the tomatoes and place them into a food processor or blender. Pinch the stem end from each of the peppers and place them into the food processor or blender as well.
Add the remaining ingredients and puree on high speed until the mixture has a smooth consistency.
Place salsa into a covered container and chill for several hours or overnight while the flavors develop.
Enjoy!

title: orange cream sherbet
directions: Stir sugar and salt into lemon and orange juice. Add milk, whipping cream and half and half. Freeze in ice cream freezer. Yield: 1 gallon.

title: tangy cider punch
directions: Cook water and sugar together in saucepan stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Boil 5 minutes; cool.
Combine cider, orange and lemon juices in a pitcher.
Add cooled syrup and serve over ice cubes.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan and arrange bread cubes along bottom. Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Mix egg substitute, eggs, milk, mustard, Worcestershire and pepper.
Pour evenly over bread. Sprinkle with bacon or sausage chunks, onions, mushrooms and tomato.
Cover and chill for 12 to 24 hours.
Heat oven to 325° and bake for 1 hour or until set.

title: lemon supreme cake
directions: Mix together everything except powdered sugar and lemon juice. Bake in a 13 x 9-inch pan at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Mix sugar and lemon juice.
Poke holes in cake while still warm and pour sugar/lemon mixture in holes and on top of cake.

title: zucchini hot dish
directions: Pour boiling water over zucchini and bring quickly to a boil. Boil
minutes.
Drain.
Mix all ingredients together and
put in	greased casserole;
bake at 350° for 40 minutes. Cover last 15 minutes.

title: pasta and ceci
directions: Render bacon in
quart saucepan until crisp;
remove with slotted spoon, leave
to
4 tablespoons fat.
Add oil, onion and garlic;
saute	until
soft.
Add
tomatoes,
juice, broth, chickpeas and rosemary.
Simmer 15 to 20 minutes or so; add tomato sauce, black
and
red
pepper to taste and parsley and simmer 5 to 10
minutes
more.
Bring
to boil; add pasta. When pasta is very firm,	shut off heat.	(You may need to add a little water.) Let
stand	a
minute
or two covered.
Serve with grated cheese.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Beat together the cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg and 1 teaspoon of vanilla in a small bowl and set aside.

title: mama's english pea salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Chill.
Better served the next day.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown meat and onion in skillet.
Stir in salsa, chili powder and salt.
Mash in beans; heat thoroughly.
Garnish with cheese.

title: coconut cake(basic 1-2-3-4 cake)
directions: Mix by creaming the butter and sugar and adding eggs, one at a time.
Stir in dry ingredients alternately with liquid (about 3 additions each).
Never overbeat.
Hand stirring is better in this last step.
Bake in 3 round pans at 375° for about 20 minutes, only until firm.
Cool on rack and put together with filling.

title: lemon fluff pie
directions: Melt butter in heavy skillet. Stir in flour, brown sugar and pecans. Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until crumbs are toasted and golden brown. Let stand until cool. Reserve 2 tablespoons of crumbs. Press remaining crumbs into a 9-inch pie plate. Combine lemon juice and condensed milk in a large bowl; mix well. Fold in whipped cream; spoon into prepared crust. Sprinkle with reserved crumbs. Chill until serving time. Makes 6 servings.

title: brandy logs
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan, stir evaporated milk and chocolate pieces over low heat until chocolate melts.
Remove from heat. Add brandy and powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Gradually stir in nuts and crumbs.
Let stand 30 minutes.
Shape into 2-inch logs.
Roll in either finely cut nuts or powdered sugar.
Cut in 1/2-inch pieces.
Makes about 4 dozen.

title: ruth's dirty rice
directions: Brown flour in oil and add onions, celery and green pepper. Cook until tender.
Stir in ground meat and seasoning.
Continue cooking until meat loses red coloring.
Blend in broth.
Cover and simmer 25 minutes.
Stir in rice and onion tops.
Cook 5 minutes longer.
Serves 6.

title: no tomato barbecue chicken
directions: In small saucepan, melt butter.
Add onion; cook until onion is transparent.
Add next 7 ingredients, stirring well.
Slowly pour in water, stirring until mixture boils.
Remove from heat. Brush chicken with sauce.
Grill, skin side up, about 8 inches from heat.
Cook about 1 hour (until fork-tender), turning and basting every 10 to 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Note:
Need one plastic or glass flowerpot (8-inch) and plastic flower to decorate to match season.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cream together until fluffy the eggs. Add the sugar, pumpkin and lemon juice. Mix well, then fold in the flour, baking powder and cinnamon. Mix well. Pour into greased jelly roll pan (grease pan, then cover with wax paper and grease again). Sprinkle with chopped nuts (optional). Bake at 375° for 15 minutes. Loosen edges and put onto powdered sugar towel while warm. Take waxed paper off and sprinkle generously with powdered sugar. Turn over and sprinkle other side with powdered sugar. Roll in towel from underside. Let cool.

title: mexican hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion. Add onion, soups and sauce. Layer large casserole with tortillas and meat mixture to make two layers. Cover with grated cheese. Bake at 350° until tortillas are soft.

title: chicken ala king
directions: Saute mushrooms and green pepper in butter about 5 minutes. Blend in flour, salt and pepper over low heat.
Remove from heat. Stir in broth, cream and mushroom liquid.
Stir constantly until thickened and comes to a boil.
Boil 1 minute.
Stir in chicken and chopped pimentos.
Serve over pastry puff shells (these can be bought frozen).
This dish can be frozen!

title: fudge
directions: Mix all but butter and vanilla.
Stir until sugar is dissolved.
Cook to 225° or until soft-ball stage.
Cool, then add butter and vanilla.
Beat until it begins to get firm.
Pour on buttered platter.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add milk and vanilla.
Sift dry ingredients together twice and add to mixture. Bake in tube pan for 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: lebkuchen cookies
directions: Beat egg, add brown sugar and beat until fluffy.
Stir in honey and molasses.
Sift together dry ingredients and add to first mixture; mix well.
Stir in fruits, peel and nuts.
Chill several hours or overnight.
On lightly floured surface, roll to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut in rectangles, 3 1/2 x 1/2-inch.
Place on greased cookie sheet.
Bake in moderate oven (350°) about 12 minutes.
Cool slightly before removing from pan.
Makes about 2 dozen.

title: brown sugar brownies
directions: Mix together.
Cook 25 minutes at 325° in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: quick dessert
directions: Break up cake and put in a flat, oblong or square pan.

title: potato cheese casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place 1/2 of potatoes in a 1 to 1 1/2-quart baking dish that has been sprayed with nonstick spray. Top with 1/2 of the Cheddar cheese, then remaining potatoes and remaining Cheddar cheese.
In a blender, combine the remaining ingredients.
Blend until smooth.
Pour mixture evenly over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, for 30 minutes or until light brown. Serves 6.

title: 1 - 10 egg drop soup
directions: Boil soup and water. Beat eggs and water in small bowl with soy sauce. Pour eggs into hot soup and stir while you count to 10.

title: quail cooked in sherry
directions: Season quail with salt; dredge with flour.
Brown in small amount of fat.
Remove; place in casserole.
Combine sherry, Worcestershire sauce and lemon juice.
Pour over quail.
Cover; bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Mix the first 6 ingredients; add milk.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Pour into unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Reduce heat to 350°.
Bake until firm.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg sugar if desired.

title: brussels sprouts with hazelnuts
directions: Cut off stem end of Brussels sprouts.
Soak in cold water 15 minutes, drain.
Place in medium saucepan with 3 cups water and the salt; bring to boiling.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, 10 minutes or until tender.
Drain.
Meanwhile, quarter shelled and peeled hazelnuts.
Saute in hot butter in saucepan 5 minutes.
Toss with drained Brussels sprouts.
Serves 6.

title: apple torte
directions: Sift into bowl flour, sugar, soda and cinnamon.
Add egg, butter and apples.

title: spice cupcakes
directions: Cook raisins and water 20 minutes.
Should have 1 cup liquid left.
Let cool.
Cream butter, sugar and egg.
Sift dry ingredients together and add alternately with raisins, liquid and 1/2 cup walnut meats.

title: french salisbury steak
directions: In a bowl, combine 1/3 cup soup with ground round, crumbs, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape into 6 oval patties.
In frypan, brown patties.
Drain off fat.
Remove patties.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Mix the ingredients together, form in small balls.
Place on cookie sheet, crisscross with a fork.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: maple drizzled apple muffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Line 12 medium cups.
Combine flour, oats, sugar, baking powder and cinnamon; mix well.
Add combined milk, margarine, syrup and egg whites.
Mix just until moistened.
Gently stir in apples.
Fill muffin cups almost full.
Top each with pecan halves, if desired.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until done.
Glaze if you wish.
Makes 1 to 1 1/2 dozen.

title: shoney's strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water and cornstarch until thick.
Stir in jello until well blended.
Mix in strawberries.
Pour into graham cracker pie shell and refrigerate.
Keep refrigerated.

title: rice krispies treats
directions: Melt margarine in large heavy pot over low heat.
Stir in marshmallows and stir over low heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Rice Krispies cereal until well coated.
Pour onto buttered 11 x 15-inch baking sheet pan.
Spread evenly with buttered hands.
Makes 35 treats or more if cut smaller.

title: raisin pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and egg, then add lemon juice and lemon peel, salt, raisins and water.
Cook over hot water for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Cool.
Pour in lined 9-inch pie pan.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until brown.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and margarine in a large saucepan. Stirring constantly, bring to a boil (boil on low heat for 10 minutes).
Remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat by hand until it thickens slightly.
Pour into a greased 12 x 12-inch flat pan or cookie sheet.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Mix ingredients.
Bake at 350° until done.

title: fruited spinach salad
directions: Drain oranges, reserving 1/2 cup liquid.
Set oranges aside. Combine 1/2 cup liquid and gelatin in a small, nonaluminum saucepan; let stand 1 minute.
Place over medium heat; cook 2 minutes or until gelatin dissolves, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; stir in 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice and poppy seed.
Pour into a glass or stainless steel bowl.
Cover; chill 3 hours. Combine oranges, remaining 1/2 teaspoon lemon juice, spinach and next 3 ingredients in a bowl; toss gently.
Arrange spinach mixture on 6 individual salad plates.
Drizzle dressing evenly over salads and sprinkle with sunflower kernels.
Yields 6 servings, about 84 calories per serving.

title: onion rings
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Beat egg, milk and oil together.
Add dry ingredients and beat until batter is smooth. Cover and set aside while preparing onions.
Cut onions into 1/4-inch slices and separate.
Dip a few at a time into batter, then deep fry at 375°.
Turn only once.
Drain on paper towels.

title: southern-style vegetables(southern cooking)
directions: *Slab bacon, fatback or cured ham hocks can be used also.

title: chicken salad spread
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store in refrigerator until ready to serve.
Delicious spread on crackers.

title: orange-cream fruit salad
directions: In large bowl, combine pineapple chunks, peaches, orange sections, bananas and apples; set aside.

title: sprout salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together in large bowl.
Toss lightly with dressing and serve immediately.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown meat; drain and add sauce.
Place noodles in bottom of large pan.
Layer the meat and cheeses.
Place under broiler until melted.

title: josh's saturday morning banana pancakes
directions: Use step stool to place son on to help.
Help son mash bananas (and not make a mess for Mom).
Add cinnamon, allspice, cloves, ginger, nutmeg, sugar, Bisquick, milk, eggs and oil. Add vanilla. Let son stir to remove Bisquick lumps.
Let son taste test.
Pour batter into 3-inch diameter pancakes on griddle.
Heat griddle and cook pancakes on medium low.
Flip pancakes when full of bubbles. Give to son with syrup. (So moist you will not need butter.)
Can substitute low-fat Bisquick one for one.
Serves 4 to 8 people.

title: oatmeal muffins
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Add milk, egg and shortening, stirring only enough to moisten.
Fill greased muffin pans 2/3's full.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.
Makes 12 medium-sized muffins.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Cook together the first 5 ingredients for 6 minutes (let it boil), stirring constantly.
Add the peanut butter and marshmallow cream.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: carrot zucchini bars with cream cheese frosting
directions: Heat oven to 350°; grease 9 x 9-inch baking dish.
Beat together brown sugar, butter and cream cheese in large bowl until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Beat in flour, baking powder and salt until well blended.
Stir in carrots, zucchini and raisins; spoon into pan.
Bake 30 minutes; cool for 10 minutes. Invert cake and cool completely.
Frost, cut into squares.

title: sugar cookies(club member: laine)
directions: Mix shortening, sugar, eggs and flavoring. Blend in flour; cover. Chill at least 1 hour.

title: blueberry banana bread
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour two (9 x 5-inch) loaf pans.
Toss blueberries with 2 tablespoons flour; set aside.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Layer into bowl, shredded cabbage, pepper sliced paper thin, and onions sliced thin.
Drain pimentos and put on top.
Do not stir.

title: strawberry fig preserves
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Set aside for about 45 minutes, then cook 45 minutes to an hour.
Pack in hot jars; seal and process 10 minutes.

title: fresh berry pie
directions: Crush 2 cups berries
and
blend
with	sugar and cornstarch. Cook about 8 to 10 minutes, stirring frequently until thick, smooth
and
clear.
Add
lemon juice and cool mixture thoroughly. Sprinkle
powdered sugar over bottom of baked pie shell.
Place remaining
berries	in pie shell and cover with cooled
mixture. Refrigerate
hours
or
overnight
before serving.
Garnish with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: white coconut cake
directions: Beat egg whites with 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix other ingredients and fold into beaten egg whites.
Bake in three layers at 350°.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Slice tomatoes and onions.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand overnight.
Drain.
Boil sugar and seasoning with vinegar 5 minutes.
Cool slightly; add tomatoes and onions and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack into hot jars.
Seal at once.

title: mini quiches
directions: Generously grease 24 small muffin cups.
Mix Bisquick and margarine.
Add boiling water.
Stir vigorously forming soft dough.
Press rounded teaspoonful on bottom and sides of muffin cups.
Divide bacon in cups.
Beat half and half and egg.
Stir in onions and seasonings.
Spoon 1 1/2 teaspoons in each cup. Sprinkle cheese over top.
Bake at 375° until golden brown, about 20 minutes.
Makes 24 appetizers.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt chips, butter and peanut butter together (do not boil) and cool until one marshmallow does not melt.
Fold marshmallows, coconut and walnuts into pot and mix.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let set.
Cut into small squares.
Yummy!

title: peanutty chocolate chip bars
directions: In large bowl, mix with mixer peanut butter, sugar, corn syrup, butter, eggs and vanilla until smooth.
Reduce speed; beat in flour, baking powder and salt until blended.
Stir in 1 1/2 cups chocolate pieces.
Spread evenly in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan.

title: no-bake pie(cream cheese peanut butter pie)
directions: In a large bowl, with an electric mixer, combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping.
(I use Cool Whip.)
Pour into pie shell.
Freeze 4 to 6 hours.
Thaw 10 minutes before serving.
Serves 8.

title: hot chicken wings
directions: Split wings at joint and discard tips; cut skin off.
Wash and pat dry.

title: green pea casserole
directions: Mix all but last 3 ingredients.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Then top with cheese.
Mix crackers and margarine. Put on top of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sweet and sour green beans
directions: Snip ends of beans and cut into 1-inch slices.
Cook in 1 cup boiling water in covered saucepan.
Save 1/4 cup of liquid from cooking.
Fry bacon until crisp; save 2 tablespoons bacon drippings.
Drain and crumble bacon.

title: apple kuchen
directions: Cut butter into cake mix until crumbly.
Mix in coconut and pat into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.
Arrange pie filling over top.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle on apples.
Blend sour cream and egg well and pour over apples.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: *spanish green beans
directions: Fry bacon, onion and green pepper in heavy skillet until bacon is crisp and onion and pepper are brown.
Add flour.
Stir and add tomatoes, green beans and salt and pepper to taste.
Place in a casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix egg and 10xx sugar together.
Add vanilla and cream cheese. In a saucepan over low heat, mix peanut butter and butter.
Add to sugar mixture.
You may add anything else you desire (ex. marshmallows, nuts, etc.).
Press into a long buttered dish or pan. Chill and cut into squares.

title: rotel chicken
directions: Boil chicken and remove bones.
Set cooked chicken aside.
In skillet, cook onion, mushrooms, pepper, oleo and English peas until tender.
Add salt, pepper and Ro-Tel.
Cook spaghetti in chicken broth and drain.
Melt cheese and add all ingredients together in baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: death by chocolate cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Coarsely chop 8 ounces chocolate squares and set aside.
Microwave the remaining 8 ounces chocolate squares on High for 1 to 2 minutes; stir until all is melted. Add sugar, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Mix in the flour, baking powder and coarsely chopped chocolate squares and chopped nuts. Drop by 1/4 cupfuls onto an ungreased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 13 minutes or until cookies are puffed.
Let cool 1 minute, then transfer to a wire rack to cool. Makes 1 1/2 dozen.

title: stack salad
directions: Put these ingredients in a tall clear bowl in order given. Cover with dressing (recipe to follow). Make sure dressing touches all sides of bowl. Sprinkle Parmesan cheese over top. Crumble bacon over top.

title: cranberry easy barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients in a 2-quart saucepan.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer for 10 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 cups sauce.
Brush on meat or chicken at the end of grilling time.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix cream cheese, ham, lemon juice, onion and garlic. Refrigerate until firm; form a ball and roll in chopped pecans.

title: parsley potato salad
directions: Wash potatoes well.
Cover with water; boil until tender. Cool, peel and cut in 1/8-inch slices.
Combine celery seed, mayonnaise, sour cream, horseradish and salt.
Set aside.
In another bowl, mix parsley and onions.

title: creamy broccoli bake
directions: Cook broccoli.
Beat soup and milk until smooth; pour over broccoli.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Mix Bisquick and butter until crumbly.
Sprinkle over cheese.
Bake until crumbs are light brown, about 20 minutes at 400°.

title: rhubarb cobbler
directions: Place rhubarb in greased 8 x 12-inch baking dish and sprinkle with 1 cup sugar.
Dot with margarine.
Mix dry ingredients and mix in shortening, then stir in egg and milk.
Pour over rhubarb and bake at 350° for 30 to40 minutes.

title: fig pudding
directions: Combine sugar, suet, egg and milk.
Sift flour, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, cloves and ginger, stirring gradually.
Add bread crumbs, raisins and figs; mix well.
Pour into buttered baking dish.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until done.

title: cheesy cauliflower broccoli
directions: Put all ingredients (except onion rings) into large baking dish and stir.
Bake at 350° until all cheese melts, stirring every 10 to 15 minutes.
Bake for 1/2 hour, then top with onion rings.
Bake an additional 10 to 15 minutes.

title: rolls
directions: Break egg into cup and add sugar; fill the cup with oil. Dissolve the yeast in lukewarm water.
Combine with the egg, sugar and oil; mix thoroughly.
Add the flour and milk alternately and make into a soft dough.
Cover and place in the refrigerator until ready for use.
Cut out and let rise for 1 hour before baking. Bake at 375°.

title: old fashion jelly roll
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add sugar slowly and beat until creamy. Fold in flour, mixing lightly.
Add rest of ingredients.
Pour to thickness of 1/3 in shallow low pan lined with wax paper.
Bake 10 minutes in moderate oven.
Unmold on damp cloth. Allow to stand 4 minutes.
Peel off paper. Spread jelly on cake and wrap in wax paper.
When ready, spread with powdered sugar.
Any kind of jelly will do; currant, grape or plum are the favorites.

title: fat-free whole wheat banana bread
directions: Combine flour, baking soda, baking powder and sugar.
Stir to mix well.
Add the banana, prune puree and vanilla.
Stir until moist.
Add walnuts.
Spray loaf pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: western broil with vegetables
directions: Preparation time:
30 minutes.
Marinating time:
6 to 8 hours. Cooking time:
16 to 20 minutes.

title: mud
directions: Make pudding as directed on box.
Add gummi worms to pudding mix.
Smash the cookies, then also add to pudding.
Refrigerate for 45 minutes.

title: red-hot corn relish
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Put in sterilized pint jars.
Makes about 9 pints.

title: top of the world candy
directions: Melt butter and combine powdered sugar, milk, coconut and nuts. Melt chocolate chips in double boiler.
Roll candy into small balls and place on waxed paper. Chill for 1 hour.
Melt paraffin and add to melted chocolate chips.
Leave chocolate mixture over double boiler so it will stay soft. Use fingers or toothpicks to dunk the candy into chocolate.
Place on wax paper after dipped in the chocolate. Candy can be frozen.

title: chocolate mint sticks
directions: Cream sugar and margarine. Add eggs. Mix and add syrup, flour, nuts and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Cool well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Butter oblong Pyrex dish or 2 square ones.
Crumble 1/2 box of Ritz into Pyrex dish.
Cut up 1/2 stick of margarine on top of crackers.
Cut chicken into bite size pieces.
Add 2 layers of chicken and water chestnuts.

title: perfect potato salad
directions: Toss together potatoes, pepper, onion, pimento and eggs.
Mix mayonnaise, mustard, horseradish, salt and pepper together.
Add to potatoes.
Mix well.

title: apple crisp
directions: Fill pie tin half full of apples.
Mix all dry ingredients together.
Followed by melted oleo or butter, stirring well and putting on sliced apples.
Bake at 350° for about 20-30 minutes or until light brown.

title: rice broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine ingredients in buttered, 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Bake for 1 hour.

title: cheesy chicken and rice casserole
directions: Spray casserole dish with Pam cooking spray.
Add cleaned chicken.
Mix soup, milk, rice, mushrooms and seasonings.
Pour over chicken.
Cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: lemon pecan bread
directions: Cream softened butter; gradually add sugar, beating well. Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each addition. Combine flour, soda and salt. Add to creamed mixture alternately with buttermilk, beginning and ending with flour mixture. Stir in the pecans and lemon rind. Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 15 to 20 minutes or until tested done. Cool in pan 10 minutes. Remove loaf from pan and cool. (Test after 1 hour baking, at times may be done.)

title: diabetic sugarless strawberry jam
directions: Sprinkle gelatine over pop in a saucepan.
Add strawberries and simmer 10 minutes.
Take pan from heat.
Add Equal.
Beat with mixer until smooth.
Store in jars in refrigerator.
Yields 2 cups.

title: parmesan crackers
directions: Mix all ingredients until just pulling together. Form into a disc and chill 2 hours or overnight. Flour surface well and roll into a rectangle. Use a ruler and a pizza cutter to cut into squares while on cookie sheet. Prick each with a fork. Bake at 375° until light golden brown, approximately 15-20 minutes. Let cool slightly and re-cut with a pizza cutter.

title: quick zucchini casserole
directions: Layer zucchini, onion, green peppers and cheese of choice in microwavable dish.
May add cooked, drained meat.
Layer if desired (hamburger, turkey, ham, sausage, etc.).
Use 1 can soup to pour over top, but only dilute with 1/2 can milk.
Use mushroom, celery soup, etc.
Cover and microwave until tender. Remove cover toward end of cooking.
Cook 20 minutes on High heat; if more layers repeated, cook longer.
Casserole does make some of own liquid when cooking.

title: cheese triangles 1(tiropetes)
directions: Beat eggs with electric mixer until fluffy.
Add cream cheese and continue beating until well blended.
Remove bowl from mixer. Crumble Feta cheese with fork and combine with egg mixture.
Cut filo 6 x 12-inch.
For each triangle, brush half the filo with melted butter; fold over other half of filo to make a strip about 3 inches in width.
Brush with butter.
Place 1 teaspoon cheese mixture at one end of each strip, folding strip diagonally until triangles are formed.
Brush tops with melted butter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in oven at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve warm.
Makes about 40 triangles.

title: planter's punch
directions: In punch bowl or large pitcher, combine all ingredients, except ice.
Stir and serve over ice.
Makes 2 1/2 quarts.

title: raspberry delight
directions: Melt marshmallows in double boiler.
Add raspberries and juice. Cool.
Whip the whipping cream and add to raspberry mixture.
Mix butter with crumbs.
Put half of crumbs on bottom of 9 x 9-inch square dish and pour raspberry mixture over crumbs.
Cover with remaining crumbs.
Chill in refrigerator 12 hours.
Serves 9.

title: spiced peaches
directions: Drain juice from peaches into saucepan.
Set peaches aside. Into juice place vinegar, sugar, cloves and cinnamon sticks. Bring to boil and simmer 10 minutes.
Pour hot mixture over peaches.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: caramel popcorn
directions: Melt butter in large saucepan.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup and salt.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil without stirring for 5 minutes.
Remove from heat; stir in baking soda and vanilla.
Gradually pour over popped corn in 2 large, shallow baking or roasting pans.
Mix well.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix all ingredients except chocolate chips and paraffin wax well and chill for 1 hour.
Then form into balls the size of your choice.
Melt sweet chocolate with paraffin wax.
Dip balls in chocolate and let dry on waxed paper.

title: whiskey cake
directions: Beat all ingredients together until well blended.
Then take 1 cup chopped walnuts and mix with 2 teaspoons flour.
Fold into cake mixture.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Melt Crisco and cool. Dissolve yeast (both packages) in warm water; add to buttermilk. Add these to flour with sugar added. Put in large bowl and mix. Cover with greased wax paper; refrigerate until needed. Roll out desired amount and cut. Let stand at room temperature 5 or 10 minutes. Bake at 425° until golden.

title: teriyaki(beef-pork-chicken-shrimp-choice)
directions: Combine soy sauce, sugar, oil, ginger and garlic in bowl.
Let meat or shrimp stand in mixture for several hours.
Line a shallow baking pan with foil and arrange meat in pan.
Broil 4 to 5 minutes brushing once or twice with oil.
Turn; brush with oil and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Broil 3 to 5 minutes longer or until done.
Serve on a bed of lettuce.

title: banana oatmeal cookies(sugar-free)
directions: Cream butter with sugar substitute; add eggs, bananas and flavorings.
Sift flour with dry ingredients.
Plump raisins and add other ingredients to flour mixture.
Add flour mixture to egg mixture.
(If batter does not seem to be thick enough, add more rolled oats, a little at a time.)
Drop by spoonfuls on nonstick or lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes. Makes about 60 cookies, depending on size.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Bake in 3 layer pans at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Place oil and uncooked macaroni in a pot of boiling water. Cook until macaroni is tender.
Drain and let cool.
In a large bowl mix macaroni, tuna fish and eggs.
Add mayonnaise, mustard, pickle relish, seasoning and celery to taste.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.
Great when served on a bed of lettuce.

title: whole wheat rolls(yeast bread)
directions: Scald milk.
Add sugar, butter and salt; stir to melt butter. Cool.
Dissolve yeast in water (warm 110° to 115°).
