Add yeast mixture and eggs to milk mixture; mix well.
Add all-purpose flour.
Stir in enough whole wheat flour to make very soft dough. Do not knead.
Place in greased bowl; turn dough in bowl to lightly grease top.
Cover; let rise until double in bulk, about 1 hour.
Punch down.
Turn onto lightly floured pastry cloth; knead until smooth and elastic.
Divide dough into 32 pieces. Shape into balls.
Place in 2 greased 9 x 1 1/2-inch cake pans. Cover; let rise until double in bulk, about 40 minutes.
Bake in 375° gas oven 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from pans; cool on racks. Yield: 2 1/2 dozen.

title: 7-layer salad
directions: Layer salad, starting with lettuce.

title: soupy chili
directions: Brown ground beef and cook with onion and pepper until vegetables look clear.
Combine with rest of ingredients in large pan or crock-pot.
Simmer for at least 4 hours.
Season to taste.

title: marion's candy
directions: Melt peanut butter chips, marshmallows, margarine and Eagle Brand milk.
Butter 9 x 13-inch pan.
Put 1/2 peanuts in the bottom.
Add melted mixture, then rest of peanuts on top. Refrigerate.

title: one dish chicken and stuffing bake
directions: Mix stuffing, 1/2 cup boiling water and 1 tablespoon margarine.
Spoon stuffing across center of a 3-quart shallow baking dish.
Place chicken on each side of stuffing; sprinkle chicken with paprika.
Mix soup, milk and parsley.
Pour over chicken.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.
Bake, uncovered, 15 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Serves 6.

title: nacho popcorn
directions: Place popcorn in large bowl.
Cover popcorn with melted margarine and toss.
Sprinkle with taco seasoning and toss.
Add chips.

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown sausage and ground meat.
Drain.
Mix other ingredients. Place over low heat until cheese is melted.
Spread on rye bread. Freeze on cookie sheet.
When ready to serve, bake at 350° for 10 minutes or in microwave oven, about 2 1/2 minutes.

title: little oatmeal pies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients (except pecans) well.
Pour into unbaked tart shells.
Place one pecan on each pie.
Bake at 350° for approximately 40 minutes.
Let cool and enjoy!
Serves 8.

title: giant stuffed hamburger
directions: In medium saucepan, melt butter or margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add stuffing mix, egg, mushrooms, beef broth, onion, almonds, parsley and lemon juice.
Mix well and set aside.
Combine ground beef and salt.
Divide meat in half.
On sheets of waxed paper, pat each half to an 8-inch circle.
Spoon stuffing over one circle of meat to within 1-inch of edge.
Top with second circle or meat.
Peel off top sheet of paper and seal edges.
Invert meat patty onto a well-greased grill basket.
Peel off remaining paper. Grill over medium coals, about 10 to 12 minutes on each side or until done.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with warmed catsup, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: rice pudding
directions: Place rice in large bowl.
Add sugar, eggs, milk, vanilla, raisins and cinnamon.
Stir thoroughly.
Pour mixture into greased baking dish.
Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.
Makes 6 servings.

title: home canned salsa
directions: Wash and prepare all vegetables.
Wash and sterilize 10 pint jars.
Combine all ingredients and fill jars.
Cook in pressure canner on 11 pounds pressure for 10 minutes.

title: cranberry fluff salad
directions: Mix the cranberries, marshmallows and sugar together and let stand 12 hours in refrigerator.
Then add apples, walnuts, pineapple and salt.
Mix Dream Whip as directed on package.
Add to mixture.
Keep refrigerated.
Makes a large salad.

title: pineapple strudel
directions: Beat egg. Add shortening and water.

Pour into sifted flour and salt, mixing with a knife. Turn onto a floured board. Knead until smooth. Let stand 1/2 hour. Roll until very thin. Spread the pineapple over the top. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar, then dot with butter.
Roll up and pinch edges together. Place on ungreased cookie sheet and twist to form a ring.
Brush with additional slightly beaten egg. Sprinkle with more cinnamon and sugar. Bake at 375° for 35 minutes. Serve with Vanilla Sauce.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown ground beef and onion together.
Add tomato sauce and simmer.
Add cottage cheese; set aside.
Boil noodles in boiling water; drain.
Layer in baking dish: sauce, lasagne noodles and Mozzarella cheese.
Continue until all is used up.
Bake about 25 minutes or until heated thoroughly at 375°, uncovered.

title: red hot applesauce salad
directions: Prepare first four ingredients, melting red hots in liquid. Pour one-half in bowl.
Reserve other half.
Mix last four ingredients and place on jelled mixture.
Pour on the reserved jello.
The second mixture is sandwiched between the jello mixture.

title: green corn pudding
directions: * Corn somewhat older is better.

title: scotcharoos
directions: In large saucepan cook Karo and sugar on low heat.
Bring to a boil and remove from heat.
Add peanut butter.
Stir until melted. Add Rice Krispies.
Stir well until all Krispies are coated. Walnuts can also be added at this time.
In a double boiler melt both packages of morsels together.
In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan put Krispies in.
Flatten until even all around pan.
Spread melted morsels over top.
Refrigerate until hardened.
Cut and enjoy. When finished, Scotcharoos can be left at room temperature.

title: instant miracle rolls
directions: Mix yeast and water. Set aside. Mix flour, soda, sugar and cut in Crisco.
Add yeast to buttermilk and mix until dough is elastic.
Then put desired amount on floured board and knead lightly.

title: peanut butter quickies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart bowl, thoroughly mix all ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Bake about 15 minutes, or until cookies are slightly
puffed but still soft.
Makes approximately 4 dozen.

title: sun burgers
directions: Place first
4 ingredients in bowl.
Blend other ingredients until creamy.
Mix all ingredients together.
Place 1/3 cup measurements on cookie sheet sprayed with Pam.
Press with fork to burger
shape.
Bake
at 400° for 40 minutes, turning once. Makes 1 dozen.

title: crab meat mold
directions: Heat soup
and	gelatin until hot.
Add all ingredients and mold.
Make several hours before you use.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix (dry) pudding and Cool Whip. Add pineapple and mini marshmallows to mixture. Top with cherries and pecans.

title: pumpkin cookies
directions: Cream the butter or margarine and brown sugar; beat until fluffy.
Lightly spoon flour into cup and level off; add soda, baking powder, salt, spices, pumpkin, egg and vanilla and cream mixture.
Drop by spoon onto ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Put first 3 ingredients in top of double boiler.
Place over boiling water; beat with beater for 7 minutes or until thick. Take from fire, add flavoring.
Beat until thick and nearly cold; add baking powder.
Continue to beat until thick enough to spread on cake without running.
Sufficient for a loaf or 2-layer cake.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Place broccoli in a saucepan with about 3 cups of water and bring it to a boil.
Boil broccoli for 10 minutes and set aside. In a large saucepan, melt margarine; saute onion until tender. Add garlic salt, pepper and cream of celery soup; cook until smooth.
Gradually on low heat, add milk until a smooth texture is reached.
Drain broccoli well and add to soup.
Add Velveeta cheese to taste, if desired.
Simmer on low for about 20 minutes. Adjust seasonings to taste.

title: polly's noodle dish
directions: Cook noodles and drain.
Cook meat and onion in butter until tender.
Add tomato soup, cheese, sugar, salt and pepper.
Simmer 15 minutes.
Place noodles in greased baking dish.
Pour meat sauce over and mix.
Top with potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Serve at once.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli according to package directions.
Saute onions and celery in butter.
Add soups and cheese until cheese melts.
Mix altogether and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: french cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except soda, baking powder and flour. When well mixed, add flour, soda and baking powder. Pour into greased and floured cookie sheet.

title: veggie dip
directions: Mix the day before.
Serve with radishes, celery, cauliflower, cucumber, carrots, etc.

title: herb bread
directions: Cut bread diagonally into 1-inch slices.
Blend butter, parsley, dill, oregano and garlic.
Put bread slices together and spread butter mixture on each slice.
Shape tinfoil around reconstructed loaf, boat fashion, twisting ends and leaving top open.
Sprinkle top with Parmesan cheese and parsley flakes.
Heat in 400° oven for 10 minutes or until very warm.

title: grape salad
directions: Wash grapes and dry them.
Mix cream cheese and sugar together.
Add vanilla and sour cream.
Put on grapes and chill.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Bring pineapple to boil and add jello.
Stir until dissolved. Chill until partly congealed.
Add buttermilk and beat until smooth.
Fold in cool whip.
Chill until firm.
Salad is very light if mixer is used for beating.

title: garlic gourmet chicken breasts
directions: Rinse chicken; pat dry.
In nonmetal container, combine sour cream, lemon juice, salt, pepper, paprika and garlic.
Add chicken to sour cream mixture; coat each piece well.
Cover; refrigerate overnight or up to 24 hours.

title: huevos rancheros
directions: Cook the 3 bacon strips until crisp.
Add onions, tomato and jalapeno.
Add salt to taste.
Simmer for about 15 minutes on low. Once all ingredients are tender, cook the 3 eggs, either scrambled or sunny side up (fried).
Serve onion and tomato mixture over eggs.

title: country buttermilk fried chicken
directions: In large bowl, combine 1 cup of buttermilk with 1 teaspoon baking powder.
Rinse chicken and generously salt and pepper both sides.
Place chicken in buttermilk bowl and pour remaining buttermilk over chicken.
Refrigerate at least 1 hour.
Put flour, 1 tablespoon salt, paprika and 1/2 teaspoon pepper in doubled plastic bags or paper sacks.
In large skillet, heat 1/2-inch of vegetable oil to approximately 350° (medium-high).
Place chicken pieces, one at a time, in flour mixture and shake bag until thoroughly coated.
Fry, turning often with tongs, 20 to 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Drain on paper towels before serving.

title: jennie's hasty pudding
directions: Bring berries or cherries and 1 cup of sugar to a slow boil. Sift dry ingredients; add a small lump of butter and enough milk to make a sticky dough.
Drop by spoon in cherry or berry and sugar mixture.
Cover and cook slowly, about 15 minutes.

title: oven chipped potatoes
directions: Layer potato slices in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Melt butter in a small saucepan.
Stir in grated onion, salt and pepper.
Brush potato slices with butter mixture.
Bake in a 425° oven for 45 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Sprinkle with parsley, thyme and shredded cheese.
Bake 15 minutes longer or until cheese is melted.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: california salad
directions: Sprinkle dressing over the cauliflower and mix with mayonnaise and cheese.
Chill and enjoy.

title: fruit slush
directions: Mix all together. Place in freezer in large covered bowl. Remove from freezer occasionally and stir well until frozen. Takes about 2 hours before serving.

title: children's slush
directions: Mix all ingredients except ginger ale.
Freeze.
Add ginger ale when serving.

title: fudge ribbon cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Prepare cake mix as package directs.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
In small mixer bowl, beat cheese, butter and cornstarch until fluffy.
Gradually beat in milk, egg and vanilla. Pour evenly over cake batter.
Bake 50 to 55 minutes. Cool 10 minutes.
Remove from pan. Cool thoroughly. Glaze and serve.

title: teething biscuits
directions: Beat eggs and add sugar, vanilla and flour and mix well.
Roll dough between 2 sheets of floured waxed paper to 1/4-inch thickness.
Cut desired shapes and place on cookie sheet, lightly greased.
Let stand overnight 10 to 12 hours.
Bake at 325°
for 20 minutes.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon, remove skin
and bones.
Combine salmon with remaining ingredients (except
nuts
and
parsley). Mix thoroughly.
Chill several hours.
Shape into
ball or log. Combine nuts and parsley and cover salmon
shape.
Chill
well. Serve with crackers or small rye rounds.

title: cream cheese frosting
directions: Blend well and spread on cool cake.

title: cheese balls
directions: Add all ingredients, except chopped walnuts and parsley; mix well.
Shape into 2 balls (or 3 small balls).
Roll in mixture of chopped walnuts and parsley.
Serve with crackers.

title: pennsylvania dutch style green beans
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon from skillet and crumble. Set aside.
Drain off all but 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Add onion and brown lightly.
Stir in cornstarch, salt and dry mustard.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Mix cream cheese with the tomato soup with hand mixer on low speed.
Add onion and Worcestershire sauce.
Fold in shrimp. Recommend to serve with Ritz crackers.

title: chop suey
directions: Add the onion and celery to the steak or pork.
Fry with meat until browned a little.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Fill frying pan 3/4 full of water.
Cook all together for 1/2 hour; thicken like gravy.
Add the bean sprouts and chop suey vegetables; heat through.
Serve over rice and chow mein noodles.

title: polish pound cake
directions: Grease (very well) and flour an angel cake pan.
Cream butter and Crisco.
Cream shortening with sugar, 1/2 cup at a time.
Beat in 2 tablespoons flavoring.
Beat in 5 eggs, one at a time.
Beat in 1/4 teaspoon salt.
Mix in flour and milk alternately (flour last).
Stir in walnuts and cherries.
Pour into pan.
Place in cold oven.
Set at 300° and bake exactly 2 1/4 hours.

title: muddy buddies
directions: Melt chocolate chips on low heat.
Put Chex in a bowl.
Pour chocolate over the Chex.
Then mix very softly so Chex won't break.
Next, pour powdered sugar over them.

title: chocolate cake
directions: Cook cake mix.
Cook in two layers by directions.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix over medium heat until thick. Pour into baked pie shell. Top with meringue.

title: pecan torte
directions: Using a pastry blender, cut cream cheese and margarine into flour until crumbly.
Press together to form a dough.
Shape into 24 one-inch balls.
Press balls into bottom and up sides of 3/4-inch muffin or torte pans to form shells.

title: economical brownies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar and cream well.
Add melted chocolate. Add egg and vanilla to milk.
Sift flour once, measure; add baking powder and sift again.
Add nuts to flour mixture.
Combine two mixtures and pour into a shallow greased baking pan.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares.

title: white fudge
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Bring to boil; stir only until sugar is dissolved.
Boil to soft ball; remove and let stand (don't stir).
Add vanilla and beat until it loses its gloss (approximately 8 minutes).
Pour into a greased pan to cool.

title: chilli-cheese dip(crock-pot)
directions: Brown ground beef well and drain off excess grease.
Put ground beef and remaining ingredients in crock-pot.
Stir well. Cover and cook on high for 1 hour, stirring until cheese is fully melted.
Serve immediately or turn to low for serving up to 6 hours later.
Serve with tortilla or corn chips.
This recipe may be doubled for 3 1/2, 4 or 5 quart models.

title: chicken chow mein
directions: Heat oil in a 12-inch skillet over low heat.
Mix in onions and celery; sprinkle with salt and sugar.
Add chicken stock; cover and simmer gently for about 10 minutes.
Drain bean sprouts. Mix cornstarch and soy sauce until smooth with 1/4 cup of the bean liquid.
Add to skillet; cook and stir until thickened.
Add drained bean sprouts and chicken; mix and reheat.
Serve with chow mein noodles.
Can also be made with any meat preferred.
It is good without bean sprouts, also, and is good on cooked rice, if preferred.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: unfried chicken
directions: Mix corn flakes, garlic powder, black pepper and red pepper. Set aside.
Dip chicken into broth.
Coat with corn flake mixture. Place chicken on baking sheet.
Bake at 400 degrees for 20 minutes or until chicken is no longer pink.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: oven baked french fries(low calorie)
directions: Cut the potatoes into fries.
In a large bowl, beat the egg whites with a fork until foamy.
Stir in the chili powder and pepper.
Add the potatoes and coat them well.
Spray cookie sheet with Pam and spread in a row.
Bake at 450° for 30 to 35 minutes, until crisp and brown.

title: banana pudding
directions: Make pudding from mix with milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Line dish with wafers, pudding and bananas.
Repeat, ending with pudding.
Chill.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and canned milk.
Boil hard for two minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in oats, cocoa, nuts (or coconut) and vanilla; mix well.
Drop on waxed paper.
Work fast.

title: danish tarts
directions: Mold flour, 1/2 pound butter and cream cheese into dough. Shape into small muffin tins.

title: cornbread
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking pan. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: pink pineapple salad
directions: Sprinkle Jell-O over pineapple and juice. Heat until dissolved. Cool. Combine Cool Whip and milk. Mix thoroughly and add to Jell-O-pineapple mixture. Add nuts, if desired.

title: chicken shortcake
directions: In small saucepan, blend soup and milk.
Add chicken and pimento.
Stir.
Add peas.
Heat gently, stirring now and then. Serve over biscuits.
Makes 4 servings.
Very good.

title: easy taco bake(makes 6 servings)
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat with green pepper and onion; drain.
Stir in seasoning mix, water and dressing; cook 5 minutes over medium heat.
Arrange tortillas, overlapping on bottom and sides of 9-inch pie plate.
Top with meat mixture and salsa.
Bake 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; continue baking 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Let stand 15 minutes.
Top with lettuce, tomato and sour cream, if desired.

title: rice and pork chops
directions: Grease bottom and sides of a 12 x 8-inch shallow pan.
Pour rice evenly over bottom.
Season pork chops with salt and pepper. Place on top of rice.
Spread onion evenly over pork chops.
Pour tomato sauce over all.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour or until pork chops are brown.

title: caramel corn
directions: Bring brown sugar, butter or oleo, Karo syrup and salt to a boil.
Cook 5 minutes.
Remove from heat and add baking soda. Pour over popped corn.
Put in 1 or 2 baking pans in a 250° oven and bake for 1 hour.
Stir every 15 minutes.

title: spinach salad
directions: Mix all ingredients adding mushrooms, cashews, and raisins to your taste.

title: mexican rice dish
directions: Saute onion and peppers.
Mix all ingredients together and place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° until hot.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: On a cookie sheet, roll out crescent rolls like a pizza crust. Bake at 375° until brown.
Let cool.
In a large bowl, mix the cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing until smooth.
Spread mixture over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with chopped vegetables and cut into small squares to serve.

title: ham and broccoli quiche
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Prepare crust as directed on package using 9 inch glass pie dish. Layer ham and cheese in crust. Line pan with broccoli (be sure it is thoroughly dried on paper towels). Combine all remaining ingredients. Beat well. Pour over broccoli. Bake for 35-45 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean. Let stand 10 minutes before serving. Serves 6.

title: spicy molasses cookies
directions: Cream shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat well.
Add egg and molasses, mix well.
Add flour mixture, cream well.
Chill 1 hour. Shape into 1-inch balls and roll dough in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: corn bread taco bake
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Stir in taco seasoning, water, corn, green pepper and tomato sauce.
Pour into 2-quart casserole.
Prepare muffin mix separately plus add 1/2 can fried onions.
Spoon muffin mixture around outer edge of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Top corn bread with cheese and remaining onions. Bake 2 to 3 minutes longer.

title: lamb or chicken kabobs
directions: Combine soy sauce, honey and mustard in glass mixing bowl. Add chicken.

title: dump cake
directions: Place pie filling in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
(Peach is good!)
Pour dry cake mix over fruit.
Melt 2 sticks butter; drizzle over dry cake mix.
That's it!
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. Great warm with Cool Whip.

title: artichoke dip
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in a shallow baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly on top.
Serve warm on crackers.

title: mexican casserole
directions: When in a hurry, go by Hardee's, Captain D's or McDonald's!

title: claudia's granola
directions: Melt over low heat sugar, honey, butter and peanut butter. Add in oats; stir.
Bake in greased pan in preheated oven at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: roast beef yorkshire pudding
directions: While
roast
beef
is cooking, prepare one cup of flour and one cup of milk, 2 eggs and pinch of salt.
Mix together to a smooth batter and let stand awhile.
When meat is ready, take out of pan.
Sauce drippings for pudding.
Put drippings in 9 x 12-inch pan or muffin tins.
Have oven set at 425° and when fat is smoking,
stir
pudding
batter
and pour into pan or muffin tins.

title: eatable centerpiece
directions: Cut cheese in small squares, place toothpicks in each piece. Put in cabbage, place parsley or lettuce leaves or broccoli. Place parsley or some type of greens on top to give appearance of pineapple.

title: five pound loaf candy
directions: Combine sugar, milk, syrup and butter in saucepan.
Cook without stirring until mix reaches 240° on candy thermometer, or forms soft ball in cold water (about 25 minutes).
This scorches easily so watch carefully.
Remove from heat; beat with electric mixer until creamy, about 10 minutes.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour into a buttered 10 x 15-inch pan.
Let stand until set.
Cut into pieces; store in refrigerator.

title: colonial cranberry salad
directions: Combine 1 cup water, sugar and cranberry in saucepan.
Bring just to a boil.
Remove from heat; cover and let cool for about 5 minutes.
Combine 1 cup boiling water, cranberry mixture and lemon juice; chill until partially congealed.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate dessert
directions: Layer bottom of a pan with crackers.
Pour hot pudding mix a little at a time.
Keep putting more crackers and pudding.
It doesn't matter if crackers move.
Just push into pudding.
You can use as many crackers as you like and keep pouring pudding over them.
Let cool in fridge and add Cool Whip and cherries (optional).
Enjoy.

title: kahlua brownies
directions: Bake brownies according to directions, adding nuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour 1/3 cup Kahlua on top while still warm (hot).
Put in freezer for 1 hour.
Spread icing on top.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf or tube pan.
Bake in 350° oven for 60 to 70 minutes.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs and liquids.
Add nuts and mix well.
Store in the refrigerator in tightly covered container. Will keep up to 6 weeks.
Bake as needed at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Yields 60 muffins.

title: company cauliflower
directions: Steam cauliflower until tender.
Fry bacon until crisp, then crumble.
Mix bacon grease into each carton sour cream.
Using a very large, deep casserole dish or dividing in two layers in the following order:
cauliflower, bacon, sour cream and cheeses. Continue to layer until everything is used.
Bake at 350° until the cheese is melted throughout.

title: tartar sauce
directions: In a serving dish mix ingredients thoroughly.
Place in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: kids fruit salad(club member: john waters)
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix until well blended.
Refrigerate. Makes 6 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mushroom pot roast
directions: Dredge meat in flour and brown.
Season with salt and pepper. Add onions.
Mix and add remaining ingredients except mushrooms. Cover and cook slowly for 2 1/2 hours.
Add mushrooms and liquid the last half hour.

title: olive cheese snacks
directions: Blend cheese and butter together until light and fluffy.
Add hot pepper sauce and Worcestershire sauce; mix well.
Stir in flour and mix to form dough.
Shape around olives, using about 1 teaspoon of dough.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake in hot oven at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.
Makes about 30.

title: little wieners
directions: Cut hot dogs in half as well as bacon.
Wrap bacon around hot dog and hold end in place with toothpick.
Place in crock-pot.

title: edna's coffee cake
directions: Mix together brown sugar, white sugar, shortening and spices. Reserve 3/4 cup of this mixture for topping.
Mix together flour, salt and soda.
Add to sugar mixture.
Add buttermilk and egg and beat until mixed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle 3/4 cup reserved mixture on top and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: banana 'n walnut lite delight
directions: Toss bananas with lemon juice.
Layer fresh fruit, yogurt, bananas and walnuts into 4 dishes.
Top with additional chopped walnuts and banana slices.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Cream cheese and sugar; set aside.
Mix pretzels and melted margarine.
Press in 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Spread cheese mixture over pretzels and Cool Whip over cheese.
Chill.
Dissolve jello in hot pineapple juice; add strawberries.
Allow to set, then pour over top and refrigerate.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix all together well.
Pour into pie crust and refrigerate.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt morsels and margarine.
Stir in crumbs and nuts.
Press half of mixture in the bottom of a 13 x 9-inch pan.

title: frozen party salad
directions: Gradually add salad dressing to softened cream cheese, blending well.
Stir in fruit, sugar and red food coloring.
Fold in marshmallows and whipped cream.
Pour into 9 x 5-inch loaf pan. Freeze.
Unmold onto platter.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: sugarless apple pie
directions: Heat apple juice; add cornstarch.
Stir in margarine and cinnamon.
Pour thickened apple juice over apples.
Pour into pie shells.
Cover with crust and bake.

title: spinach dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well and serve, preferably with dip style Fritos.

title: parmesan chicken breast
directions: Dip chicken breasts in melted butter or margarine.
Roll in crumb mixture.
Place on cookie sheet and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: limeade salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients with hand beater.
Makes 1 cup dressing.

title: banana nut bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Beat in egg yolks.
Add banana. Sift all dry ingredients; add alternately with sour cream to banana mixture.
Stir in flavoring.
Fold in beaten egg whites and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes, or until done in center.
Cut into bars while warm.
Ice with a powdered sugar icing.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: kringle
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together thoroughly and refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Divide into 2 to 4 pieces.
Roll each piece into a rectangle.
Fill center third of each with jam, pie filling or preserves.
Fold both sides over and fold ends up.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.
Frost with sugar glaze.

title: texas hash
directions: In electric skillet, heat oil.
Slowly cook onions and pepper until soft.
Transfer to small bowl.
Raise heat; brown meat. Drain fat.
Return vegetables to meat in skillet; add seasonings, tomato juice, tomatoes and rice.
Cover and lower heat to 275° to 300°; cook until rice is soft, usually about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: stuffed grapevine leaves(dolma)
directions: Saute chopped onions in 1/2 cup oil.
Stir until golden. Drain the onions and set them in a bowl.
Add 1 cup raw rice, chopped parsley, salt, pepper and a dash of garlic.
(Meat is optional.)
Mix them all.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Trim pork chops, salt and pepper and flour them.
Saute chops in oil until brown.
Remove from pan.
Add onion and green pepper to pan; saute until tender.
Add tomatoes and rice; season to taste.
Place pork chops on top.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: hobo bread
directions: Pour boiling water over raisins, add soda, sugar, and stir -add oil, salt and let cool.
Add beaten egg and flour slowly.
Bake in 3 cans (these are large soup or vegetable cans).
Fill 1/2 full. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: the three little bears porridge
directions: Get a bowl and put the bag of porridge in it.
Get a measuring cup and put in 5 inches of water.
Put the raisins in, then stir it up until it gets all watery and that's all.

title: chicken-wild rice soup
directions: Combine onion, mushrooms, celery and butter in 1-quart glass mix 'n pour bowl.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are just about tender.
Add water, chicken, wild rice and bouillon.
Microwave on High, uncovered, 5 to 6 minutes or until mixture boils.
Let stand 5 minutes, then microwave on High 2 to 2 1/2 minutes or until hot.
Makes about 2 servings, 310 calories each.

title: date and nut cream candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk together until soft ball will form when dropped into cold water.
Have dates cut into small pieces; put into sugar and stir until dates are melted.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla and beat until nearly thick enough to pour out.
Add nuts and beat until thick enough to pour, so it will spread well.
Pour into dish and when cold, cut into squares.

title: quick and easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Blend all ingredients together in bowl.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: bacon and broccoli salad
directions: Combine broccoli, bacon, onion, raisins and pecans in bowl; mix well.
Add dressing; toss to mix.
Chill for 2 hours.
Yield: 8 servings.

title: honey balls
directions: Cream honey and peanut butter.
Mix with dry milk.
Shape into balls and roll in crushed vanilla wafers.

title: corn-broccoli bake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients and pour into a buttered 1-quart casserole dish.
Add topping made from the last 2 ingredients. Bake 45 minutes at 350°, uncovered.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and dry spinach.
Cut into bite sized pieces.
In a large salad bowl, combine the spinach, onion, bacon and mushrooms.
In a separate bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Blend thoroughly.
Pour over the salad and serve immediately.
Serves 6.

title: prune cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour pan ( 9 x 13-inch).
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Mix all together and bake for 40 minutes.
When done, make glaze and pour on cake while hot.

title: breakfast flash:  dutch oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Melt butter in heavy 10-inch skillet in oven.
Beat eggs vigorously 30 seconds.
Gradually beat in flour. Mix in milk and salt.
Tip heated pan to coat with butter.
Pour in batter; bake 20 minutes.
Lower temperature to 300°.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cut into wedges.
Serve with maple syrup or with melted butter, lemon juice and confectioners sugar.
Serves 4.

title: barbecue carrots
directions: Peel and cut up carrots to desired shape and size.
Cook carrots and drain.
Cook bacon until crisp; crumble.
Saute onion, chopped in a little bacon drippings until tender; drain. Put carrots, bacon pieces, onion, tomato soup, brown sugar and liquid smoke into baking dish and mix well.
Bake in a 350° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Scald milk or tomato juice.
Add to bread crumbs.
Add meat, seasonings and slightly beaten egg.
Pack well in greased pan. Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Serve hot with tomato or brown sauce.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti with eggs and bacon
directions: Cook spaghetti according to package directions.

title: date-nut cake roll
directions: Grease and flour the bottom and sides of a 15 x 10 x 1-inch jellyroll pan; set aside.

title: mercer's frosted orange salad
directions: Mix orange jello, sugar, hot water, cold water and frozen orange concentrate juice
well. Chill slightly, then add crushed pineapple and mandarin oranges.

title: baked apple pie
directions: Slice apples thin.
Mix first 5 ingredients together and pour into pie crust.

title: squash fritters
directions: Combine squash, eggs, onion, seasonings and cracker crumbs. Mix well. Drop mixture by tablespoonfuls in hot oil. Cook until golden brown.

title: popcorn balls
directions: Makes great Christmas gifts.

title: hot apple cider
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Strain; discard fruit and cinnamon sticks.
Serve hot.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread bread with butter, cut off crusts and cut into cubes. Alternate layers of bread cubes and cheese in 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Mix together remaining ingredients and pour over bread-cheese mixture.
Let set several hours or overnight in refrigerator.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, uncovered.
Cut into servings (like a quiche).

title: chocolate zucchini cake
directions: Beat together until light in color the eggs, oil and sugar. Stir in zucchini and cooled, melted chocolate.

Mix well. Stir together the flour, salt, baking powder, soda and cinnamon. Set aside 1/4 cup. Add remaining flour to egg mixture, mixing just to blend. Toss nuts with the 1/4 cup flour and mix until blended well. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Make cream cheese icing.

title: grilled curry fruit
directions: On double thick foil, mix all ingredients.
Wrap in foil. Place on grill for 15 minutes.
Just before serving, stir fruit well.

title: oven steak and gravy
directions: Cut steak into serving size pieces.
Salt with seasoning. Place in casserole dish.
Pour dry soup over steak, then spread mushroom soup over all.
Add small amount of water.
Cover with foil; bake in oven for 2 to 2 1/2 hours at 375°.
Check for tenderness, if need to cook longer.

title: chocolate marble cheesecake
directions: Beat sugar and cheese in bowl.
Add eggs; beat well.
Add vanilla. Measure 2 cups cheese mixture.
Fold this into melted chocolate. Pour remaining cheese into buttered spring-form pan or buttered pie plate.
Add spoonfuls of chocolate mix and swirl with spatula. Bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: turkey cutlets piccata
directions: Have your child crumble up the crackers in a bowl; add the milk and soak for a few minutes.
Add everything else, eggs last. Pour it all into pie crust or a greased casserole and bake it in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, uncovered.

title: 4th of july baked beans(or any time of the year)
directions: Place bacon, onion, bell pepper and garlic in 7 x 11-inch glass baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Microwave on High (100%) 5 minutes.
Stir in beans, brown sugar, mustard, Worcestershire sauce and Creole seasoning.
Cover with wax paper. Microwave on High (100%) 20 minutes, stirring at 10 minutes. Continue to microwave on High (100%) 5 minutes, stirring at 2 minutes.
Let stand, covered, 5 minutes before serving.
Cooking time is 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: simple stew
directions: Mix soups, water and other ingredients.
Cook in covered, greased casserole at 300° for 3 hours.
Take out of oven and stir in carrots and serve with hot rice.

title: beer bread
directions: Mix ingredients in loaf pan.
Bake 1 hour at 375°.
Serve warm.

title: cornbread
directions: Mix together and bake at 450° until done.

title: 7-up party salad
directions: Combine 7-Up and marshmallows. Cook until melted. Add Jell-O. Add hot mixture to cream cheese and beat until smooth.
Add pineapple and nuts. Chill until set, then fold in Cool Whip and Miracle Whip. Chill until firm.

title: puppy chow
directions: Take a pack of country cured ham hocks and put them in a big boiler with lots of water.
Cook slow all day, or until tender. Cool.
Fill small Tupperware bowls or oleo cups.
Keep in freezer and get out as you need to season vegetables.

title: mexican black beans
directions: Heat water and beans to boiling in 2-quart saucepan.
Boil uncovered 2 minutes; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer about 1 hour, stirring occasionally, until beans are tender (do not boil or beans will burst); drain.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Cook and stir until mixture is hot.
Also great served cold.
Makes 4 servings, 135 calories, 1 gram of fat.

title: tangy twist patty melt
directions: With stove on medium/high temperature, place frying pan or griddle iron on stove top.
Grease pan or griddle with one bottle cap full vegetable oil.
Cook ground beef patty as desired.
While cooking patties, saut onions.
In microwaveable dish, melt margarine; add Italian seasoning.
Brush this mixture on outside of bread slices with a basting brush.
Place bread, brushed side down on griddle to brown.
While patties are cooking, place two slices of cheese on top.
Add onions.
With spatula, add patty between toasted bread.
Slice diagonally.
ENJOY.

title: punch
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: curried chicken dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Serve with crackers.

title: broccoli-wild rice bake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook frozen, chopped broccoli according to directions but do not overcook.
Drain in strainer.
Stir in cooked rice, shredded cheese, slightly beaten eggs, milk, margarine, onion, salt and Worcestershire sauce.

title: party punch
directions: Combine in punch bowl or decorative serving pitcher.
Decorate with frozen slices of orange, pineapple and strawberry, if desired.

title: pumpkin pie cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add pumpkin, sugar, spices and milk.
(Do not have to use beater for pumpkin mixture, just blend together well.)
Pour into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Do not use Pyrex.
Sprinkle dry cake mix evenly over top (can take knife and poke cake mix into pumpkin mixture before baking).
Drizzle melted margarine over all of it. Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: banana punch
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients and freeze.
Remove from freezer 3 hours before serving time.
Add crushed bananas and ginger ale.

title: scrambled egg casserole(serves 12 to 15)
directions: Saute ham and green onions in 3 tablespoons butter in a large skillet until onions are tender. Add eggs and cook, stirring to form large soft curds. When eggs are set, stir in mushrooms and cheese sauce. Spoon egg mixture into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan. Combine 1/4 cup melted butter and bread crumbs; spread evenly over egg mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and chill overnight. Uncover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: vegetarian chili with beans
directions: Put textured vegetable protein or crumbled tofu in a bowl with the tomato products to soak about an hour.
Saute the onion, garlic and bell pepper in the olive oil.
Then add the TVP or tofu mixture and spices.
Simmer on low and stir often to keep from sticking and scorching (about an hour).

title: banana split pie
directions: Mix the ingredients for crust and line a 9 x 13-inch pan with them.

title: stroganoff superb
directions: Cut meat into bite size pieces.
In skillet, cook and stir mushrooms and onions in oleo until onions are tender.
Remove mushrooms and onions from skillet.
In same skillet, brown meat on both sides.
Set aside 3/4 cup bouillon; add remaining bouillon, catsup, garlic and salt to skillet.
Stir to mix.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Blend mushrooms and onions into skillet.
Heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil for 1 minute, stirring in sour cream.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: weight watchers strawberry pie
directions: Stirring frequently over medium heat, cook water and cornstarch until bubbles form.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Jell-O and sweetener to taste.
Cool.
Stir in strawberries.
Pour into crust.
Chill.
Serve with or without Cool Whip.

title: divine chicken
directions: Blend bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, parsley, pepper, melted butter and garlic salt.
Dip chicken into butter and the bread crumbs.
Roll each piece into firm roll and toothpick each one. Put in pan to bake at 325° to 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Sprinkle lemon juice and drizzle remaining butter over chicken.
Sprinkle paprika on top.

title: homemade yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, oil, egg and salt.
Mix thoroughly.
Add flour slowly (enough to make dough sticky).
Leave in a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise.
When doubled in bulk, punch down, roll and cut.
Put in greased pan.
Cover and let rise again.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: jelly roll with chocolate frosting
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Break eggs into a large mixing bowl.
Beat at a high speed until thick and lemon colored. Add sugar a tablespoon at a time, beating constantly.
Add vanilla, reduce speed to slow.
Add dry ingredients to egg mixture until well blended.
Bake 15 minutes in a 370° oven.

title: old-fashioned vanilla sugar cookies
directions: Beat shortening with vanilla in a large bowl.
Add sugar gradually, creaming thoroughly.
Beat in the eggs until mixture is light and fluffy.
Add dry ingredients in fourths, alternating with milk in thirds to creamed mixture, beating only until blended.

title: avocado-tomato salsa
directions: Chop tomatoes and avocados into small chunks.
Chop onion. Combine tomatoes, avocados, onion and cilantro in large serving bowl.
Add just enough salsa to hold it all together.
Serve with chips for dipping.
All ingredient measurements may be adjusted to taste.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar and continue beating. Add flour. Add vanilla. Keep beating. Heat milk with the stick of butter just until butter melts. Then add the milk and butter. Beat until blended well. Now add the baking powder. Batter will be thin. Grease and flour a 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: oreo ice cream pie
directions: Crush oreo's in food processor. Melt oleo and add 2 c. crushed cookies. Press into bottom of a 13 x 9 inch dish. Mix puddings and half/half and let set for 5 minutes. Fold together pudding, whipped topping and 1-1/2 c. crushed oreo. Pour filling into crust and sprinkle with remaining cookies on top. Place in freezer. Remove 1/2 hour before ready to serve. Does not melt fast.

title: old fashioned chocolate cookies
directions: Cream butter; add sugar, egg, sour milk and chocolate, melted over hot water (may use cocoa, if chocolate is not available). Sift flour, salt and soda and mix into chocolate mixture.
Add raisins and nuts, if desired, and mix in.
Mix well and drop with a teaspoon onto a buttered cookie sheet; or use more flour and roll out.
Bake in a moderate oven (350°).

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Start with ingredients at room temperature.
Cream butter, Crisco and sugar; add flavoring.
Add eggs, one at the time.
Sift flour and baking powder together twice and set aside.
Mix milk and sour cream together.
Add flour mixture and milk mixture alternately to creamed batter.
Beat and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 290° for 1 hour and 30 minutes or until done.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix together.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until just begins to turn brown.
Cool.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix cake, oil, sugar and sour cream. Add eggs, 1 at a time and mix.
Add poppy seed.
Grease and sprinkle sugar in Bundt pan.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: cheese roll
directions: Have sharp cheese and cream cheese at room temperature for easier mixing.
Mix all ingredients together in a food processor and form into 2 rolls.
Mix:
2 Tbsp. chili powder and 2 Tbsp. paprika together.
Roll cheese in mix to give it an outer coating. Place in refrigerator overnight.
Serve with crackers.

title: slow cooker pork chop casserole
directions: Brown pork chops in skillet, then put into slow cooker. Mix remaining ingredients and pour over pork chops. Cover and cook on low 6 to 8 hours or high 3 to 4 hours.

title: washington apple cake
directions: In large bowl, beat eggs at high speed until light and thick. Combine sugar and oil; beat into eggs.
Stir together flour, cinnamon, baking soda and salt.
Add to egg mixture, along with vanilla.
Stir in nuts.
Spread apples in buttered 13 x 9-inch pan.
Pour batter over apples, spreading to cover.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until top is pale golden and apples are done.
Cool. If desired, spread with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into balls.
Heat Ragu just to boiling; add meatballs.
Lower heat and stir gently.
Let cook about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Meatballs can be cooked on simmer for several hours.

title: easy fruit salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and serve.

title: raspberry coulis
directions: May also use blueberries, apricots, kiwi, strawberries, pears or peaches.
Follow same directions.

title: honey mustard dressing
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients until smooth.
Serve over salad greens.
Serves 100.
Makes about 4 quarts.

title: chicken, pepper and rice medley
directions: Saut chicken pieces in margarine until cooked through; may brown slightly.
Cook rice or noodles while chicken cooks.
Add green pepper strips early or when chicken is nearly done for crisper pepper.
Stir in soup and water and 1/3 to 1/2 package of seasoning to taste.
Simmer 10 to 15 minutes on low heat.
Serve over rice noodles.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: In skillet, brown beef and onion.
Drain grease.
Place in a flat baking dish.
Add a layer of green beans and Tater Tots.
In a small bowl, beat soup and milk; pour over mixture.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.
(You can also put grated cheese over top before baking.)

title: maple flavored syrup
directions: Combine sugars and water.
Stir until dissolved; bring to a boil.
Cover, then boil gently 10 minutes.
Remove from heat; cool slightly and add vanilla and maple extract.
Stir only until mixed.

title: adline's cream of tomato soup
directions: Cook together onion, tomatoes and water.
Strain, if desired. Add soda.
Make a white sauce of rest of ingredients.
Add tomato mixture to white sauce, not white sauce to tomatoes.

title: pecan muffins
directions: Dissolve soda in buttermilk.
Mix all ingredients.
May be kept in refrigerator for up to 6 weeks. Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes in muffin cups.

title: fried bananas
directions: Select ripe bananas. Remove skins; cut bananas in halves lengthwise. Dip into batter made from the egg, flour, milk, sugar and salt. Roll bananas in bread crumbs. Fry the bananas until golden brown. Drain on paper towels; keep hot. Squeeze lemon juice over them before serving.

title: drop brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix brown sugar, butter and eggs first.
Then add other ingredients.
Bake on greased cookie sheets.
Drop and bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomato soup
directions: Simmer first 4 ingredients for 20 minutes.
Melt butter; add flour, sugar and beef bouillon.
Cook and mix with the tomato, celery, onions and bay leaves.

title: deviled eggs
directions: *Let eggs come to a rapid boil.
Cut off and let eggs stand in water for about 10 minutes.

title: sassy slaw
directions: Stir together sour cream, vinegar, sugar, salt and red pepper seasoning in a small bowl.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate for up to 2 days.

title: carolyn's poppy seed dressing
directions: Mix well sugar, salt and mustard.
In blender, add these ingredients and slowly pour in vinegar, onion juice, oil (adding slowly, but steady) and poppy seed (more or less as desired). Serve over lettuce.
Can be used as a topping for chicken salad and fruit.

title: apple yam casserole
directions: Mix together cinnamon, nutmeg, brown sugar, flour and oats. Cut in butter until crumbly.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In lightly greased 2-quart casserole, spread 1/2 of applesauce.
Spoon 3 tablespoons of the topping over the applesauce.
Evenly arrange the potatoes over the base.
Add remaining applesauce to cover yams.
Add the rest of the topping and spread evenly.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until heated through.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Skin, boil and cut up chicken breasts.
Stir drained Veg-All, peas, soup and broth together with cut up chicken.
Pour into casserole dish.
In blender, mix 1 stick softened butter, 1 cup flour and milk.
Blend together and pour into other ingredients in casserole.
Cook about 1 hour at 350° or 400°.
Cover with aluminum foil if needed.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pear bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix oil, eggs, sugar, vanilla and pears.
Mix all together. Bake in a large loaf pan at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: caramel squares
directions: Beat together first 2 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream together well and add about 2 tablespoons pineapple juice and nuts, if desired.

title: fish chowder
directions: Chop potatoes, celery and onion.
Add pepper, celery salt and olive oil in a large cooking pot.
Simmer for 3 minutes.
Add fish; simmer 2 more minutes.
Melt sour cream in 1 cup of hot water, then pour over fish with soup.
Stir for 5 minutes over medium heat.
Add milk; bring to a boil while stirring.
Simmer for 1 hour.

title: cheese bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in the cheese. Add the eggs, milk and oil but stir only until all of the dry ingredients are moistened.
Pour the dough into a greased loaf pan. Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour or until loaf is firm in center.
Let cool in the pan for 5 minutes and then cool on a rack.

title: coleslaw
directions: In a small bowl, blend the mayonnaise, vinegar, sugar (Splenda), celery seed, salt and pepper. Mix well. In a large bowl, combine the cabbage and carrots. Pour the dressing over the mixture and blend well. Refrigerate.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Boil chicken until chicken falls from bones.
Remove skin and dice.
Cook broccoli as directed. Alternate layer of chicken, broccoli and chicken in greased baking dish.
Top with sliced cheese.
Pour cream of celery soup over cheese.
Mix herb stuffing (per directions on package) and place on top of soup.
Bake 35 to 45 minutes.
I usually add more soup and cheese and a little less stuffing mix.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Pare potatoes.
In saucepan, heat 1 inch salted water (1/2 teaspoon salt to 1 cup water) to boiling.
Add potatoes.
Cover; cook for 30 to 35 minutes, or until tender.
Drain; set aside.
In large skillet, fry bacon until crisp; remove and drain.
Cook and stir onion in bacon drippings until golden brown.
Blend in flour, sugar, salt, celery seed and pepper.
Cook over low heat, stirring, until mixture is bubbly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in water and vinegar; heat to boiling, stirring constantly.
Boil and stir 1 minute.
Crumble bacon.
Thinly slice potatoes.
Carefully stir bacon and potatoes into hot mixture.
Heat through, stirring lightly to coat potato slices.
In skillet, brown bratwurst in shortening, turning with tongs; do not pierce with a fork.
Serve with potato salad.
Makes 5 to 6 servings.

title: easy homemade pizza
directions: Rub cooking oil on both sides of crusts; place in pans.
Layer sauce, pepperoni, ground beef, onions, green peppers and cheese. Top with mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: crab bake
directions: Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Combine baking mix, 1 cup of the cheddar cheese, milk and half of the melted butter in a medium bowl. Mix by hand until well-combined. Pat out the dough into a circle approximately 8 inches in diameter, with a slight lip around the edge (like a pizza crust). Sprinkle the parsley over the top of the dough. Be sure the dried parsley flakes are crushed fine. You can easily crush the flakes in a small bowl with your thumb and forefinger. Sprinkle the crab over the top of the dough. Sprinkle the remaining cheese over the crab. Don't go all the way to the edge of the dough - leave a margin of 1/2-inch or so around the edge. Bake for 14 to 16 minutes or until the cheese on top begins to slightly brown. Combine the remaining butter with the garlic powder and brush it over the top of the bake as soon as it comes out of the oven. Slice it like a pizza into 8 pieces and serve hot.

title: strawberry fizz
directions: Place 1 teaspoonful of strawberry syrup into each glass.
Pour seltzer water into each glass until it is 2/3 full.
Stir syrup and seltzer water briskly until they are mixed.
Don't let it bubble over.
Place a scoop of vanilla ice cream into each glass. Top with a lot of sliced strawberries.
Place a straw in each glass and serve.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, lard and buttermilk.
Add the spices and then the molasses.
Rinse the molasses bottle with 3/4 full of warm water and add to mixture.
Add the flour until it's at a consistency that can be rolled out on the table.
Cut into large circles or gingerbread man shapes.
Bake at 375° for 6 to 7 minutes.
Once cool, ice with powdered sugar icing.
Yields approximately 12 dozen cookies.
Recipe can be cut in half.

title: seven-cup salad
directions: In large bowl, combine all ingredients.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours, or at least one day.
The reason for this is the salad actually improves in taste after it sits in refrigerator.

title: vanilla covered strawberries
directions: In medium microwave-safe bowl, place vanilla milk chips and shortening for 30 seconds; stir, stir.
Microwave an additional 15 seconds at a time until smooth.
Holding by top, dip 2/3 of each strawberry into vanilla mixture; shake gently to remove excess. Place on wax paper-covered tray.
Refrigerate until coating is firm.
Store, covered, in refrigerator.
Makes about 3/4 cup of coating.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add egg and vanilla.
Mix well. Sift dry ingredients and stir into creamed mixture.
Refrigerate 2 to 3 hours.
Heat oven to 375°.
Divide dough in half and roll out on dough sheet.
Cut with cookie cutter to desired shape and bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: no fail biscuits
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Cut in Crisco until mix is about the size of peas.
Add milk.
Stir until blended.
Pat dough on floured board about 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with 2-inch cutter.
Bake 18 minutes at 400°.

title: betty ford's chocolate icebox dessert
directions: Slice angel food cake and layer in a 9 x 9-inch cake pan that has been lined with wax paper.

title: 3 layer crackers
directions: Combine the sugar, brown sugar, graham crackers, milk and margarine in saucepan. Stir until dissolved and boil on medium for 2 minutes.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan, layer the Club crackers, then hot mixture, then crackers. Melt the peanut butter, chocolate chips and butterscotch chips.
Spread over top and chill. Cut into squares.

title: ham delights
directions: Combine all ingredients in bowl. Split rolls in half; spread mixture over rolls evenly. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: peach pecan pie
directions: Combine egg, pie filling and salt.
Add corn syrup, pecans and vanilla.
Pour into a pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce oven temperature to 325°.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes longer or until set.

title: lebanese green beans
directions: Saute the garlic and onion in oil. Add seasonings and remaining ingredients; mix well. Cook together over low heat for about 15 minutes.

title: corn supreme
directions: Heat cream of chicken soup.
Add Shoepeg corn, whole kernel corn and chopped onions.
Cook 10 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: baked potatoes
directions: Prick potatoes with fork.
Wrap in foil.
Place potatoes in crock-pot (do not add water).
Cover and cook 8 to 10 hours.

title: swedish spritz cookies
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix together the butter, eggs, sugar and flavoring.
Add flour to mixture slowly.
Add food coloring, if desired.
Put part of cookie dough in cookie press and force onto ungreased baking sheet.
Bake until firm, approximately 8 minutes.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook and drain squash.
Drain and chop pimento.
Melt margarine and stir in stuffing.
Line a 2-quart dish with 1/2 of mixture.
Mix other ingredients and spoon on top of stuffing in dish.
Cover with balance of stuffing and bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.

title: cream pie
directions: Cream the cream cheese and sugar.
Add Cool Whip.
Pour into graham cracker crust and top with your favorite pie filling.

title: carrots almondine
directions: Cook carrots, covered in 1/2 inch boiling water, 8 minutes; drain.
Turn carrots into a 1-quart baking dish.
Stir in raisins, butter, honey, lemon juice and ginger.

title: ravioli
directions: Brown meat and minced garlic.
Add tomato sauce and tomato soup.
Chop olives and mushrooms; add.
Cook macaroni and drain. Combine remaining ingredients and add sugar if desired.
Let simmer about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese (to taste) on top.

title: chicken and pasta salad
directions: Prepare salad dressing.
Mix with oil, vinegar and water as directed on package; set aside.
Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain; rinse with cold water and drain.
Combine pasta, vegetables, chicken and cheese in large bowl.
Toss with salad dressing.
Chill.
Serve on a bed of lettuce, if desired.
Makes 8 servings.

title: lazy way soup
directions: Throw it all together (except for seasoning packets) in the biggest pot you can find (8-quart).
Add a cup or so of water, if there's room.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat and simmer a couple hours.
After simmering about an hour, add contents of seasoning packets and a little more water if needed.
tags: frozen Pictsweet vegetable for old fashion soup with seasoning
frozen Pictsweet vegetable for New Orleans gumbo with seasoning

title: bob hope's favorite lemon pie
directions: Combine cornstarch and sugar, add water slowly, stirring constantly, until thick and smooth.
Add slightly beaten egg yolks, butter, lemon rind and juice and salt. Cook 2 or 3 minutes. Pour into baked shell.
Cover with meringue.
Bake in slow oven 15 minutes or until light brown.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Sift together flour, soda, baking powder and salt.
Beat together sugar and egg.
Alternate adding fruit cocktail juice and fold in fruit.
Bake in ungreased pan.
Mix together 1/2 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup nuts.
Place on top of mixture.
Bake until done.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Cook spaghetti and set aside.
In a skillet, brown ground beef with onions.
Add next 5 ingredients and simmer for 10 minutes. Spoon over spaghetti and sprinkle with cheese.
Serves 4.

title: frosted date balls
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add milk, vanilla, flour and salt. Blend in dates and nuts.
Roll in 1-inch balls and place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Roll in additional confectioners sugar.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Tear up bread and place pieces in a greased baking dish, 13 x 9 x 2-inches.
Brown and drain sausage or links in skillet.
Drain off fat.
Spoon meat over bread.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Beat together eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Pour over mixture in baking dish.
Bake in preheated oven for 35 to 40 minutes.
Cheese will rise to top during baking.
Can prepare the night before; cover and refrigerate.
Breakfast cooks without any effort.
Try serving along with fruit cups.

title: swiss broccoli casserole
directions: Thoroughly combine soup and milk.
Arrange broccoli in an 8 x 12-inch baking dish.
Layer eggs, 1/2 can onions, soup mixture and cheese over broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top with remaining fried onions.
Bake 5 minutes longer.
Serve hot.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and Crisco; add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs (one at a time), alternating with the flour and milk.
Beat well.

title: three corn casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix butter, sour cream and egg.
Stir in both corns.
Blend in dry muffin mix and spoon into a well-greased casserole.
Bake for 1 hour until puffed up, golden brown and crispy on top.

title: joe ironside chicken noodle soup
directions: Bring water to boil with bouillon cubes and broth.
Add carrots and pimiento and continue to boil.
Add noodles and a few minutes later add chopped chicken.
Cook until noodles are tender, approximately 7 minutes.
Thicken with flour.
It will be thicker the next time it is used, but a little milk can be added.

title: holiday peas
directions: Saute celery and onion.
Add remaining ingredients and heat thoroughly.
Serves 4.

title: uncle butch's orange walnut bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients. Mix wet ingredients, then add to the dry ingredients. Add nuts. Spray 2 (1-pound) coffee cans inside with Pam. Pour half of batter into each can. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: stir-fry
directions: Using electric frypan, put sliced meat in pan with approximately 1/2 cup of water and cook at 350° for approximately 20 minutes.
As meat is cooking, prepare vegetables and add to meat; cook for approximately 30 minutes or until tender.
Add can of soup with approximately 1 cup of water and simmer for 10 minutes.
Add pepper.
Serve.

title: red pepper relish
directions: Put peppers and onion in food processor for a few seconds, then combine with other ingredients.
Cook on high heat about 30 minutes.
Keep stirring to prevent sticking.
Keeps a long time in refrigerator.
Good on hot dogs, hamburgers or to eat with green vegetables.

title: puffy paint
directions: Mix flour, salt and water in a small bowl.
Add several drops of food coloring, stirring until you get a desired shade.
Make a few batches in different colors.
Pour the puff paint into plastic squeeze bottles (empty ketchup or mustard containers).
Squirt onto heavy paper or cardboard.
As paint dries, it will become puffy and textured.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: In a saucepan, saute onion in butter until tender. Stir in flour until blended. Add the tomatoes, sugar, oil, salt and pepper. Bring to a boil. Cook and stir for 2 minutes or until slightly thickened. Stir in toast cubes. Yields 6 servings.

title: graham muffins
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking soda and baking powder together.
With a fork, beat together egg, buttermilk and butter. Pour all at once into flour mixture.
Stirring as little as possible, moisten the flour.
Batter is not smooth.
Bake in muffin pans at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: my stromboli
directions: The ingredients can be changed to suit your taste.
Be creative.

title: pickled red beets and eggs
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1 1/2 cups liquid.
Place beets and liquid along with all other ingredients; mix well and cook until thickened.

title: baked fish
directions: Place fish in single layer in greased pan (use olive oil). Sprinkle with salt, pepper and oregano.
Add 1/2 cup olive oil. Add tomatoes, scallions, parsley and garlic.
Top with bread crumbs, covering fish completely.
Dot with butter.
Add 1 cup water and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Decorate with onion rings, olives and lemon.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Combine sugar, flour, baking powder and nutmeg in mixer bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and beat well. Pour filling in pie crust and bake 15 minutes.
Reduce oven temperature to 350°.
Bake until knife inserted in center comes out clean, about 45 minutes longer.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir. Chill until slightly set.
Add pineapple and nuts.
Pour half of mixture into an oiled 9-inch square pan.
Chill slightly.
Fold sour cream into remaining Jell-O mixture and pour over other mixture.
Chill until firm.

title: cabbage rolls
directions: Cook rice in water with salt.
Combine tomato juice, sugar, pepper, garlic powder and oregano.
Pour into large roaster. Cut out core of cabbage and cook in kettle to half cover cabbage. Leaves can be cut away and removed as they get tender.

title: caramel apples
directions: Melt the butter in heavy saucepan.
Stir in the brown sugar, syrup and milk.
Mix well.
Bring to a boil, stirring frequently. Cook to firm ball stage (245°), stirring frequently.
(Takes about 15 to 20 minutes.)
Remove from heat and stir in the vanilla extract.
Put a wooden stick in each apple core and dip in mixture. Place on waxed paper to allow caramel to set.
Store in a cool, dry place at room temperature.

title: easy light wings
directions: Combine all ingredients, except wings, in blender.
Blend until smooth.
Place chicken wings on rack in shallow baking pan. Brush with apricot sauce.
Bake in 425° oven for 30 minutes, basting with sauce every 15 minutes.

title: million dollar pie
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Put in pie crusts and chill.

title: chinese chews
directions: Cream sugar and eggs until fluffy.
Add salt and baking powder to sifted flour.
Mix dates and nut meats in flour mixture; add vanilla.
Mix well with sugar and egg.
Pour into well-greased shallow pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cool and cut in squares.

title: taco dogs
directions: Combine hot dogs and taco sauce; bring to a boil.
Spoon into heated taco shells and top with cheese, lettuce and sour cream.

title: salsa
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve as a dip.
It is better if you leave mixture in refrigerator overnight but not necessary.

title: french fried shrimp for 100
directions: Wash shrimp and drain well.
Dredge shrimp in mixture of flour, salt, pepper and paprika.
Shake off excess.

title: lemon bars
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine flour, butter and 1/2 cup powdered sugar.
Mix thoroughly.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot apple butter
directions: Peel and slice apples to fill crock-pot.
Cook on low for 18 hours (do not lift lid while cooking).
Remove lid and stir well (may use mixer).
Add sugar and spices.
Cook 4 additional hours with lid off, stirring occasionally.
Put into jars and seal tops.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add sugar; stir well until dissolved.
Add fruit and nuts.
Refrigerate.
Can be frozen for future use.

title: s o s
directions: Cook beef with butter until edges curl.
Stir in flour and add milk at same time.
Cook and stir until bubbly.
Stir in Worcestershire sauce and pepper.
Spoon over buttered toast.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Put in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Mix eggs with milk and add salt, garlic salt and mustard. Beat well and pour over sausage.
Top with cheese and refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: cheese dip
directions: Cut up cheese and place in a double boiler with just a touch of milk for creaminess.
When melted, stir in picante sauce. Serve warm.

title: no weeping meringue
directions: Combine cornstarch, 2 tablespoons sugar and water.
Cook until mixture thickens.
Set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites until stiff; add 5 tablespoons sugar gradually.
Continue beating until very stiff.
Add the cooked mixture (which must be cold) beating well.
Add a few drops of vanilla.
Pile on pie and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Open door, let pie remain in oven a few minutes longer before removing to cool.
This helps prevent the meringue from falling.

title: hungarian sunday soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except potatoes and noodles, into large soup kettle.
Bring to a boil and lower heat so soup bubbles gently.
Cover and cook 3 hours.
Add whole potatoes and cook 1 hour more.
Serve broth over noodles.

title: enchiladas roja
directions: Fry one big onion in bacon grease; brown.
Add 2 tablespoons flour.
Add tomato sauce.
Add the remaining ingredients, except cheese, olives and green onions.
Dip tortilla in sauce, fill with ripe olives and chopped green onions.
Roll and cover with grated Colby cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and 1/2 can of the onions.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Add remaining onions; bake for 5 minutes. For main dish, you may add ground beef.

title: sugar starch
directions: Cook over heat and when completely dissolved, simmer.
Remove from heat.
Let set 10 minutes.
Starch doilies and let dry and iron or block.

title: old fashioned butterscotch meringue pie
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and salt in medium size saucepan; gradually stir in milk.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture comes to a boil and is thickened.
Boil 1 minute; remove from heat.
Slowly stir into egg substitutes, about 1/2 cup of hot mixture; slowly stir back into remaining mixture in saucepan.
Cook, stirring constantly, over low heat, 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in margarine, vanilla and maple flavoring; pour into pie shell.

title: chili dog soup
directions: In Dutch oven, brown meat; drain.
Stir in wieners, undrained tomatoes and rest of ingredients.
Simmer, covered, for about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.
Remove bay leaf.
Serve in bowl topped with grated cheese, chopped onions and corn chips.

title: corn casserole
directions: Make
a sauce of margarine, flour, milk and seasonings. Add corn, slightly
beaten egg and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour in a baking dish.
Cover
with
buttered
crumbs and bake in a moderate 350° to 400° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Rub potatoes with shortening.
Prick with a fork.
Bake until potatoes are tender, 1 to 1 1/4 hours. Increase oven temperature to 400°. Cut slice from top of each potato.
Scoop out inside, leaving a
thin shell.
Mash potatoes. Add milk in small amounts, beating after each addition.
Add margarine, salt and pepper.
Beat until fluffy.
Fill shells with potatoes.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese.
Bake until golden, about 20 minutes.

title: chocolate no-bake cookies
directions: Boil margarine, sugar and milk 2 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper.
Let set.

title: french vanilla ice cream(club member: ashley wilson)
directions: Mix sugar, salt, milk and egg yolks into saucepan. Cook over medium heat. Stir constantly until bubbles appear around edge of mixture in pan. Cool to room temperature.

Stir in vanilla and cream. Pour into freezer can and put dasher in place. Cover can. Fill freezer with alternate layers of ice and rock salt. Turn on mixer. Let run until it stops. Let ice cream set until it ripens.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Arrange sauerkraut in bottom of 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Layer corned beef over kraut.
Layer Swiss cheese.
Combine mayonnaise and salad dressing, spread evenly over the cheese.
Cover with tomato slices, toss bread crumbs in melted butter.
Sprinkle over the top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: tomato catsup
directions: Crush tomatoes through colander or sieve.
Combine all ingredients in a large pan and cook slowly until thick enough. Bottle or put into jars.

title: zucchini squash casserole
directions: Layer the ingredients in a buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Sprinkle with a little brown sugar, dash of pepper, 2 teaspoons sweet basil and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Cover and bake at 350° for 2 hours.
Check it after 1 hour.

title: easy wassail(mulled cider)
directions: Put in a large pot and bring almost to a boil; turn down and let simmer for several hours.
Very good at Thanksgiving and Christmas holidays.
Makes the house smell great too!

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bone.
Set aside.
Mix soups and sour cream.
Crush crackers; mix with melted margarine.
Put crackers on the bottom of casserole dish (reserve 1 cup of crumbs).
Layer chicken over crackers.
Pour soup mixture over chicken.
Top with remaining crackers.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fresh broccoli salad
directions: Chop day before if you like.
Dressing added 2 hours before serving.
Chill.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add melted chocolate.
Beat yolks. Add water and vanilla; blend.
Gradually add yolk mixture to chocolate mixture and beat until light and fluffy.
Sift together flour, salt and baking soda.
Alternately add flour mixture and milk, blending well after each addition.
Beat egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold in batter.
Turn into greased and floured 9-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until cake springs back when lightly touched.

title: crustless leek and potato quiche
directions: Preheat the oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a 10-inch quiche dish or pie pan.
Set aside.
In a 10-inch skillet, melt butter over moderate heat.
Add leeks, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Cook for 1 minute.
Add the water; simmer, covered, for 12 minutes.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat sugar, flour, Karo syrup, eggs, salt, vanilla and butter together.
Add pecans.
Bake in an unbaked pie shell at 250° for 1 hour.

title: butterscotch squares
directions: Melt butter.
Add sugar.
Bring to a boil.
Cool.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Stir in vanilla, flour and baking powder.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: coca-cola cake
directions: Sift flour and sugar together.
Heat butter, cocoa and Coca-Cola; pour over flour and sugar.
Add all other ingredients except marshmallows and pour into a 10 x 13-inch pan.
Add marshmallows on top.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 55 minutes.
Let cool.

title: southern corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs in a medium bowl.
Add cornstarch, salt, sugar and melted margarine.
Mix well.
Add drained corn and scalded milk; blend with egg mixture and stir until smooth.
Pour into a well buttered casserole and bake at 350° until firm, approximately 40 minutes. Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: toffee apple pie
directions: Prepare pie crust according to package directions for a filled 1 crust pie using 9-inch pie pan. (Refrigerate remaining crust for another use).
Preheat oven to 375°.

title: pumpkin spice cookies
directions: Cream sugar and margarine until light and fluffy. Blend in egg. Add combined flour and spice. Mix well. Chill. Roll out dough onto lightly floured surface to 1/8 inch thickness. Cut with 3 inch round cookie cutter. Place on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 6 to 8 minutes or until edges are very lightly browned. Cool

title: sausage and egg breakfast pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brown sausage in skillet until no longer pink.
Separate rolls into eight triangles.
Place in ungreased 12 inch rimmed pizza pan with points toward the center. Press together; seal perforations and form a circle one inch larger in diameter than pan bottom.
Turn edges under to make a slight rim.
Sprinkle cooked sausage over crust.
Top with potatoes; add peppers and green onion, if desired.
Sprinkle with cheddar cheese.
Stir eggs, milk, salt and pepper in a small bowl; pour evenly over pizza.
Sprinkle with parmesan.
Bake 20 minutes or until eggs are set and crust is golden.

title: hot apple cider punch(crock-pot)
directions: Put cider and oranges or orange juice in crock-pot.
Put all spices in linen bag (square of cloth tied tight to hold spices). Put in crock-pot with juices and set on low.
Plan on letting cook in crock-pot at least 8 hours before serving.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Cream butter well; add sugar slowly and mix well.
Drop in egg yolks; beat 1/2 hour.
Add vanilla, nuts and pineapple. Arrange layer of crumbs in buttered pan, then a layer of fruit mixture and then crumbs, continuing until pan is filled.
Top with crumbs.
Let
stand
24 hours or longer in refrigerator. Serve with whipped cream.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Make juice from tomatoes.
Cook peppers, onion and garlic until well done.
Put in a blender.
Mix all ingredients.
Cook until thick, about 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: deviled egg filling(sandwich spread)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Yields 1 1/4 cups.

title: ampa's peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, syrup and water on medium heat until it spins a light strand from a fork. Do not stir. Add the peanuts.
Cook until brown spots appear on top of the mixture. Add soda and stir as you remove from heat.
Pour out immediately on well buttered flat pan.
Let cool.

title: refrigerator bran muffins
directions: In a large bowl, combine the first 5 minutes.
Make
a well; add eggs, buttermilk and oil.
Stir just enough to moisten dry ingredients.
Cover and store until ready to bake up to 6 weeks. When ready to cook, spoon into greased muffin pans 2/3 full.
Bake at 400°
for 12 to 15 minutes.
To vary muffins, I add chopped pecans to the batter I am cooking, not to the big batch.

title: chicken pie
directions: Cook the chicken in salted water until tender.
Remove from bones and lay in bottom of baking dish.
Prepare gravy as follows: Mix melted butter, flour and pepper together.
Add broth and milk.
Let cook to bubbling and pour over chicken, reserving some for gravy boat.
Place dish over heat to keep hot while preparing crust.

title: deviled eggs florentine
directions: Peel the eggs; cut into halves.
Remove yolks to small bowl; set aside.
Cook frozen spinach according to package directions; drain thoroughly, pressing out excess water.
Place spinach in blender or processor with sour cream, salt, nutmeg and cayenne. Puree.
Mixture will be a little dry, so scrape down sides of bowl and start blender up 2 or 3 times.
Spoon mixture into a bowl; set aside.
Use a fork or blender to mash the yolks with mayonnaise, mustard and salt.
Spoon spinach mixture into each egg half.
With a decorating bag, pipe yolk mixture over top, or use a fork to do so.
Sprinkle each egg half with paprika before serving.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Heat applesauce to boiling hot.
Sprinkle jello on applesauce and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat; add ginger ale and blend well.
Pour into individual molds or one larger mold.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sugar, flour and salt together.
Beat egg yellows and add with milk. Stir all ingredients together and heat until boiling on medium heat. Stir continuously.
Layer wafers, bananas and pudding.
End with a layer of wafers on top.
Enjoy.

title: chicken-apple salad
directions: Mix all ingredients in a large bowl.
Chill until ready to serve.

title: soft pretzels
directions: Soften dry yeast in warm water.
Add salt, sugar and flour. Knead, then roll into ropes and twist into pretzel shape.
Brush with beaten egg and sprinkle with coarse (kosher) salt.
Let rise until desired size.
Bake at 425° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: mexican wedding cakes
directions: Mix butter and powdered sugar.
Add other ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Chill dough.
Roll into small balls and bake until done, about 8 to 10 minutes, at 375°.
When done, roll in powdered sugar.

title: fruit salad or dessert
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar; fold in drained pineapple, then add other ingredients.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch dish and freeze.
