title: coconut and peanut butter cookies
directions: In large bowl beat butter and peanut butter until blended. Add sugar; beat well.
Beat in egg, salt and vanilla.
Stir together flour, soda and baking powder.
Stir into butter mixture until well blended.
Stir in coconut.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook for about 25 to 35 minutes. Excellent for chicken wings or canning for a later use.

title: golden mushrooms
directions: Rinse, pat dry and trim fresh mushrooms or drained canned ones.
Set aside.
In small paper or plastic bag, combine corn flake crumbs, Italian seasoning, salt and pepper.
Dip mushrooms into half and half, then into bag with corn flakes and shake to coat.
Place on a cookie sheet.
Bake in preheated oven for 15 minutes at 350°.
Serve warm.

title: rice pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Put into well buttered deep baking dish. Bake in a 350° oven for 2 hours or until soft, stirring once or twice before it starts cooking.

title: tuna wedge
directions: Turn oven to 350°.
Mix Bisquick and water and make a dough. Roll it and place it on a pizza pan.
Make sure to push up the sides slightly.
Bake in oven for approximately 15 minutes (until light brown).
Let it cool.

title: creamy coleslaw
directions: In a large salad bowl, toss cabbage, carrots and green pepper. In a small bowl, combine the remaining ingredients.
Pour over the cabbage mixture and toss to coat.
Chill for at least 2 to 3 hours.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: cinnamon buns
directions: Soften yeast in 1/2 cup lukewarm water.
Scald milk.
Add 2 tablespoons sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm; add yeast.
Stir well.
Beat in eggs and 4 tablespoons butter.
Add flour, stirring, until moderately firm dough is formed.
Turn dough out on lightly floured board; knead until dough is smooth and not sticky.
Roll up; cut into slices.
Put buns on buttered baking sheet.
Cover; let rise 30 minutes (or double in bulk).
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until brown.
Makes 24.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 13-inch dish.
Put chicken on top.
Pour Veg-All on top of chicken.
Mix cream of chicken soup and chicken broth together.
Pour on top of Veg-All.
Mix Bisquick and milk. Pour on top and bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chocolate sin
directions: Bake cake per instructions.
Cool and cut into 4 layers.
Make pudding per instructions.
In large deep bowl, layer cake, pudding, Cool Whip, candy, repeat layers.
Top with whipped cream.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Cook corn bread according to package directions. Cool. Crumble into pieces in a large bowl. Add rest of ingredients. Toss.
Add which dressing desired.
Mix well.
Chill for at
least 2 hours or more before serving.

title: elip's knock yo' teeth out barbecue sauce
directions: Mix jelly, mayo and brown sugar or honey on low flame.
After it has melted down, add the rest.
Use ingredients to amount being served and to taste.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix ingredients together and pour 1/2 of mixture in skillet. Sprinkle 1 cup grated cheese over this.
Chop 3 hot peppers and 1 bell pepper finely; mix and sprinkle over cheese, then add remaining batter over all.
Bake at 450° for 25 minutes.

title: dan's fudge
directions: Add milk, sugar and cocoa.
Bring to a boil over medium heat; boil for 5 to 8 minutes.
To test for hardness, let drop of hot mixture fall from spoon into cup of cold water.
If drop forms into a small, firm ball, mixture is "hard" enough.
Remove from heat and add butter and vanilla.
Beat briskly until mixture begins to get thick.
Do not overbeat.
Pour into buttered pan or dish.
Cool and enjoy!

title: angel food cake(strawberry delight)
directions: Break cake into bite sizes in bottom of 8 ounce pan.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and Dream Whip all together.
Spread over cake.
Then add strawberries and strawberry glaze.
Pour over cake.
Let stand overnight.

title: chicken, cheese enchiladas
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Cook onion in butter until tender. Stir in chicken, salsa, cream cheese and cumin. Heat thoroughly. Add 1 cup grated cheese and stir until melted. Spoon mixture in shells and wrap. Lay in 9 x 13 pan. Pour enchilada sauce over enchiladas, then sprinkle grated cheese over this. Bake in oven 15 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli as per package directions.
Drain.
Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli, milk, water and soup.
Cook slowly until warm; add cheese and continue cooking until cheese is melted and soup is hot.
Do not boil.
Season to taste.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix ingredients in a bowl by hand.
Mix and form dough into balls.
Bake at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes about 25.

title: chewy cake squares
directions: Melt margarine and brown sugar in a pan.
Add eggs, flour and nuts.
Spread on buttered cookie sheet.
Cook 15 minutes at 345°.

title: tropical milk shakes
directions: In a blender, combine the milk, bananas, ice cream and pineapple. Cover and process until smooth. Pour into chilled glasses. Top with coconut and pecans. Yield: 5 cups.

title: mom's corn
directions: Put corn in an oil covered dish.
Add salt, pepper and eggs; mix.
Add milk and mix well.
Add 3/4 of crumbs; mix and let stand.
Melt 2 tablespoons butter to rest of crumbs.
Put over top and put in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Take off lid last 15 minutes.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cupcakes
directions: In a large bowl, pour boiling water over oats.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Stir in brown sugar and butter.
Mix in egg.
Sift together flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Add flour mixture to batter; mix well.
Stir in vanilla and half the chocolate chips.
Divide batter among 24 fluted paper muffin cups or greased and floured cups.
Sprinkle tops with nuts and remaining chips.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted comes out clean.

title: lime sherbet punch
directions: Place sherbet in a punch bowl.
Gradually add chilled 7-Up until desired thickness is achieved.
Yields 18 to 20 servings.

title: apricot gelatin salad
directions: Combine pineapple juice, water and sugar in saucepan.
Bring to boil.
Stir in jello and let cool for a few minutes.
Add cream cheese, celery, nuts and blend.
Fold in Cool Whip after jello has slightly thickened.
Refrigerate several hours to set.

title: taco pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Bake in a greased pie plate, 10 x 1 1/2-inch, or medium sized casserole dish.

title: crab appetizers
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and spread on Ritz crackers.
Bake at 425° until cheese has melted.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: baked garlic
directions: Place pod of garlic into piece of foil.
Cut top so you can get some butter into center area.
Close foil around it and bake at 350° for about 30 minutes.
Garlic will slip out of peeling when done.
Spread on hot buttered bread or mix with butter for great garlic butter.

title: blueberry lemon bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Cream 1 cup sugar and butter until fluffy.
Add eggs and lemon peel; beat well.
Set aside 2 tablespoons flour; sift remaining flour with baking powder and salt.
Mix the flour alternately with milk into creamed mixture.
Beat smooth after each addition.
Combine reserved flour with blueberries.
Fold gently into batter.
Turn into pan and bake 1 hour.
Cool 10 minutes and pierce gently with a fork.
Combine lemon juice and 1/4 cup sugar.
Dissolve and pour over loaf.
Enjoy!

title: beef garden casserole
directions: Cook onion, ground beef and seasoning; brown lightly.
Add green beans, corn and tomato soup.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with cheese spins.
Make cheese with biscuit mix.

title: chinese sesame-chicken salad
directions: Toast the sesame seed until lightly browned.
Let cool.
Put the shredded chicken in a bowl and sprinkle with mustard, ginger, garlic and onion powders, orange juice, soy sauce and sesame seed.
Toss well.

title: mike's chili beans
directions: Season ground beef patties with hamburger seasoning and garlic salt while cooking on a charcoal/gas grill until medium done. Chop cooked meat.
Saute pepper and onion in some margarine in a large iron skillet on the grill.
Add ground beef patties that have been chopped; remove from heat.
Combine remaining ingredients in mixing bowl with 1 tablespoon margarine.
Add to ground beef mixture in iron skillet.
Simmer on grill for 1 hour.

title: creamy broccoli soup
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and salt; gradually add milk, stirring constantly, in double boiler.
Bring to a boil.
Add broth; cook over low heat until serving time. Approximately 30 minutes before serving, add carrots and broccoli. Stir occasionally, but do not boil.

title: striped delight
directions: Mix together cracker
crumbs,
1/4 cup sugar and margarine. Press
firmly
into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Chill 15 minutes. Beat cream cheese,
1/4 cup sugar, milk until smooth, fold in Cool
Whip, spread
into crust.
Prepare chocolate pudding as directed on box. Pour over cream cheese layer.
Chill several hours.
Spread 1 1/2 cups Cool Whip over pudding; garnish with nuts.

title: quick beef stroganoff
directions: Brown beef well. Mix can of soup with mayonnaise. Add to beef. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Crumble 1/2 box of crackers in bottom of buttered casserole dish. Chip 1/2 stick butter over crumbs.
Layer chicken, chestnuts, pimentos and sour cream on top of buttered crackers. Pour soup over mixture.
Top with the other half box of crackers and 1/2 stick butter.
Bake in a 350° oven about 45 minutes or until brown and bubbly.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: Cream the butter and sugar. Add eggs, milk and then the flour in which the baking powder has been sifted.
Flavor with nutmeg and lemon juice. Roll dough into thin sheet.
Cut into shapes. Bake them on greased tins at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: creamy baked chicken breasts
directions: Arrange chicken in a lightly greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Top with cheese slices.
Combine soup and wine.
Stir well and pour over chicken breasts.
Shake crumbs (stuffing mix) over top and drizzle the butter over the crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: french toast
directions: Sift dry ingredients together. Add all liquids and stir until blended. Dip slices of dry bread (crust may be trimmed) into batter and fry in deep fat at 370°.
If batter is too thick, thin with milk. Serve hot with syrup or sprinkled with powdered sugar and topped with halved strawberries.
Yields 8 servings.

title: overnight rolls
directions: Start these rolls at 5 p.m.
Dissolve yeast in warm water; add margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add 7 to 9 cups flour and salt.
Mix as you would any yeast dough.
Should be a little bit sticky. Punch down every hour for 5 hours.
Shape into rolls, buns, coffee cake, etc., then put on greased pans.
Cover with a light cloth and let stand overnight on counter.

title: caramel chocolate squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Heat caramels and 1/4 cup of the milk in saucepan over medium heat, stirring constantly, until caramels are melted and mixture is smooth.
Keep mixture warm over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Mix cake mix (dry), margarine, remaining milk and the pecans.
Spread half of the dough (1 1/2 cups) in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch rectangular pan.
Bake 6 minutes; remove from oven.
Sprinkle chocolate chips and coconut over baked layer. Drizzle caramel mixture over chocolate chips and coconut.
Drop remaining dough by teaspoonfuls onto caramel layer, spreading evenly.
Bake until cake portion is slightly dry to touch, 15 to 20 minutes longer.
Cool completely.
Refrigerate until firm.
Cut into 2 1/4 x 1-inch bars.
Makes 48 bars.

title: dump bars
directions: "Dump" all ingredients, except chocolate chips, together in a bowl.
Mix all ingredients until moistened.

title: bohemian sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar and sugar together; bring to a boil and let cool. Combine all ingredients. Refrigerate, covered, for 24 hours before serving. Salad will keep refrigerated 3 to 4 weeks.

title: sombrero spread
directions: Brown meat and 1/2 cup onion in skillet. Stir in catsup, Tabasco sauce, chili powder and salt.
Mash in beans. Heat through.
Garnish with the cheese around the edge, onions next and olives in the center.
Serve hot from
a chafing dish with corn chips.

title: hayride kitchen soup
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
You can add salt and pepper for spicy taste.
Cook 3 hours in crock-pot.

title: microwave apple butter
directions: Combine apples and cider.
Microwave on High for 12 to 15 minutes or until tender. Stir twice during cooking.
Add sugar, cinnamon, cloves and allspice.
Microwave on High for 25 to 35 minutes.
Stir only halfway through cooking.
Spoon into jars and store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks or freezer for 3 months.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery, onion and margarine until tender.
Add broccoli, soup, Cheez Whiz, salt and pepper.
Mix and put in a greased casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes.

title: real pretty salad for christmas
directions: Pour boiling water over jello.
Add frozen strawberries and drained pineapple, also bananas.
Pour half into a 9 x 12-inch glass pan.
Chill firm.
Spread sour cream and let set, then pour other half on top.
Add nuts.
Let set again.
"Sure good."

title: calico beans
directions: Fry bacon until crispy.
Remove from fat and set aside.
In bacon fat, fry hamburger and onion.
Drain and set aside.
In large casserole pot, mix remaining ingredients, then add hamburger, onion and bacon.
Mix well.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix together well in larger bowl, then add 1 cup chopped pecans and 1 cup coconut (optional); pour into a well-greased tube pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool in pan 15 minutes, then turn out onto wire rack to finish cooling.
This cake freezes well.
(You can make for loaf pan; cook 50 minutes.)

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown and drain hamburger.
Mix with soups and vegetables. Arrange Tater Tots on top in a 9 x 13-inch
pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 or 40 minutes until vegetables are done.
Put cheese on top the last 5 minutes.

title: bessie's hamburger pie
directions: Cook onion, pepper and celery in a small amount of oil. Add ground beef after vegetables are done.
Cook until beef is "grey". Line oiled
("Pammed")
casserole	with
package crescent rolls.
Pour
in
meat-vegetable mixture.
Add can of tomato sauce on top;
sprinkle
with
cheese.
Top
with other half of crescent rolls.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: minestrone
directions: Wash and drain beans.
Put in large, heavy kettle with 3 quarts water.
Bring to boil and boil 2 minutes.
Remove from heat, cover and let stand 1 hour.
Bring to boil, cover and simmer 1 1/2 hours or until tender.

title: broccoli pie
directions: Separate crescent rolls and pat into a 9-inch pie plate.
Cook broccoli; drain well.
Mix broccoli, egg and cheese together.
Put on top of crescent crust.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes or until brown.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Remove from refrigerator 1 hour before baking.
Add enough crushed corn flakes to cover the top.
Bake 1 hour in a 350° oven.
Makes 2 quarts.

title: beer with egg
directions: This is an excellent antidote for the chef who has overindulged the night before.
Fill a tall glass to the 3/4 mark with beer.
Add an egg; beat with a fork.
This makes a gold-colored, bland drink for one.
Try poaching eggs with beer. The brew adds a special something to both the taste and the texture.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Combine salt, celery and nuts; moisten with mayonnaise.
Mix lightly with 2 forks.
Serve on crisp lettuce leaves.
Makes 6 servings.

title: brunch casserole
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch greased pan, layer bread cubes, sausage and Cheddar cheese.
Beat eggs, milk, salt and dry mustard together. Pour over layered mixture and refrigerate overnight.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Fry onion, garlic and green pepper.
Add rest of ingredients, except shrimp.
Simmer for 30 minutes.
Add shrimp; heat 15 more minutes.
Serve over rice with toasted French bread.

title: fluffy rolls
directions: Cream together Crisco, sugar and salt. Pour over this mixture 1 cup boiling water.
Set aside.
Mix yeast with warm water.
Beat 2 eggs and mix with yeast mixture when it is cool.
Add this to first mixture.
Add 7 cups plain flour.
Mix with hand.
Cover with wax paper.
Let set on counter until double in bulk. Cover after you push down.
Place in refrigerator until ready to make into rolls.
Let rolls rise until double.
Bake at 450° until brown.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: pansit(philippine main dish)
directions: Saute onion, garlic and oil.
Brown together chicken, ham and shrimp.
Combine with onion mixture and simmer 2 minutes with soy sauce, cabbage and chicken stock.
Add cooked vermicelli, salt and pepper.
Serve with lemon wedges.

title: twice baked potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes at 425° for 45 minutes, or until done.
Cool slightly.
Cut off tops of potatoes lengthwise.
Scoop out the insides and mash.
Add milk, onion powder and garlic powder.
Mix well and mound mixture into potato shell.
Top evenly with cheese, pepper and paprika.
Bake for 3 to 5 minutes, or until cheese melts.

title: frozen strawberry salad
directions: Mix sugar and cream cheese until smooth.
Gently fold in pineapple, nuts and then whipped topping.
Fold in strawberries. Place in mold and freeze.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: delicious shrimp
directions: In heavy skillet, brown butter, onions and mushrooms together on medium heat.
Lower temperature; add 2 cans soup (undiluted) and crab boil.
Stir and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes.
Add shrimp; simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Be careful, it's spicier than you think.
Serve over rice.
Enjoy the compliments.

title: country raisin gingersnaps
directions: Cream together shortening and sugar; beat in eggs and molasses.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and spices.
Add to mixture.
Stir in raisins.
Chill dough for 1/2 hour.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls and roll in sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: chicken squares
directions: Blend until smooth
cream cheese, butter and milk.
Add salt, pepper, onion
and chicken.
Mix all together.
Separate 2 tubes of Pillsbury
cresent
rolls
into 8 rectangles, pinch seams. Spoon 1/4 cup
chicken
mixture
into
center
of each rectangle then pull up
sides
to center and pinch side seams. Place in Pam-sprayed
pan,
brush
with butter.
Sprinkle each square with Stove Top
(one
step stuffing mix).
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: diabetic sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks until thick and lemony colored.
Add 1/2 cup of water, artificial sweetener, vanilla and lemon juice to egg yolks. Beat until thick and fluffy.
Using clean beaters, beat egg whites until foamy.
Add cream of tartar and beat until stiff peaks form. Carefully fold egg whites into egg yolk mixture.
Combine flour and salt; sift gradually over egg whites and yolk mixture, folding in gently.
Pour into ungreased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: beef brisket
directions: Marinate brisket overnight in beer.
Remove brisket and place on foil.
Cover brisket with green chilies, soup mix, celery and enough beer to "dampen."
Wrap in foil and bake 8 hours in 250° oven.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: aunt mamie's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix sugar, oleo, eggs and raisins with mixer.
Add flour, oatmeal, soda, salt and vanilla.
Drop by spoonfuls on greased sheet. Bake at 300°.
Makes 5 or 6 dozen.

title: risotto with vegetables
directions: Heat oil in skillet.
Saute pepper and zucchini until crisp or tender.
Set aside.
In large saucepan heat butter and saute onion and garlic over medium heat 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add Risotto and cook about 3 minutes.
Stir in 1/2 cup hot chicken broth.
Continue stirring until almost absorbed.
Add remaining hot broth 1/2 cup at a time, stirring until Risotto is al dente.
Stir in red pepper, zucchini, peas, chicken and cheese.
Rice may be substituted for Risotto.
Serves 4.

title: kings inn bombay dressing
directions: Pit,
peel
and mash avocado.
Put avocado, sour cream, onion soup
mix,	garlic,
curry	powder	and
lemon juice in blender. Blend on high speed; pour into glass jar and refrigerate.

title: farmers casserole
directions: Place potatoes in an 8 inch square baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese, ham and onion.
Beat eggs, milk, pepper and salt; pour over all.
Cover and refrigerate for several hours or overnight.
Remove from the refrigerator 30 minutes before baking. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until knife inserted near the center comes out clean.
Yield: 6 servings.

title: pizza sauce
directions: Put tomatoes and green pepper through the blender.
Cook onion in pan with olive oil until tender & add garlic.
In large pot mix in all other ingredients.
Add in 2 (12 oz.) cans tomato paste.
Add in the garlic/olive oil mixture.
Bring to a boil. Turn down & simmer for 30 minutes.	Put into jars, seal & water bath for 40 minutes.

title: wassail bowl
directions: Squeeze lemons and oranges and reserve the juice.
Add the skins to water, seasoned with sticks cinnamon, whole cloves and sugar.

title: grandma rolls
directions: Work all ingredients in until stiff like biscuit dough.
Put in an oiled bowl and let rise until double in size.
Do not beat down; pinch off biscuit size amount of dough.
Place in greased pan and let rise for about 2 hours.

title: apple cake
directions: In a large bowl combine all ingredients except the last 3.

title: fried eggs and bacon
directions: Fry bacon to desired crispness, using medium-high.
Remove bacon; pour off grease, leaving only enough to fry eggs.
Turn unit off.
Break egg into skillet.
Add 1 tablespoon water, cover and cook to desired hardness.

title: perfect microwave fudge
directions: Sift sugar and cocoa together into ungreased 9-inch square pan.
Cut margarine into 5 pieces and place on top of dry ingredients.
Pour milk in but DO NOT STIR (important).
Cook on High power in microwave for 2 to 3 minutes or until mixture is bubbling.
Remove from microwave and stir thoroughly; blend in nuts and vanilla and spread evenly in dish.
Refrigerate 1 hour before serving.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 1 1/2 pounds.

title: candy topped pizza
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 12-inch pizza pan or skillet.
In medium bowl, with electric mixer at medium, cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy (about 1 minute).
Beat in egg.
At low stir in flour and baking soda until well blended.
Evenly spread dough into prepared pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until lightly brown.
Sprinkle marshmallows and candies on cookie during last 5 minutes of baking.
Cool 10 minutes in pan or on wire rack.
To serve, cut cookies into wedges.
Makes 16 servings.

title: sausage wedges
directions: Crumble sausage in a 9-inch pie plate.
Cover with paper towel; microwave for 3 to 4 minutes on High.
Drain off fat. Sprinkle cheese over sausage; stir in onion.
In a medium bowl, combine milk and eggs.
Add parsley and butter.
Pour over sausage.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave 4 minutes on High. Stir, cover and microwave for 6 to 8 minutes on Medium (50%).
Let stand, covered, for 5 minutes.

title: pork tenderloin in tequila
directions: Heat oil and garlic in 10-inch skillet until hot.
Coat pork with mustard.
Cook pork over medium heat until brown.
Remove garlic.
Stir in remaining ingredients except parsley.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until pork is tender, about 30 minutes.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: chicken mushroom puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crushed croutons and nuts; set aside.
Mix chicken, cream cheese, butter, salt and mushrooms. Put one rounded teaspoon of chicken mixture on wide end of roll. Roll up.
Dip in melted butter, roll in crouton nut mixture.
Bake as directed on package at 350°.
Serve cold or hot with gravy. May freeze for later use.
Then thaw at room temperature to serve cold.

title: glazed pork roast
directions: In a small bowl, combine orange marmalade and spices.
Brush half of glaze over roast.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 45 minutes. Uncover and baste roast with remaining glaze.
Bake, uncovered, for 45 minutes longer or until meat thermometer registers 170°. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: chicken and rice
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Cook rice in 4 cups of broth from chicken.
Add soups to rice after cooked.
Add chicken.
Put in large casserole dish and bake for 20 minutes.

title: cranberry-orange bread
directions: Combine flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar in medium bowl.
Combine shortening, orange juice, egg, orange rind and almond extract.
Add liquid mixture to dry mixture, stirring until well moistened.

Fold in cranberries. Bake in greased and floured 8 1/2 x 4 1/2 x 3-inch loaf pan at 350° for 1 hour until inserted toothpick comes out clean. Cool for 10 minutes, then remove from baking pan and cool on rack.

title: pillsbury easy stromboli
directions: Unroll dough; place on greased or parchment-lined cookie sheet. Press dough into 12 x 8-inch rectangle.
Spread sauce on dough to within 2-inches of long sides and 1/2-inch of short sides.
Top with ham, cheese, peppers and Italian seasonings.
Fold long sides of dough over filling; pinch to seal.
Pinch short sides to seal. Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes or until golden.
Serves 6.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion and bell pepper; drain off excess fat.
Combine golden mushroom soup and Hunt's special sauce with ground beef mixture.
Simmer for 10 minutes.
Cook spaghetti as directed on package; drain and mix with ground beef mixture.
Add salt and pepper to taste.

title: grandma letty's cheese-baked halibut
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease a large shallow baking dish.
Wipe halibut with damp cloth; place in dish.
Pour lemon juice over fish, then sprinkle with salt, pepper and thyme.
Bake, uncovered, for 15 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine cheese and bread crumbs.
Sprinkle fish with cheese mixture, then melted butter. Return to oven and bake 20 minutes longer or until fish flakes easily with fork.
Serve right from baking dish.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheese and onion enchiladas
directions: Make cheese sauce; melt margarine.
Blend in flour, seasoning and milk.
Stir constantly until bubbling.
Sauce will be thick. Blend in cheese.

title: corn and bean casserole
directions: Mix together the corn, beans and onion, then place in a casserole dish.
Mix the cream of mushroom soup and sour cream, then pour over corn and beans.
Melt margarine, then mix with crushed crackers.
Place on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco dip
directions: Mix seasoning with sour cream and spread in Pyrex or ceramic pie plate. In layers, spread taco sauce on top of sour cream mixture, then sprinkle tomatoes, then lettuce and finally shredded cheese.
Garnish dish with chips around edges.
Serve with extra chips in bowl. Serves 15 to 20.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, salt and sugar.
Measure milk and oil.
Stir together.
Pour into flour mixture.
Stir; form into a ball. Divide equally into 2 balls.
Roll between 2 pieces of waxed paper to desired size.
Peel off top paper.
Lift and turn onto pan. Carefully lift off paper from dough.
Punch a few small holes with a fork and bake or fill.
Bake at 375°.
Makes 2 single or 1 double pie crust.

title: beef and gravy
directions: Dump all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook on low 6 to 8 hours (until meat is tender).
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: coffee milk shake
directions: Blend coffee, syrup and ice cream in blender until smooth; pour into chilled glass and top with whipped cream.
Serve. Makes 2 tall or 4 short servings.

title: zucchini walnut bread
directions: In blender, combine first 4 ingredients.
Add remaining ingredients and turn into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Turn out on wire racks to cool.

title: shrimp mold
directions: Soak gelatin in 1/2 cup cold water.
Heat soup (do not add water) and cream cheese until melted.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into a salad mold.
Refrigerate until congealed.
Unmold and garnish with sliced hard-cooked eggs and/or ripe olives. Serve with crackers.

title: vegetable fish bake
directions: If fish is frozen, thaw.
Cut fish into 4 portions and place in non-stick sprayed baking dish.
Sprinkle with lemon juice and paprika.
Combine mushrooms, tomato, green pepper, parsley and pepper.
Spread over fish.
Cover and bake for 25 minutes at 350°. Serve with lemon wedges.

title: apple impromptu
directions: Place sliced apples in a 9-inch cake pan.
Combine 1/4 cup sugar and cinnamon.
Sprinkle over apples.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: orange rice(weight watchers)
directions: In 1 1/2-quart nonstick saucepan heat margarine over medium heat until bubbly and hot.
Add celery and onion and saute, stirring occasionally, until vegetables are tender.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to a boil.
Reduce heat, cover and let simmer until liquid is absorbed and rice is tender, 12 to 15 minutes.

title: speedy cheesecake pie
directions: Press into buttered 8-inch pie plate.

title: buttermilk brownies
directions: In saucepan, combine butter, cocoa and 1 cup water.
Bring to boil; stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
In large mixing bowl, stir together flour, sugar, soda and salt; stir in eggs, buttermilk and vanilla.
Add cocoa mixture; mix until blended. Pour into one greased 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch baking pan or 2 (11 x 7 1/2 x 1 1/2-inch) baking pans or 2 (9 x 9 x 2-inch) pans. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Immediately pour frosting over brownies; spread evenly.
Cool; cut into bars.
Makes 60.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain grease.
Mix mushroom soup, green chilies and hamburger.
Add about 1 can of water; mix and simmer for about 5 minutes.
Use a 9 x 13-inch pan and layer sauce, tortilla, sauce, cheese, tortilla, sauce and cheese.
Use all ingredients, putting cheese on top.
Bake in oven at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let cool for a few minutes before cutting.

title: cornmeal pie
directions: Beat eggs well; add sugar, cornmeal and melted margarine. Beat until well mixed.
Add vinegar and vanilla; stir again.
Pour into unbaked pie crust.
Bake in a moderate oven (about 350°) until thick and light brown.
Very good!

title: hearty breakfast muffins
directions: Heat
oven
Mix
flour,
brown
sugar, soda, cinnamon, salt and nutmeg in a large bowl.	Beat egg whites in a small
bowl.
Stir	in milk, oil and molasses.
Add to flour mixture
and
stir	until just moist.
Stir in cereal, raisins and apples.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full. Bake 20 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen muffins.

title: coconut cake
directions: Follow directions on the cake mix box for making two layers. When layers are baked and cooled, split each layer, making 4 layers.
Mix together the ingredients for filling and icing. After mixing thoroughly, spread between layers, on top and sides. Refrigerate overnight. Must be kept refrigerated.
This cake is very moist and not too sweet.

title: chicken-broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and drain well.
Place in a lightly greased 1 1/2-quart casserole. Top with chicken. Combine remaining ingredients except bread crumbs.
Stirring well, spoon mixture over chicken. Top with bread crumbs. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: baked macaroni and cheese
directions: Put butter, flour, salt, pepper, milk and cream in blender for 35 seconds.
Add onion and cheeses.
Mix ingredients with cooked macaroni in 2-quart casserole.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: apple crisp
directions: Peel apples.
Slice and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle enough white sugar over to sweeten.
Add dash of salt and dash of cinnamon.
Mix together the flour, brown sugar, oatmeal, butter and cinnamon.
Sprinkle mixture over apples.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: stacey's olive salad
directions: Mix all salad ingredients; add salad dressing and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Combine sugar and cocoa; mix well.
Then add milk and butter. Cook and stir until comes to rapid boil.
Then cook 1 minute. Remove; add peanut butter, vanilla and oats.
Mix and drop on wax paper.

title: quick caramel frosting
directions: Melt butter in saucepan. Add brown sugar and cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly. Add milk and cook until mixture comes to a boil. Remove from heat and cool about 10 minutes. Gradually add powdered sugar until frosting is of spreading consistency, beating well after each addition.

title: 24 hour salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except fruit, marshmallows and whipping cream.
Put in a double boiler and cook until thick.
Add 1 cup miniature marshmallows to mixture.
The marshmallows do not need to be completely dissolved.
Mix fruit cocktail, pineapple and cherries well with mixture.
Then add whipped cream.
Add bananas, apples, grapes or other fruit as desired.
Let set for 24 hours before serving.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Beat together the ingredients until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or bake in layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: kasha pilaf
directions: Saute onions and mushrooms in olive oil.
When softened, mix in kasha moistened with egg.
Stir over medium-high heat about 2 to 3 minutes or until kernels are separate.
Reduce heat and add boiling water.
Cover pan tightly.
Simmer 8 to 11 minutes or until kasha kernels are tender and liquid absorbed.
Serves 4 to 6 generously as side dish instead of rice or potatoes.

title: jane cole cupcakes
directions: Melt butter and chocolate.
Let cool.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, flour and vanilla to eggs.
Stir in chocolate mixture.
Add pecans.
Pour into well greased or paper-lined muffin tins.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: cracked chocolate cookies
directions: Combine brown sugar, shortening, water and vanilla in large bowl.
Beat on medium speed until blended.
Beat eggs into creamed mixture.
Combine flour, cocoa, soda and salt.
Mix into creamed mixture at low speed just until blended.
Stir in chocolate chips. Shape dough into 1 1/4-inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Place 2-inches apart on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake one sheet at a time.
Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake 7 to 9 minutes until cookies are set, do not overbake.

title: peanut butter chocolate chip cake
directions: Stir first 4 ingredients together.
Mix in margarine and peanut butter at slow speed.
Remove 1 cup of this mixture and set aside. To remaining mixture, add milk, eggs and vanilla.
Mix 3 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch (or larger pan), ungreased, or lightly greased.
Top with chocolate chips, then reserved crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° approximately 40 to 45 minutes (until set).

title: cuban picadillo(pronounced pee kah dee yo)
directions: In the oil, fry onion and garlic for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add the seasonings, meat and wine and stir again.
Add the tomatoes, raisins and olives and stir.
Add the green pepper and cook only long enough for it to get thoroughly hot; it should retain crispness and color.
The cooking only requires 10 minutes time.
The chopped and slicing can be done in advance.
The Cubans serve the Picadillo on top of rice with its juices trickling down. Makes enough for 3 to 5 people.

title: shrimp and scallop saute
directions: Heat oil in 9-inch skillet until very hot.
Add shrimp and cook 2 minutes, turning occasionally.
Add scallops and saute 2 minutes more.
Add snow peas, radishes, dill, salt and pepper. Cook 1 more minute.
Can be served over cooked rice.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream together brown sugar, sugar and butter.
Blend in egg, vanilla and then add flour, soda, salt and nuts.
Chill 20 minutes. Shape into balls the size of quarters.
Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Press flat with drinking glass. Bake for 10 to 12
minutes in a 350° oven. Cool. Swirl on icing.

title: kentucky bourbon cake
directions: Cream sugar and butter until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each addition.
Add molasses and mix well.

title: vermicelli with lemony green vegetables
directions: Cook pasta as directed on package.
Drain.
Cook vegetables in butter in a large skillet or wok, stir-frying until tender-crisp, about 7 minutes. Toss with lemon zest.
Remove from pan and keep warm.
Heat milk and cream cheese until smooth and creamy. Stir in Parmesan cheese, salt and pepper. Toss with pasta.
Serve vegetables over pasta with lemon wedges and coarsely ground pepper.

title: becky's sticky buns
directions: Mix night before.
Mix together sugar, pudding and cinnamon. Place frozen rolls in buttered Bundt pan.
Pour sugar mixture over rolls, then pour melted butter on top.
Place dish towel over pan and let sit overnight.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Turn over as soon a you get it out of the oven.
The bag usually comes with 24 rolls; it is best to use 20 rolls at the most.

title: jessie's chicken and dumplings
directions: Cook chicken until tender in 4 quarts of salted water. Remove chicken from broth.
Cool chicken and remove meat from bones.
Add enough chicken broth to give 5 - 6 quarts of broth. Mix flour and salt together.
Add enough water to make a soft ball of dough.
Roll out dough to about 1/4 inch thick, cut into strips.
Bring broth to a boil, then drop 8 - 10 dumplings into broth stirring them lightly.
As broth comes back to boil, add 8 - 10 more.
Continue until all dumplings are in pot.
Cook at a full boil approximately 5 minutes stirring lightly to keep dumplings separated.
Add cooked chicken meat back to pot.
Boil 2 minutes more.
Remove from heat, cover and wait 20 - 30 minutes before serving.
Sprinkle with black pepper.

title: new york knobby apple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg and vanilla.
Stir in dry ingredients (dough will be stiff), then stir in apples and nuts. Spread into a 9-inch square greased baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chess pie
directions: Mix well and pour into a pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°; then lower heat to 250° and bake 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: squash casserole
directions: Wash, slice and cook squash in salted water.
Drain and mash squash.
Add onion, carrots, sour cream and soup.
Mix well.
Melt margarine.
Add to dressing.
Pour enough dressing into bottom of 2-quart casserole dish to cover.
Add squash mixture.
Sprinkle remaining dressing to cover top of dish.
Cook at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or until bubbly.
Freezes well.

title: cookie jar gingersnaps
directions: In a large mixing bowl, cream the shortening and 1 cup sugar. Beat in
the egg and molasses.
Combine flour, baking soda, ginger and cinnamon.
Roll teaspoon of dough into balls.
Dip one side of each ball into sugar.
Place with sugar side up on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: 24 hour casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients in glass bowl and store in fridge for 24 hours.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake 2 hours at 225°.
Serve with sauce.

title: gumbo orleans
directions: Saute onion, celery and green pepper in hot oil until tender. Add stock, tomatoes, tomato sauce and okra; simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Add shrimp, crab meat, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 30 minutes to 1 hour.
Serve on top of mounds of hot, boiled rice as main dish along with tossed green salad and hot French bread.

title: doodads
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large pan (Dutch oven size).
Mix in the next 3 ingredients thoroughly.
Meanwhile, in a large bowl, mix the dry ingredients.
Add to butter mixture; stir until each piece is thoroughly coated.
Put in a large baking pan.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring twice.
Remove from oven; cool and store in an airtight container.

title: battered potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes; cut into 1/4-inch slices.
When cutting potatoes, keep them in water until all are cut.
Put next 4 ingredients in plastic bag.
Drop 4 pieces of potato at a time into bag and coat well, until all pieces are coated.
Melt stick of margarine in baking pan, then place coated potatoes in pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes, or until golden brown.

title: glazed carrots
directions: Put carrots and remaining ingredients except cornstarch mixture in a medium size saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until carrots are tender, but not soft. Add cornstarch mixture; cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chow mein hot dish
directions: Brown ground beef, onion and celery.
Add remaining ingredients and pour into casserole dish.
Bake 1 hour at 350°. Take out and spread chow mein noodles on top.
Return to oven and bake 30 minutes.
(Measure water in soup cans to rinse out.)

title: fig cake
directions: Beat together the sugar, oil and eggs.
Combine flour with the dry spices.
Add half the flour mixture to the sugar, eggs and oil mixture; mix well.
Add figs, pecans, vanilla and remaining flour mixture.
Bake in a greased Bundt pan for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.
Do not overbake.

title: easy cheese ball
directions: When cream cheese is softened, place in a bowl with the salad dressing, onion soup mix and dash of Worcestershire sauce.
Mix well (using hands).
Shape into a ball and place on a sheet of wax paper, covered with nuts.
Coat ball well and top with maraschino cherry.
Serve with crackers.
Recipe can be doubled to make 2 balls.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mix ingredients lightly and spoon into fluted paper cups set in muffin pan.
Freeze (cover with plastic wrap) 15 minutes before serving.
Remove from freezer, peel off paper cups and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: easy chocolate pie
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients.
Cook until thick and bubbling. Add butter and vanilla.
Makes 2 pies.
For meringue, use egg whites.

title: stir-fried spinach
directions: Heat wok or large heavy skillet.
Add oil and hot stir-fry spinach for 1 minute.
Add salt and sugar.
Continue to stir-fry for 1 minute.

title: white trash
directions: In a very large bowl, mix first 5 ingredients.

title: banana cream pie
directions: Mix flour and milk.
Add beaten egg, corn syrup and 1 tablespoon honey.
Cook in top of double boiler over rapidly boiling water until thick.
Remove from fire.
Add vanilla.
Cool and pour into baked pie shell.
Slice bananas and spread over top of custard.
Top with the heavy cream, which has been whipped stiff and sweetened with 2 tablespoons honey.
Place in refrigerator.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs with melted butter. Add powdered sugar and peanut butter.
Mix well. Spread evenly on a greased cookie sheet (greased with butter). Melt chocolate chips and spread over top. Chill and cut into squares.

title: sister minnie mclain's 14-day pickles
directions: Use glass jars only.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Combine first 10 ingredients.
Blend well at low speed.
Shape into round balls, using teaspoon.
Roll balls in additional sugar; place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Top each cookie immediately with a chilled candy kiss, pressing down firmly so cookie cracks around edge.

title: low-calorie pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients (except egg whites) and mix well. Beat egg whites until stiff; then fold gently into cottage cheese mixture.
Using low heat, drop by teaspoonfuls onto griddle or skillet and cook, turning once so that both sides are browned.

title: make ahead mashed potatoes
directions: To the mashed potatoes add all ingredients except 1 stick of margarine and paprika; mix well.
Put in baking dish.
Melt the remaining stick of margarine and pour over potatoes.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.
Can be made ahead of time and baked later or frozen and baked later. Great for potluck dinners because they stay soft.

title: dinner rolls
directions: All measurements level (use standard measuring cups).
Use fresh yeast.
Do not sift flour before measuring, but fluff the flour with a spoon and then spoon it lightly into a measuring cup and level off (do not tap cup to get more flour in it).

title: winter carrot casserole
directions: In saucepan, cook carrots, covered, in boiling salted water 10 minutes (until tender); drain.
Place in 1-quart casserole. Combine mayonnaise, onion, horseradish, salt and pepper.
Spoon over carrots.
Mix crumbs and butter; sprinkle atop.
Bake, uncovered, in a 350° oven 30 minutes (until hot).
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: pistachio salad
directions: In large bowl, mix pudding with whipped topping.
Add other ingredients and chill.

title: mayonnaise cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients together in a large bowl.
Add vanilla and water or coffee until well blended.
Fold in mayo; bake in a greased pan at 350° for 35 minutes.
Frost with cocoa icing when cool.

title: bbq cups
directions: Brown meat; drain.
Add barbecue sauce and set aside.
Place biscuits in ungreased muffin cups. pressing dough up sides to edge of cup.
Spoon meat mixture into cups.
Sprinkle with cheese. Bake at 400 degrees for 12 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: autumn salad
directions: Boil pineapple and sugar for 3 minutes.
Add Jell-O to mix and cool.
Add Cool Whip, apple, cream cheese, celery and pecans to mix; pour into mold and refrigerate overnight.

title: pickle relish
directions: Soak cucumbers, water and lime for 24 hours.
Rinse and soak in
clear
water
for
3 hours.
Grind and soak in celery seed, pickling
spices,
vinegar, sugar and salt for 12 hours. Slowly bring
to
a boil and cook until dry enough.
Serves 12 pints.

title: pineapple chicken(po lo chi)
directions: Dredge uncooked chicken meat (cut in 1-inch pieces) with a mixture of the cornstarch, salt and cold water.
Add the soy sauce.
Saute the onions (sliced lengthwise) in the oil for about 2 minutes and remove from pan.
Saute celery (cut diagonally) and water chestnuts (sliced lengthwise) in oil for 2 minutes or less and remove from pan.

title: peppermint dessert
directions: Crush candy; add light cream and heat in double boiler until candy dissolves.
Add gelatin dissolved in cold water.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Break chocolate wafers in half and stand around outside of 9-inch square pan. Place layer of wafers in bottom of pan; spread remaining gelatin mixture and top with crushed wafers.
Chill 12 hours.
Cut in squares.
Serves 9.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream butter or margarine and add sugar and brown sugar.
Cream well.
Blend in unbeaten egg, 1/3 cup peanut butter, soda, salt and vanilla.
Sift in flour and oats.

title: baked squash
directions: Cut tips of squash and cut each into 3 or 4 pieces.
Drop squash into a large saucepan with enough boiling water to cover. Return to a boil, reduce heat and cook until tender.
Drain in colander.
Mash.

title: gumbo(avoyell parish, la)
directions: Cut up chicken as for frying.
Heat 2 tablespoons fat in deep Dutch oven, preferably the black cast-iron type.
Brown chicken lightly about 20 minutes.
Remove excess fat; add hot water and simmer on low heat.
In skillet, melt remaining 2 tablespoons fat; when hot, add flour, stirring constantly, until flour is golden brown.
(This is the roux).
To roux, add chopped onion and garlic. Cook on low heat until onion wilts (5 minutes).
Add this mixture slowly to chicken.
Add salt, black and cayenne pepper.
Chicken should be semi-tender.
Then add sausage, which has been browned lightly, chopped green onions and parsley.
Simmer 45 minutes or until chicken is done (very tender).
Turn off heat; add the file. Stir well and let stand, covered, for 10 minutes before serving. Serve in soup bowls, accompanied by steamed rice, added by each person according to their liking.
Baked sweet potatoes in the skin is usually served with this.

title: coconut cake
directions: Beat eggs and sugar.
Add oil.
Sift together baking powder, salt, sugar and flour.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk to eggs and sugar.
Add extracts and Angel Flake coconut.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: hearty beef 'n potato casserole
directions: Place potatoes on bottom and up sides of an 8 x 12-inch casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for 10 minutes.
Brown beef and drain.
Place beef, broccoli, onions, and tomatoes into potato shell.
Combine milk, soup, cheese, and seasonings.
Pour over beef mixture.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.
Take part of cheese and onions.
Bake, uncovered, 2 to 3 minutes. Ready in 15 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix meat, eggs, rice and onion in large bowl until rice is all mixed in well.
Make into balls, about size of walnut (40 to 50 balls).
Brown meat balls on all sides.
Take out of frypan; put in another kettle.
Mix 3 1/2 cups boiling water with flavor envelope from Rice-A-Roni; pour over balls.
Simmer slowly for 30 to 45 minutes.
Add more water, if needed, or can thicken like gravy.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Mix beef, rice and onion in a bowl.
After well mixed, make small balls.
Heat paste, soup and sauce with water until boiling. Drop balls in; allow to cook, covered, stirring occasionally for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: savory crescent chicken squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In medium bowl, blend cream cheese and margarine until smooth.
Add next six ingredients; mix well. Separate crescent dough into 4 triangles; firmly press perforations to seal.
Spoon 1/2 cup chicken mixture onto center of each rectangle.
Pull four corners of dough onto top center of mixture, twist slightly and seal edges.
Brush tops with margarine; dip into crouton crumbs.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 20 to 25 minutes, or until golden brown.
Makes 4 sandwiches.

title: variety cookies
directions: Cream shortening and sugars.
Stir in eggs.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Add to sugar mixture.
Blend in vanilla, oatmeal, coconut and one or more of other additives.
Mix thoroughly.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: rocky road squares
directions: Melt chocolate in cream and pour over nuts and marshmallows. Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch pan or on wax paper.
Let cool and cut in squares.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Beat eggs and stir in water.
Mince scallions.
Blend cornstarch and remaining cold water to a paste.
Bring stock to a boil.
Reduce heat to medium and stir in sugar, salt, sherry and soy sauce.
Add cornstarch paste and cook, stirring, until soup thickens and is smooth.
Reduce heat to low.
Pour eggs in slowly, stirring constantly, until they separate into shreds, then turn off the heat.
Garnish with minced scallions.

title: glorified rice
directions: Mix all ingredients and put into middle size casserole dish with tight fitting lid.
Place 1/2 stick butter in middle.
Cover and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Fluff up with a fork and serve.

title: braised beef with cabbage
directions: Heat oil in large skillet.
Add beef and brown on all sides. Remove.
Add onions to skillet, and cook slowly until golden brown.
Add browned beef.
Stir in 1 cup water.
Add apple and tomatoes, then sprinkle with sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring to boiling; reduce heat and simmer covered for 2 hours.
Add potatoes and cabbage to meat mixture; simmer, covered, for 20 minutes longer or until vegetables are tender.
Makes 4 servings.

title: baked macaroni
directions: Cook pasta al dente (after boiling 12 to 15 minutes).
Drain. Mix in cheese.
In blender, combine soup, milk and onion.
Blend together.
Mix all ingredients together except bacon.
Lay in pan or casserole dish.
Cover with bacon slices.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour until browned but not dry.

title: blondies
directions: Cream brown sugar and oleo.
Add eggs and beat well.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Add chocolate chips and vanilla.
Press into large sheet cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Do not overbake.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: crispy coconut-oatmeal cookies
directions: Beat shortening and sugars at medium speed with an electric mixer until blended; add eggs and vanilla, beating well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients; add to shortening mixture, mixing well.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls, and place 2 inches apart on lightly greased cookie sheets; flatten slightly with fork.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.
Transfer to wire racks to cool.
Yields 6 dozen cookies.

title: golden bake casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup butter and corn flake crumbs.
Put in pan.
Spread corn flake mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes covered with foil.
Remove foil and bake for 10 minutes.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers;
do not peel.
Slice paper thin.
Makes about 16	cups.
Cut peppers and onions up with cucumber.
Put in pan. Sprinkle
with
salt and cover with crushed ice.
Let stand 3 hours.
Wash and drain.
Make pickling syrup of sugar and white vinegar.
Add
spices.
Boil
for
minutes.
Add cucumbers, onions
and
peppers.
Bring
mixture to simmering point; do not boil.
Pack in clean hot jars and seal at once.

title: becky's chicken
directions: Place chicken breasts in a flat Pyrex baking dish.
Top with slices of Swiss cheese.

title: cheese and garlic dog biscuit
directions: Grate the cheese and let stand until it reaches room temperature.
Cream the cheese with the softened margarine, garlic, salt and flour.
Add enough milk to form into a ball. Chill for 1/2 hour.
Roll onto floured board. Cut into shapes and bake at 375° for 15 minutes or until slightly brown and firm. Makes 2 to 3 dozen, depending on size.

title: south ponderosita cornbread
directions: Melt shortening in an iron skillet.
Mix all ingredients, including shortening, folding in cheese last.
Pour into skillet. Bake at 350° until done (about 1 hour and 15 minutes).
Should be brown and firm.

title: minestrone
directions: Simmer vegetables in water and bouillon cubes until tender, about 12 to 15 minutes.
Add spaghetti sauce and simmer gently 5 minutes longer.
Makes 8 (1-cup) servings, 90 calories each.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Brown pork chops.
Mix rice, soup and water in casserole dish.
Place pork chops on top of rice mixture.
Bake in a 350° oven for 45 minutes, covered, and 15 minutes, uncovered.

title: seven layer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Place rice and corn in a 2-quart glass casserole dish with tight-fitting lid.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Pour tomato sauce and 1/2 cup water over 1st two layers. Add remaining ingredients, covering with bacon.

title: pan pierogi
directions: Melt margarine.
Saute onion in margarine.
Add cheese to melt. Make potatoes according to directions.
Combine melted margarine, onion and cheese with potatoes.
Makes enough for a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: easy chicken with rice
directions: Line a small baking dish with foil.
Dot margarine on bottom of foil.
Pour rice, then onion soup and then water.
Place seasoned chicken on top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: layered lettuce saladfort collins, colorado
directions: Layer ingredients in order given in 9 X 13 pan.
Do not stir or mix.
Cover tightly and let set in refrigerator overnight. Keeps well.

title: twice-baked potatoes
directions: Rub potatoes with margarine and prick with a fork.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until done.
Cut a lengthwise opening in top and scoop out potato.
Set shells aside.
Mash potatoes while hot with sour cream, margarine and egg.
Beat until fluffy.
Stir in onion and cheese.
Season with salt and pepper.
Spread inside of shells with margarine.
Pile mashed potatoes lightly and high into shells.
Bake at 425° about 20 minutes.

title: vegetable rice soup
directions: In a large saucepan over medium heat, heat all ingredients to a boil.
Reduce heat to low; simmer for 25 minutes, or until rice is done.

title: one pot chicken dinner
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
(Can be cut up if in a hurry, leave whole if not.)
Put all ingredients into a covered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
It makes its own juice so do not add liquid.
Serve with a salad.

title: lasagna casserole
directions: In large pan, brown ground meat with salt, pepper, onion and garlic. Drain.
Add mushrooms, spaghetti sauce, and tomato sauce.
Mix well and simmer about 10 minutes.
Add seasonings as desired.
Cook pasta, drain.
(Any non-shelled pasta will work fine, such as bow-ties).
Add to meat mixture.
Spray pan with Pam.
Add half of mixture, sprinkle with half of cheese.
Add remaining mixture and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese is thoroughly melted.

title: traditional pumpkin pie
directions: Combine all ingredients; mix well.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool.
Garnish with Cool Whip or ice cream.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Heat shortening in skillet.
Add chicken and brown on all sides.
Remove chicken from skillet and place in shallow baking pan.
Add onion to shortening in skillet and brown.
Add all remaining ingredients and simmer 30 minutes to make sauce.
Pour some over chicken and cover with aluminum foil.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 to 50 minutes or until done.

title: calypso pie
directions: Crust:
Crush Oreos and combine with melted butter.
Put into a 10-inch pie pan or square pan.

title: butterscotch candy
directions: Combine sugars, corn syrup, cream and water.
Cook, stirring, until sugar dissolves to very hard ball stage (260°).
Add butter and cook to light crack stage (270°).
Remove from heat; add salt and vanilla extract.
Pour into two large shallow pans.
When cool, break in pieces.

title: egg sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage.
Drain.
Saute onion and green pepper until tender.
Mix together.
Set aside. Mix last 5 ingredients together.
Add sausage.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch casserole.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Remove 1 hour before cooking.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes (let stand at least 10 minutes before cutting).
May sprinkle with more cheese before baking if desired.

title: baked corn dish
directions: Saute diced onions in butter or Crisco.
Mix a little of the milk with the 2 heaping tablespoonfuls of flour.
Add the rest of the cup of milk to the onions.
After onions and milk heat, thicken with the flour and milk mixture.
Add the corn and diced, cooked meat. Add salt and pepper to taste. Top with crumbled soda crackers.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: carl's pumpkin pie
directions: Put all in bowl and use eggbeater to mix.
Pour into unbaked pie shell and bake at 425° for 45 to 55 minutes.
About 10 minutes before pie is done; add the topping mix in a circle approximately 2 inches from outside crust and return to oven to finish baking.

title: kool-aid punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid according to directions on package.
Add fruit juices and chill.
Just before serving, add ginger ale or 7-Up. Yields 25 punch cups.

title: cherry rhubarb crunch
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with shortening or spray.
In large bowl, combine oats, brown sugar, flour and salt.
Stir well.
Using pastry cutter or fork, cut in butter until crumbly.
Pat 2 cups of mixture into prepared pan. Set aside remaining mixture.

title: impossible pie
directions: Blend flour into sugar.
Add eggs, milk, oleo, vanilla and coconut.
Beat well and pour into two 8-inch pie pans.
Cook in 350° oven until firm.

title: 7-up wedding punch
directions: Mix all together just before serving.
Delicious!

title: cavatini
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain.
Add Ragu and pepperoni.
Boil noodles until firm, then rinse in cold water.
Layer noodles in casserole dish.
Spoon sauce over noodles.
Sprinkle with cheese. Keep repeating layers.
Keep enough cheese to sprinkle on top. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes to melt cheese or microwave until cheese melts.

title: rocky road brownies
directions: In a medium bowl, add ingredients, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
After adding Marshmallow Creme, stir just enough to create brown and white swirls.
Spoon into a 9 x 13-inch brownie pan, lightly coated with cooking spray.
Bake at 325° for 18 minutes.

title: golden rolls
directions: Mash carrots (4 to 6), which have been cooked in 1 cup water. Soak yeast cake in lukewarm water for 5 minutes.
Add to warm carrot water.
Add carrots, sugar, shortening, salt and egg yolk. Mix the carrot mixture with 1 1/2 cups of flour, just until smooth.
Let rise until double.
Add beaten egg whites and remaining flour.
Let rise again until double.
Knead lightly. Shape into rolls.
Brush tops with melted butter.
Let rise until light.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: vegetarian pizza
directions: Roll
out
crescent
rolls
(do
not
separate).
Place complete section
of rolls on cookie sheet for crust.
Bake as directed on can.
Mix cheese, mayo and dressing together well. Spread onto baked cooled crust.
Sprinkle vegetables on top of cheese mixture.
Blend
for color.
Cut into small squares for serving.

title: oyster stew
directions: In saucepan, melt margarine.
Add oysters (drained), salt, pepper and celery; steam until oysters curly.
Blend milk together and add to mixture in saucepan.
Heat until hot...(do not boil). Cover and let stand about 15 minutes.
Re-heat if necessary. Serve with a dash of paprika and crackers.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Cream together butter and sugar until fluffy.
Stir sifted dry ingredients in alternately with milk. Beat until smooth.
Pour into loaf pan, 10 x 5 x 3-inch or 2-quart casserole.
Spoon fruit over batter; sprinkle with sugar.
Pour fruit juice over top.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
During baking, the fruit and juice go to the bottom and a cake-like layer forms on top.
Serve warm with cream or whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: 1 pound rock candy
directions: In 2-quart pan, stir.
Stir steady while heating.
Cook to 310°.
Take off heat.
Gently stir in (1 dram) oil flavoring from drugstore.
Add regular food coloring of your choice.
Use cookie sheet or aluminum foil pan.
Butter lightly.
Pour on cookie sheet or aluminum foil pan.
Mark with knife or wait until hard, then break with knife handle.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Spread dough in pizza pan, bake for 5 minutes according to instructions on package.
Saute all ingredients in olive oil, except sauce.
Spread sauce over dough.
Spread veggies over sauce.
Cover with grated Mozzarella cheese.
Bake 10 minutes. Great cold for lunches.
Healthy, too!!

title: pineapple delight
directions: Pinch the angel food cake in large bowl.
Mix whipped cream and Eagle Brand milk together with mixer.
Stir in lemon juice and pineapple (do not drain juice).
Pour mixture over angel food cake; stir together.

title: barbecue
directions: Fry onion and green pepper in 10-inch skillet until soft.
Add next 5 ingredients.
Cook slowly on low for 30 minutes.

title: easy bread
directions: Mix together warm water, yeast and sugar; set aside and let it foam.
Stir egg, oil, 3/4 cup sugar and salt into yeast mixture. Stir in 6 cups flour, 3 cups first.
Work until mixed up good. Put in greased bowl to rise until double.
Punch down and make into rolls.
Bake at 350° until golden brown.

title: orange salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate. Can be molded or served by the spoonful.

title: hamburger-cheese casserole
directions: Brown the meat and onion in large skillet.
Stir in the water, catsup and mustard.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Bring the mixture to a boil.
Stir in the uncooked rice; cover and remove from the heat.
Let it stand for 5 minutes, then fluff with a fork.
Top the casserole with cheese; cover until the cheese melts and blends in.

title: christmas chili roll
directions: Thoroughly mix cheese with ground cheese.
Add all other ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 4 rolls.
Put chili powder on wax paper.
Wrap rolls in aluminum foil and refrigerate until used. Slice before serving or cheese can be made into balls and at room temperature can be used as spread.
Sharp cheddar cheese can be substituted instead of longhorn.

title: turkey stroganoff
directions: Turkey and Sauce:
Brown ground turkey.
Combine sauce mixes, milk and water.
Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Add mushrooms and simmer 2 to 5 minutes longer.
Remove from heat and stir in sour cream.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time; mix well.
Add vanilla, lemon, baking soda, salt and sour cream; mix well.
Mix in flour, a little at a time.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold in and mix well.
Bake in large tube pan, greased and floured, at 350° for 1 hour and 15 minutes. Remove from pan and let cool.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix sugar and cinnamon together, mixing well.
Put in eggs, mixing well.
Add pumpkin, mixing well.
Add canned milk, mixing well.
Fill pie shells.

title: pineapple dessert
directions: Butter 9 x 13 pan; layer half of crushed wafers on bottom. Combine powdered sugar, butter and eggs.
Beat well and pour over wafer crust.
Mix together whipping cream, pineapple and chopped nuts.
Spread in pan.
Sprinkle remaining wafers on top and chill overnight.

title: rice krispies treat
directions: Mix sugar and Karo syrup in large glass bowl.
Microwave on High 4 to 5 minutes; stir.
Repeat this again until mixture boils. Remove from microwave immediately and add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and press into 9 x 13-inch buttered pan.
Melt chips together in a medium sized glass bowl on low-medium heat. Do not melt completely.
Chips will finish melting as you stir them.
Spread on top of Krispies bars.

title: crunchies
directions: Melt over low heat the chips and peanut butter; remove from heat.
Stir in 1/2 bag Chinese egg noodles (I use a little more). Drop on waxed paper with teaspoon.

title: salmon stew
directions: Remove skin and bone from salmon.
Mash salmon into pieces, then add salt, pepper, margarine and milk.
Bring to a boil, then remove from heat and enjoy.
Tastes like oyster stew, only better!

title: mexican dinner casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in a large skillet.
In a mixing bowl, combine tomatoes and spices.
Mash tomatoes with potato masher. Add tomato mixture to meat mixture.
In a 2-quart casserole, alternate layers of tortillas, meat mixture and cheese until all ingredients are used.
Cover and bake about 30 minutes until heated through.
Cut into pie shaped wedges; top with 1 teaspoon sour cream.

title: dinner in a bowl
directions: About 1 1/2 hours before serving, in a large vessel, cook beef in salt water until tender.
Add remaining ingredients, except macaroni; simmer until all is done.
Add macaroni and cook for about 15 minutes or until tender.
Serve in bowls with crackers and celery stuffed with pimento cheese.

title: crunchy double chip cookies
directions: Stir together flour, salt, baking powder and soda.
Beat in large bowl the sugar and margarine until fluffy.
Add eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients until thoroughly blended.
Add 2 cups of crushed cornflakes, chocolate and peanut butter morsels.
Drop by tablespoon into remaining cornflakes, coating completely.
Place on greased pan about 2 inches apart. Bake in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes.

title: champagne cake
directions: Combine cake mix, pudding, club soda, eggs and oil.
Beat 2 minutes.
Stir in rest.
Put in 3 (8-inch) layers greased and floured.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 40 minutes.

title: white turtle cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Combine cake mix, water, oil, eggs, and 1/2 can condensed milk.
Beat well with mixer.
Spread 1/2 of batter in a 9x13 buttered cake pan.
Bake approximately 20-30 minutes or until golden brown.
(Cake will be pulling away from sides of pan.)
Melt caramels, remaining milk and nuts.
Pour over hot cake, then add remaining 1/2 batter on top.
Spread evenly and bake for about 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: minestrone soup
directions: In Dutch oven, cook carrots, zucchini, onion, and garlic in oil for 7 minutes or until tender.
Add broth, V-8 juice, garbanzo beans, tomatoes, green beans, macaroni, and basil.
Bring to boil; reduce heat, simmer uncovered for 15 minutes.
Stir in parsley. Cook 5 minutes longer or until macaroni is tender.
Serves 8.

title: sock it to me cake
directions: Mix all ingredients in mixer, adding one egg at a time.
Pour 1/2 mixture in greased stem pan.
Mix 2 tablespoons of brown sugar and 1 teaspoon of cinnamon.
Sprinkle over batter.
Add remaining batter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chess pie
directions: Beat eggs. Add sugar, butter and vanilla. Mix well. Add vinegar last. Pour into pie shell. Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: sour cream chocolate cake
directions: Add butter, chocolate and water in a heavy saucepan and melt until smooth.
Cool.
Add sugar and eggs; mix until smooth.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Then stir in sour cream and vanilla. Grease and flour 2 cake pans and bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: bean salad
directions: (This is a desired amount recipe.)

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and onion together.
Add 1 tablespoon of flour. Add mushroom soup and 1 can water.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add sour cream.
Pour over noodles.

title: pumpkin muffins
directions: Combine dry ingredients in one bowl.
In large bowl, combine other ingredients and then add dry ones.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Fill and bake for 17 minutes at 350°.
Refrigerate after baking.
Yield:
12 muffins.

title: faye's pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs well. Add white Karo and dark Karo to eggs. Melt butter and add to mixture. Blend well. Fold in chopped pecans. Pour into pie crust and bake at 350° for about 1 hour or until medium brown and center of pie is set.

title: leaping leprechaun jelly-o's
directions: Mix unflavored gelatin with 1 cup cold water.
Stir lime gelatin into 1 cup of boiling water.
Add to unflavored gelatin mixture.
Stir in cold water.
Pour in oiled pan.
Chill several hours.
Let children use cookie cutters to cut favorite shapes. Remove shapes with spatula and eat!

title: greek salad
directions: Combine ingredients in large bowl.

title: dry roasted nuts
directions: Add sugar, milk and water to beaten egg whites. Coat nuts thoroughly with mixture using a rubber spatula. Place aluminum foil on jelly roll sheet. Arrange nuts in a single layer on foil. Bake for 15 minutes in 275 degree oven. Remove from oven, stir carefully lifting pecans from foil. Return to oven and bake an additional 15 minutes. Stir and repeat two more time. a total of one hour. Remove, allow to cool and store in a tight jar.

title: curried beef and rice
directions: Cook beef in a large skillet over medium-high heat, stirring to crumble.
Drain off pan drippings.
Stir in onion and next 5 ingredients; bring to a boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer 20 minutes or until rice is done.
Add green beans and cook just until beans are heated.
Serve immediately.
Yield:
4 servings.

title: smothered steak
directions: Put steak strips, flour, salt and pepper in crock-pot.
Stir well to coat steak.
Add all remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on low 8 hours (high:
4 hours).
Serve with rice.

title: hot dip
directions: Mix tomatoes, garlic salt, cooking oil, pepper and vinegar in blender. Serve with chips.

title: edith shepherd's raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins, sugar, water, salt, butter and lemon juice for five minutes.
Dissolve cornstarch in 3 tablespoons cold water. Add to raisin mixture.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Remove from fire and add lemon extract.
Pour into pastry-lined pie pan.
Make top of pastry arranged lattice fashion and bake 25 minutes in hot oven (425° F.).

title: holiday pudding
directions: Beat egg yolks.
Add sugar, flour and milk.
Cook in double boiler until creamy.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat; add vanilla.
Place alternate layers of crackers, fruit and nuts.
Add the pudding.
Sprinkle coconut on top.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Add 4 tablespoons sugar and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Spread over the pudding.
Bake in oven at 350° until brown.

title: nonfat chocolate sauce
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a small saucepan.
Add milk and stir until combined well.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until thick and bubbly.
Cook and stir 2 more minutes. Remove from heat; stir in vanilla.
Use warm or cool.
To improve smooth texture, thoroughly cool before using.
May be reheated in microwave.
Store in refrigerator for up to 1 week.
Makes approximately 16 rounded tablespoon servings.
Calories:

title: raspberry-peach sauce
directions: Combine peaches or nectarines, sugar and lemon juice in medium bowl.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Combine raspberries and light corn syrup in blender; puree until smooth.
Add to peaches.
Makes 1 3/4 cups.

title: swedish meatballs
directions: Beat egg and water together; add next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Shape into 1-inch balls; bake on cookie sheet for 10 minutes at 350°.
Drain on paper towels until cool.
Prepare sauce and add meatballs; keep warm in chafing dish or slow cooker.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil. Add dry ingredients. Fold in apples and pecans.
Grease and flour a long baking dish.
Put butterscotch on top of batter. Bake 55 to 60 minutes at 325°.

title: easy chicken pie
directions: Cook chicken and pull off the bone. Cut up in bottom of dish. Mix soup and chicken broth. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle salt and pepper. Mix flour, milk and butter. Pour over other mixture. Cook until golden brown.

title: easy filled cookies
directions: Mix shortening, brown sugar and eggs thoroughly. Stir in milk. Sift flour and measure, then add soda and salt; sift again. Stir into preceding mixture. Chill at least 1 hour.

Heat oven to 400°. Drop rounded teaspoons of dough 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Place 1/2 teaspoon of date filling on top of dough and drop an additional small teaspoon of dough on top of filling. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Microwave the first 3 ingredients; pour into shell or crust. Add strawberries or favorite fruit.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Use clear punch bowl or clear bowl.
Divide cake in half and crumble each half.
Pack half of crumbled cake on bottom of bowl. In order, use half of each ingredient: pudding, coconut, pineapple, fruit cocktail, cherries, Cool Whip and pecans.
Layer again, starting with cake first, then in order as first.
Keep refrigerated.

title: creamy potato soup
directions: In saucepan, cook bacon until crisp.
Set bacon aside.
Pour off all but 3 tablespoons drippings.
Add onions and brown.
Add potatoes and water.
Cook, covered, about 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Blend in chicken soup, milk and salt.
Heat, but do not boil.
Garnish with bacon.

title: cream cheese stroganoff
directions: In large skillet, add butter, onions and beef cubes.
Stir-fry until beef is browned (about 10 minutes).
Add cream of mushroom soup, milk and cream cheese until creamy.
Simmer on low for 20 minutes.
Cook noodles to package directions and combine with cream cheese mixture.

title: spicy bean dip
directions: In a medium saucepan, combine all ingredients.
Heat thoroughly over medium-high heat until cheese is melted and texture is smooth, stirring frequently, approximately 5 to 7 minutes.
Serve warm with nacho chips for dipping.
Makes 3 cups.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix well and bake in greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: hot cottage potato salad
directions: Mix all together and pour 1 c. melted butter and 3/4 c. milk over mixture.
Stir.
Sprinkle corn flake crumbs over top.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs, one at a time. Add Carnation cream and flavorings.
Add flour a cup at a time and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Cool in pan.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Stir flour, salt, nutmeg, cinnamon, soda, and baking powder together in a bowl.
Add sugar and oats.
Mix in thoroughly the shortening, milk, and egg.
Stir in raisins and nuts.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheet. Bake at 375° about 8 minutes.
Cool on a wire rack.
Yields 2 dozen.

title: squash "souffle"
directions: Melt 1/2 stick of butter in casserole dish.
Sprinkle with heavy layer of Pepperidge Farm herbed crumbs.
Alternate layers of squash mixture and crumbs, ending with crumbs.
Dot with butter. May be refrigerated until needed.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Bake 35 minutes, if refrigerated.

title: tijuana torte
directions: Brown ground beef with onion, add Lawry's seasoning and canned tomatoes then simmer for 10-15 minutes.

title: hash brown potato casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients for potato mixture together and put in long cake pan.
Top with 1/2 cup melted butter and cornflake mixture.
Bake for about 1 hour at 350°.

title: pumpkin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, soda, cloves, nutmeg and salt.
In a large bowl, mix together sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Beat in eggs.
Add dry ingredients; stir until smooth.
Stir in nuts.
Pour batter into 2 to 3 loaf pans (greased and floured).
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: my mother's lemon meringue pie
directions: Crush enough wafers to line bottom of pie pan.
Line edges of pie pan with whole wafers.
Separate eggs.
Beat whites with sugar until stiff.
Grate and juice lemons.
Mix juice, peel, egg yolks and condensed milk.
Pour this mixture in pie pan.
Top with meringue.
Bake until meringue browns, about 12 minutes, at 350°. Refrigerate.

title: martha's chili(chili cook off entry - 1994)
directions: Brown ground beef with chopped onion.
Drain grease off (if any).
Add to beef, beans, tomato sauce and water.
Stir in chili powder, salt, pepper and garlic powder.
Cook over low to medium heat for at least 1 hour (longer won't hurt).
Stir as needed.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken; remove bone, save broth.
Melt margarine and mix with stuffing mix.
Mix 2 cans of soup with 2 cans of broth.

title: green tomato relish
directions: Chop all ingredients and put in large enameled kettle.
Add salt.
Let stand overnight, then drain.
Add vinegar, sugar, mustard and flour.
Cook 20 minutes, stirring often so it doesn't stick.
(Count time from when it starts to "perk.")
Can in hot jars; process 10 minutes in hot water bath.

title: italian torti bread
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 4 small loaves.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix Marshmallow Creme and cream cheese together until all blended together.
Serve with apple wedges, grapes, strawberries, cantaloupe slices, fresh peach slices and even bananas.

title: easy quick rolls
directions: Dissolve water and yeast.
In saucepan, melt milk, sugar, salt and margarine.
Set aside to cool.
Combine milk mixture and yeast.
Add flour.
Let rise one hour.
Make out rolls.
Place in greased glass ovenware.
Bake at 450° about 15 minutes or until done.
Makes about 18 rolls.

title: meatballs
directions: Mix first 9 ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
