Melt shortening in skillet, brown balls, remove them and drain.
Heat chili sauce and grape jelly in skillet until jelly is melted, stirring constantly.
Add meatballs to sauce and stir until cooked.
Let simmer 30 minutes.
Serve hot.
Makes around 5 dozen meatballs.

title: instant hot chocolate
directions: Mix well.
To an 8 ounce mug, use 1/3 cup milk.
Add boiling water and stir well.

title: ala chicken
directions: Dip chicken in eggs.
Dip in bread crumbs or flour.
Dice garlic.
Fry chicken in oil and garlic.
Put lemon in whole slices and simmer.
Take juice out and pour over chicken with more lemon and garlic.
Add salt and pepper.
Wash and clean lettuce and put over chicken in pan.
Baste with juice.
Cover and cook for 10 minutes.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Fry meat, garlic and onion together; drain.
Add tomatoes and any other desired seasonings.
Simmer.

title: maple-baked limas
directions: Wash and soak beans all night.
Bake at least 1 1/2 hours until beans are tender.

title: greek hamburgs
directions: Mix all ingredients and form into patties.
Broil until done and serve topped with sliced onion, lettuce, tomatoes with or without bun.

title: butterscotch fudge
directions: Combine morsels and peanut butter in top of double boiler. Place over hot (not boiling) water until morsels melt.
Remove from water and stir until blended.
Add milk and stir until blended. Spread in foil lined 8-inch square pan.
Press chopped nuts into fudge.
Cut into 1-inch squares when firm.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Cook until thickens.
Remove from heat and add 1 stick of butter and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Stir until butter is melted.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party pizzas
directions: Cook meat, crumbled, until done.
Drain and blot to rid of grease.
Add cheese to meat mixture; heat, stirring constantly. (Burns easily.)
Add dressing and spread on bread.
Freeze or broil until hot.

title: tortilla casserole
directions: Brown hamburger and onion in skillet.
Drain.
Put in the bottom of a 13 x 9 Pyrex dish.
Tear tortillas in strips and put on top of hamburger, then put grated cheese over the tortilla strips.
Add beans, then spread soup and tomatoes.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375°, uncovered, for about 30 to 40 minutes or until good and bubbly.

title: the best fudge pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour in a large mixing bowl, stirring well. Stir
in
melted butter.
Combine cocoa, water and eggs; beat well.
Pour
into
sugar
mixture,
stirring
well.
Pour mixture into
a buttered 9-inch pie plate.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or
until
set.
Garnish
pie with pecan halves.
Cool completely and slice.
Yields 1 (9-inch) pie.

title: corn pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients except margarine.
Pour into a 9 x 11-inch pan.
Melt margarine and pour over batter.
Bake until like cake, uncovered, for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.
Cut into squares and serve hot/warm.
Serves 4 to 6.
Recipe may be doubled.

title: hot poppy seed bread
directions: Place one slice of cheese between each 1-inch slice of bread. Place bread in tinfoil.
Lay foil open on top.
Pour butter, onion, poppy seed and parsley over bread. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes until top is crispy. Sprinkle with paprika. Serve.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Measure flour in medium bowl; cut in shortening with pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in cheese and milk.
Knead lightly 3 or 4 times.
Roll dough to 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter and place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake at 450° for 10 to 12 minutes.
These are super!

title: philly miracle whip wreath
directions: Combine cream cheese and salad dressing until well blended. Add the remaining ingredients and mix well.
Chill.
Place drinking glass in the center of a serving platter.
Arrange the mixture around the glass.
Garnish with chopped parsley and pimento to resemble a wreath.

title: shredded zucchini frittata
directions: In heavy 6 or 7-inch skillet, heat 2 tablespoons oil and saute onion and garlic until tender, stirring.
Increase heat, add zucchini and saute until almost tender, stirring frequently.
In bowl, beat eggs; stir in cheese, salt and pepper.
Add to zucchini mixture, reducing heat.
Cover and cook until eggs are set on bottom.
Loosen sides and bottom, then invert onto warm plate.
Add remaining 1 tablespoon oil to skillet.
Slide frittata back into skillet.
Cover and cook until set.
Cut into wedges.
Serves 4.

title: cherry salad
directions: Soften Cool Whip slightly.
Mix pie filling and Eagle Brand milk.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into serving dish.
Chill at least 1 hour before serving.

title: 5 minute soup
directions: Combine all ingredients; cook and stir over medium heat, until heated through.

title: hamburger noodle casserole
directions: Put hamburger, sausage and onion in skillet and fry until red is gone from the hamburger, but not brown.
Add chili powder, tomato paste, soup and the corn; cook 10 minutes.
While this is cooking, put noodles in hot salted water and cook until done.
Put in large casserole in layers the meat mixture and the noodles. Then put grated cheese on top.
Bake until cheese is melted. Serve hot.

title: big mac special sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put on hamburger.

title: sourdough starter
directions: Let stand until bubbly and well-fermented, at least 1 day. Store, covered, in refrigerator. Use in 10 days to begin
another cake.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put a layer of each one of the items and over this a pint of mayonnaise sweetened with sugar.
Layer all vegetables etc. twice and lastly put rest of the mayonnaise.
Seal with Saran Wrap and chill at least 8 hours or overnight.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add broccoli in frozen state to onions.
Cover and simmer over low heat until broccoli breaks apart.
To this, add cheese, soup, water, milk and rice.
Put all in casserole dish and bake in 350° for 45 minutes.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Blend well all ingredients and let stand overnight.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Combine peanut butter, sugar, egg and vanilla to thoroughly blend.
Drop by teaspoon 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Flatten with bottom of glass dipped in sugar.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes until lightly browned.
Cool on rack.

title: honey oat bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Pour milk over shortening, honey and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. stir in 2 c. flour, add dissolved yeast and oats.
Mix well.
Stir in enough additional flour to make soft dough.
Turn out on to floured board and knead 8 to 10 minutes, until smooth and elastic.
Place in large greased bowl, turn once to coat surface.
Cover.
Let rise in warm place about 1 hour or double in bulk.
Punch down.
Cover, let rise 10 minutes.
Divide dough in half.
Roll each half to form a 15 x 9-inch rectangle. Roll up.
Press ends and seams good to seal.
Place in two 9 x 5 loaf pans.
Brush lightly with melted butter.
Cover, let rise about 45 minutes or nearly doubled.
Bake at 375 about 45 minutes. Remove from pans.

title: old fashioned fried peaches
directions: Melt butter in an iron skillet.
Place peach halves evenly in skillet.
Fill the peach cavities with brown sugar.
Simmer over low heat until well cooked.
Serve while warm with cream and dash of cinnamon and nutmeg.

title: "easy" chicken casserole
directions: Boil 1 chicken.
Remove bones and skin and cut in pieces.
Mix soups, sour cream and onion soup together.
Mix Stove Top dressing according to directions.
Put in a casserole, first the chicken. Then cover with 1/2 the soup mixture.
Then layer on the stuffing mix.
Cover with the remainder of soup.
Top with crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Use 9 x 13-inch casserole or pan.
tags: cream of celery soup or mushroom

title: smothered okra
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Pour the oil into the bottom of a large roasting pot, not cast-iron. Add the remaining ingredients and stir to mix well. Cover the pot with a lid. Bake, stirring occasionally, for 30 minutes. Reduce heat to 300°. Continue baking with the lid on for 1 1/2 to 2 hours or until slime has disappeared. Bake, uncovered, for the last 15 minutes of cooking time. Remove and cool completely before storing in freezer containers. This is excellent to serve as a side dish or to use as the base for okra gumbo. Makes 10 servings.

title: hamburger cheese dip
directions: While cutting up cheese, brown beef and onions in skillet. Drain mixture and place in slow cooker. Place all remaining ingredients in slow cooker and combine. Cover. Cook on low 2 hours or until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally. Serve over baked potatoes or with tortilla chips.

title: chicken cordon bleu
directions: Combine mustards; brush chicken evenly with the mixture.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.

Cook chicken in the butter for 4 minutes; turn and continue cooking for 2 minutes. Lay the ham and cheese over chicken; continue cooking until chicken is cooked through and cheese is melted, about 3 minutes.

title: apple-orange tzimmes *
directions: Put all the ingredients in a large heavy pot and cover.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer, covered, for one hour.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion, salt and pepper. Shape into balls.
Combine tomato sauce, ketchup and sugar.
Pour over meatballs and bake for 1 1/2 hours in 350° oven.

title: cottage cheese loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes. Serve with gravy.

title: vidalia onion pie
directions: Saute onions in the margarine until tender.
Pour into pie crust.
Beat eggs slightly.
Add milk, salt and pepper.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes in a 425° oven.
Check doneness by inserting knife near the center.
If it comes out clean, the pie is done.

title: amish friendship bread starter
directions: Bake in well greased and sugared pans for 1 hour at 350°. Reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes or until center is done.

title: oven stew
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in deep stew pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and bake at 225° for 2 hours and then bake at 250° for 2 hours.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Cook and mash potatoes.
Add sour cream, cottage cheese, onion, butter, salt and pepper.
Mix well.
Place in casserole dish.
Sprinkle parmesan on top.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: birthday party punch
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients three hours ahead to secure a good flavor.
Put into refrigerator.
When it's time to serve, add ginger ale and sherbet.
Serves 30.

title: succotash
directions: Combine beans, corn and milk in saucepan.
Simmer until tender. Add butter and seasonings.
Mix well. Serve.
Yields 4 servings.

title: hamburger corn bread pie
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Add seasoning and tomatoes.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add beans and pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with corn bread.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes or until brown.

title: english pea casserole
directions: Mix peas and cream of mushroom soup.
Pinch off in little pieces 3 pieces of loaf bread.
Slice eggs and add to mixture. Pinch off cheese in pieces.
Stir all up together.
Pour in baking dish.
Crumble crackers across the top of casserole.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes.

title: casserole mexicana
directions: Brown meat in oil and add next 3 ingredients and boil.
Put in 2-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle cheese over meat, chips around edges and olives in middle.
Bake 10 minutes at 350°.

title: sauerkraut relish
directions: Combine sauerkraut and sugar.
Let stand for 30 minutes.
Cut sauerkraut with scissors.
Mix all ingredients.
Chill for 12 hours.
Makes 12 servings.

title: pasta and ham mornay
directions: Prepare pasta as directed
on package.	Rinse with warm water. Drain.
Set aside.

title: sweet and sour bites
directions: Cut each wiener 7 times for bite size pieces.
Add wieners to sauce.
Serve hot in fondue pot.
Use toothpicks to serve.
Makes about 160 pieces.

title: hummingbird cake
directions: Combine flour, sugar, salt, soda and cinnamon.
Stir.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pan(s) - 2 10-inch round pans or 1 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 375° for approximately 1 hour.
Cool and ice with cream cheese icing of your choice.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Put rice and margarine in saucepan.
Cook until rice is brown. Pour in casserole dish.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili cheese dip
directions: Brown hamburger meat.
Drain.
Add all other ingredients except cheese.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Add cheese.
Melt.
Pour into dish and serve with chips.

title: lemon bread
directions: Grease 2 loaf pans and line with wax paper.
Mix 1 cup sugar, butter and lemon extract.
Beat in eggs.
Sift dry ingredients and add alternately with milk.
Beat just enough to blend.
Fold in nuts and lemon rind.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Combine juice and 1/2 cup sugar.
Mix well.
Remove baked bread from pan while hot; drizzle with lemon juice mixture over top and into cracks.
Do not cut for 24 hours.
Freezes well.

title: creamy corn pudding
directions: Melt butter in a heavy saucepan over low heat; add flour, sugar and salt, stirring until smooth.
Cook 1 minute, stirring constantly until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and stir in corn.
Beat eggs well and gradually add 1/4 hot mixture into eggs. Stir.
Add to remaining hot mixture, stirring constantly.
Pour into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mexican corn casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: easy strawberry shortcake
directions: Mix jello with boiling water.
Add cold water; add frozen sliced strawberries; mix.
Pour into angel food cake pan. Immediately put angel cake on top of mixture.
Chill overnight.

title: yum-a-setta
directions: Brown hamburger with onion; drain.
Add brown sugar and tomato soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Mix well.
Cook noodles; drain and mix with cream of chicken soup.

title: grandpa gilkerson's rolls
directions: Add butter, sugar, salt and milk.
Mix well.
Let cool (lukewarm); crumble in yeast.
Stir until dissolved.
Add 1 cup flour; beat with mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; beat until smooth.
Mix in remaining flour.
Cover.
Let rest 5 minutes. Knead 10 minutes.
Let rise.
Make rolls; let rise.
Bake 8 to 10 minutes at 425°.
Makes 3 dozen rolls.

title: turtle cake
directions: Mix cake according to package directions.
Set aside half of the batter; pour remaining batter into a greased and floured 9 x 13-inch baking pan and bake at 350° for 18 minutes.
Meanwhile, in a saucepan over low heat, melt the caramels, milk and margarine. Remove from heat and add nuts.
Pour over baked cake; sprinkle with chocolate chips and reserved batter.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more or until cake springs back when lightly touched.
Cool.
Cut into squares.
Top with ice cream or powdered sugar and a pecan half.

title: potato soup
directions: Peel and boil potatoes; dice.
Strain and add all other ingredients.

title: cashew chicken
directions: In a medium bowl combine 2 tablespoons soy sauce, 2 tablespoons sherry, 1 tablespoon cornstarch, ginger root, garlic, sugar and salt; mix well.
Add chicken cubes and let stand 30 minutes.
In wok or large skillet heat 2 tablespoons peanut oil.
Add cashews; stir-fry over medium heat 1 to 2 minutes until browned.
Remove and drain on paper towels.
If necessary add 1 tablespoon peanut oil to wok; turn heat to high.
Add pea pods and mushrooms; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes until crisp-tender.
Add bamboo shoots; stir briefly.
Remove to large bowl.
In wok, heat 1 tablespoon oil.
Add one-third of the chicken mixture; stir-fry 3 to 4 minutes until chicken is no longer pink inside.
Remove to bowl with vegetables.
Repeat process, adding 1 tablespoon oil each time, until all chicken is cooked.
Combine remaining soy sauce, sherry and cornstarch with chicken broth or water and Worcestershire sauce; pour into wok and cook, stirring until sauce boils and thickens.
Return chicken and vegetables to wok; mix and reheat briefly.
Stir in cashews.
Remove to serving dish and sprinkle with green onions.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: ripe tomato relish
directions: Place cutup peeled tomatoes in a large boiler.
Chop other ingredients; add to tomatoes with sugar, spices and vinegar.
Cook slowly until thickness you desire.
Stir often.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Roll out crescent rolls and press in the bottom of a 9 x 13 glass dish. Pour sausage over the crescent rolls. Sprinkle cheese over sausage. Beat eggs, milk, salt and pepper. Pour over all other ingredients. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: italian roast beef
directions: Rub horseradish and mustard over meat.
Cut garlic into 4 pieces.
With the sharp point of a knife, make 4 small gashes in the meat and bury the garlic in the meat.
Roast in 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Cover the meat tightly and cook for another 1 1/2 hours.
Remove meat from pan and let it get very cold.
Slice very thin and lay the meat in the leftover juices.
Let it simmer in the juices for at least 30 minutes.
(If there is not enough juice, add about 1 cup of water or beef bouillon.)

title: cheddar snacks
directions: Mix oil and spices.
Put remaining ingredients into a big bag. Shake.
Add spice mixture and shake again.
Serve.

title: custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and salt and beat again.
Scald milk and add slowly.
Stir well and add vanilla.
Pour into pastry shell, prebaked about 5 to 10 minutes in hot oven.
Place in moderately slow oven about 15 to 30 minutes.
When a knife stuck in center comes out dry, baking is completed.

title: super sweet cucumber and onion relish
directions: When grinding cucumbers, save the juice (I use about half.) Mix spices with sugar and pour over all ingredients into canning vessel, enamel or stainless.
Bring to a boil, but do not scorch and simmer 20 minutes.

title: veggie pizza
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and line bottom of 15 x 9 x 1 inch pan. Cook at 350° for 7 to 8 minutes or until golden brown. Mix cream cheese, mayo and dressing mix on medium speed one minute. Spread on crescent rolls and top with vegetables. Your may adjust the vegetables to your taste, but this mix is very colorful. Top with shredded cheese. Cover and chill over night. Cut into small squares.

title: taco dip
directions: Brown hamburger and drain.
Add cheese (cut in cubes) and melt.
Add chili and tomatoes.
Cook on low heat 15 to 20 minutes, until all is melted and blended together.
Serve with nacho chips

title: cheesy pears
directions: Arrange pear halves, cut side up, on glass serving plate or shallow dish.
Microwave cream cheese in glass bowl 1/4 to 1/2 minute or until softened.
Stir until creamy.
Blend in sugar and vanilla.

title: torta rustica
directions: In large nonstick skillet, heat oil over medium-high heat. Add sausage; cook 6 to 7 minutes, stirring to break into small pieces until browned.
With slotted spoon, remove sausage from skillet; set aside.
Add onion to skillet; cook, stirring frequently, for 2 to 3 minutes, or until tender.
Stir in broccoli, basil, fennel seed and salt.
Cook for 4 to 5 minutes, or until broccoli is tender.
Transfer mixture to medium bowl.
In small bowl, combine Ricotta, egg substitute, milk and Parmesan cheese; set aside.

title: ravioli
directions: Dough:
Mix all ingredients together, then work the dough well.

title: corn casserole
directions: Beat eggs well; add corn.
Stir until blended together.

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix pudding with milk.
In separate bowl, beat cream cheese. Gradually add pudding to cream cheese and beat.
Add Cool Whip. Put 1/2 of cookie crumbs in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan, then put pudding mixture on top of cookies.
Add rest of crumbs on top.

title: wine jello salad
directions: Pour cup of boiling water over Jell-O.
Dissolve Jell-O and set aside.
Cut up oranges.
Stir in.
Add grapes and 1 cup cold water, wine, nuts and sugar.
Add Jell-O and mix thoroughly.
Put in refrigerator to gel.
Serve topped with whipped cream.

title: ginger ale punch
directions: Place water, sugar and cinnamon in saucepan over high heat. Bring to a boil, stirring to dissolve sugar.
Boil 5 minutes. Remove from heat and strain.
Stir syrup into other juices.
Mix well and chill until ready to serve.
Add ginger ale and cherries just before serving.

title: stew
directions: Flour stew meat; brown and simmer in water until tender. Place meat and juice in a Dutch oven or large pot.
Add other ingredients and cook until vegetables are done.
(Check package directions for length of cooking time.)

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef and when almost done, chop onions and cook with beef. Drain beef when done. Heat thoroughly until all vegetables are warm.

title: creamed mushrooms
directions: In butter, saute onion.
Add a little caraway seed.
Add chopped mushrooms and saute.

title: scalloped pineapple
directions: Mix sugar, butter, eggs, pineapple and crumbs in a baking dish.
Pour juice over top.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: aunt susan's "chili sauce"
directions: Melt butter in saucepan.
Add flour and cook.
Add chili powder, 1 teaspoon of salt and garlic powder.
Cook until blended. Add tomato juice and water.
Let thicken.

title: baked rice
directions: Bake, covered, for 1 hour at 350°.

title: wild rice soup
directions: Boil chicken, onion, celery and carrots until cooked.
Cook wild rice.
After all is cooked, add bacon, Cheddar cheese, water chestnuts, chicken broth, cream of chicken soup and half and half. Heat and serve.
Freezes well.

title: easy potato casserole
directions: Peel and slice potatoes crosswise.
Rotate ingredients, starting and finishing with cream of chicken soup.
Add 1/2 can water.
Cover and bake at 350° until potatoes are tender.
May cover with cheese if preferred.

title: fiesta rice
directions: Brown hamburger and onion together. Drain any fat. Put remainder of ingredients in pan and mix together. Put into casserole dish; cover and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: apple-jello treats
directions: Slice red Delicious apples into wedges.
Toss the apple wedges in dry strawberry jello.
Serve with Cool Whip.
Tasty and fat free!

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown sausage and onion until done.
Drain off fat.
Add soup, milk and instant rice together.
Stir into sausage mixture.
Bake in casserole dish at 350°.

title: apple pie
directions: Mix crust together and roll out on floured board.
Makes a top and bottom.

title: best baked beans
directions: Steam onion and bell peppers until tender.
Combine with bacon, then stir in pork and beans.
Then add remaining ingredients.
Spoon into greased 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake at 400° for 40 minutes.
Yields 5 3/4 cups.

title: imperial chicken
directions: Line baking pan with foil.
Mix Italian bread crumbs and Parmesan cheese.
Remove skin and excess fat from chicken breasts. Season chicken to taste with a blend of Morton's "Nature's Seasons" black pepper and Cajun King's Cajun herbed spice mix.
Melt margarine and mix with garlic.
Dip chicken into margarine and garlic mixture.
Then, dip into Italian crumb mix.
Place chicken into foil lined pan with crumbs.
If there is any margarine/garlic mixture left, pour over prepared chicken pieces.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chris' and g.t.'s lemon pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a bowl, beat egg yolks.
Stir in condensed milk, lemon juice and rind.
Turn into shell.
In a small bowl beat egg whites with cream of tartar until foamy. Gradually add sugar and beat until stiff.
Spread over filling. Bake 10 to 15 minutes or until meringue is golden brown.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt in mixing bowl.
Put cocoa, water, margarine and oil in saucepan; bring to boil.
Pour over dry ingredients while hot.
Dissolve soda in buttermilk, add along with eggs and vanilla to mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Grease and flour pan.
Pour into 18 x 12 x 1-inch pan.
Bake for 18 minutes at 400°. While cake is baking make icing.

title: best-ever fudge
directions: In a heavy 4 quart pan combine sugar, butter, salt and evaporated milk.
Stir over low heat until sugar is dissolved. Increase heat to medium; continue cooking and stirring to soft ball stage.
Remove from heat.
Immediately add chocolate, Marshmallow Creme, pecans and vanilla.
Stir virgorously until chocolate pieces are melted.
When mixture begins to thicken turn into 12x7 1/2x2 inch pan.

title: picante cornbread
directions: Heat 9 in cast-iron skillet at 425° for 5 min. Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl; make a well in center of mixture. Combine buttermilk, eggs, and picante sauce.

Add dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened. Remove skillet from oven. Add butter and return to oven for 1 minute or until butter melts. Pour melted butter into batter, stir until blended. Pour into hot skillet, bake at 425° for 20 min or until done.

title: mock apricot jam
directions: Cook zucchini for 1 hour with a little water until clear.
Add sugar, crushed pineapple, lemon juice and pectin. Boil hard for 6 minutes.
Add apricot Jell-O.
Pour into jars and seal.
Makes 6 pints.

title: cake in a jar
directions: You will need 8 straight sided, wide mouth canning jars (pint size) and 8 rings and lids for jars.

title: sherry mushroom chicken(senior guys '94)
directions: Place chicken breasts in a 9 x 13-inch ovenproof dish.
Season chicken with spices.
Sprinkle mushrooms and onions over chicken breasts.
Mix together soup, sour cream and sherry.
Pour over chicken and mushrooms.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serve over wild rice.

title: chicken and dumplings
directions: In large pan, boil chicken until it comes off bones easily. Remove chicken and cut into chunks.
Mix flour and shortening. The mix will be very stiff - I mix it with my hands.
Add more shortening if needed.
Put the dough between waxed paper and roll out very thin.
Cut in strips and put small pieces in the boiling chicken broth with enough water added to make two quarts.	Add chicken to pot, stir to heat through and serve.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Mix together first four ingredients.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Dip cut-up chicken pieces in melted butter and lay them on the first layer.
Sprinkle with salt (if desired), pepper and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix ingredients in order given; pour into unbaked deep dish pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, until firm and slightly browned.

title: crabmeat spread
directions: Combine cream cheese and milk.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Spoon into an ovenproof dish.
Sprinkle with paprika. Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Serve piping hot on crackers or party rye bread.

title: heart cookie pizza
directions: Lightly grease a baking sheet.
Spread half of the refrigerated cookie dough on prepared baking sheet and shape it into an 11 x 8-inch heart.
Reserve the remaining dough for sugar cookies.
Bake heart cookie in a 350° oven for about 15 minutes or until golden.
Cool on wire rack.
Carefully transfer heart cookie to a nice tray or platter.
Evenly spread 1/2 cup of frosting over heart to within 1/4 inch of the edges.
Top with strawberries. With pastry bag, pipe remaining frosting around edges of heart or put kisses or star candy around the edge.

title: cherry cheese ring-around
directions: Grease tube pan.
Spread cherry pie filling on bottom of pan. Sprinkle 3 tablespoons chopped nuts on top of cherry pie filling. Cut loaf into 20 pieces.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, vanilla and remainder of nuts.
Place spoonful of cream cheese mixture in middle of each piece of dough.
Seal edges around cream cheese to form a ball.
Place balls in double row in pan on top of cherry pie filling and nuts.

title: kay's sausage quiche
directions: Preheat oven to 375 degrees.
In medium skillet, fry sausage until cooked; remove and drain.
Reserve 2 tbsp. fat; saute onions and pepper in fat for 3 minutes.
Combine cheese and flour; stir in sausage, green pepper and onion.
Mix well.
Mix remaining ingredients and add to sausage mixture; mix well.
Pour into pie shell and bake on cookie sheet for 35-40 minutes.
Cool and slice.

title: italian meat balls
directions: Mix eggs into dry ingredients and shape into balls the size of a walnut.
Fry in a small amount of oil.
(Careful!
They brown quickly.)
Place in casserole and cover with tomato sauce.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Serve with spaghetti or potatoes. Leftovers are good made into sandwiches.

title: baked beans
directions: Fry onion in bacon grease until clear, not brown.
Add all ingredients together in fried onion pan and let boil until thickened.

title: fruit squares
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients together.
Spread slightly more than half the mixture over bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread the preserves over mixture in pan, leaving an inch border all around pan.
Crumble remaining mixture on top.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: winter cider
directions: Heat slowly until red hots are dissolved.
Stir occasionally. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.
This is so simple and so very delicious!
For those of you who go "yuck" at apple cider, your "yuck" will turn to "yum".

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cook beans and peas separately; drain.
In a bowl mix beans, peas and remaining ingredients except onion rings.
Put into a casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Spread onion rings over top and bake an additional 5 to 10 minutes.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Boil macaroni and drain.
Stir in butter and eggs.
Mix salt and sugar with 1 tablespoon hot water.
Add to milk.
Add the cheese, leaving enough
to
sprinkle
on
top.
Pour
into buttered casserole dish.
Add
remaining
milk.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes or until custard is set and top is crusty.

title: asparagus rolls with cheese
directions: Roll asparagus in rolls.
Bake according to directions.
Heat soup and spoon over rolls.
Serve immediately.

title: country corn bread
directions: Heat oven to 450°. Grease 9-inch square pan. Place in oven to heat.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Toast the bread in the oven.
Spread the butter on the toast. Mix the cinnamon and sugar.
Then put it on the toast.
Good!

title: christmas eve beet borscht
directions: In a food processor, grate beets and onion.
Combine with water in a large saucepan.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat to a simmer.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer 1 hour.
Serve hot with a spoonful of sour cream to garnish each soup bowl.

title: almond tea
directions: Pour 2 cups hot water over tea bags.
Let stand 5 minutes. Add 2 cups cold water.
Remove tea bags.
Add and dissolve 2 cups sugar.
Add remaining ingredients.
Serve hot or cold.
Serves 25.

title: lemon-raspberry pie
directions: In a small saucepan, combine raspberries and cornstarch.
Cook and stir until thickened and clear.
Cool 10 minutes.
Chill thoroughly, about 20 minutes.
In a large bowl, combine Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice.
Fold in whipped cream.
Spread 1/3 lemon mixture into pie shell.
Top with raspberry mixture, then remaining lemon mixture.
Chill thoroughly.

title: quick and delicious chocolate chip and cream cheese squares
directions: Spread	1 package of softened cookie mix in bottom of a 9
x 13-inch
pan.
Beat
the
eggs, sugar, vanilla and cream cheese. Spread
over
dough in pan.
Spread remaining package of dough on top of cream cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pina colada dip(low-fat recipe)
directions: In a medium bowl, blend yogurt and pudding mix.
Stir in the drained pineapple and extracts.
Fold in whipped topping.
Cover and refrigerate until serving time.
Serve with Keebler low-fat Graham Selects.
Also, a good dip for fruit.

title: brueliatti
directions: Open rolls, but do not separate into individual rolls.
Unroll the 2 pieces and place on floured surface.
Gently press together perforated seams to form 2 rectangles.
Roll lightly with floured rolling pin to form 2 rectangles about 5 x 10 to 20-inches each. Coat each piece with a light layer of olive oil, leaving a narrow strip along one long side unoiled.
Crumble raw beef to cover dough; sprinkle with black pepper, cheese, onion and olives. Start with one long edge, roll up jellyroll style toward unoiled edge; press edge lightly to seal.
Cut roll into 1 to 1 1/2-inch pinwheel rolls; press together gently.
Place on end on oiled baking sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.
Can bake, freeze and reheat in microwave.

title: saucy vegetables
directions: Defrost green beans in microwave.
In dish, combine all ingredients, using only half can of onions.
Cover with plastic wrap; microwave 10 minutes.
Stir halfway through cooking time. Let sit 3 to 4 minutes.
Top with remaining onions and serve.

title: cheddar mashed potato bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart casserole, combine soup, sour cream, onion and pepper.
Stir in potatoes.
Bake 30 minutes or until hot.
Makes about 4 cups or 8 servings.

title: minnie's molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, spices and salt.
Cream shortening with sugar until light and fluffy.
Add egg, then molasses and beat well.
Add all dry ingredients and follow with vinegar and water mixture.

title: spicy pineapple-zucchini bread
directions: With a rotary beater, beat eggs to blend.
Add salad oil, sugar and vanilla.
Continue beating mixture until thick and foamy.
With a spoon, stir in zucchini and pineapple.
Combine all-purpose flour (unsifted), soda, salt, baking powder, cinnamon, nutmeg, walnuts and currants; stir dry ingredients gently into zucchini mixture just until blended.

title: broccoli corn bake
directions: Combine corn, broccoli, egg, 1/2 cup cracker crumbs, onion, 2 tablespoons butter or margarine, salt and pepper.
Turn into casserole.

title: norwegian ale soup
directions: Beat ale, water, eggs and cream in saucepan and bring to boil. Add the sugar; stir constantly.
Garnish with toast cubes. Serves 4.

title: mock potato salad(low calorie)
directions: Mix all ingredients together and serve.

title: spinach cornbread
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients well, then add cornbread mix.
Bake in an 8 x 12-inch pan for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: chicken dish
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over chicken.
Mix together mushroom soup and sour cream and spread on chicken.
Seal with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake an additional 30 minutes.

title: lemon puddle cake
directions: Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or cookie sheet.
Mix all cake ingredients together and bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes (20 minutes on cookie sheet).

title: cheese soup
directions: Boil first 5 ingredients until vegetables are tender; mash vegetables.
Melt butter; add flour, then milk.
Add to stock. Add and cook last 4 ingredients on low heat until cheese melts.

title: no crust pumpkin pie
directions: Pour all in a blender and blend at medium speed until well blended. Pour in a greased 10-inch pie plate and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: italian minestrone soup
directions: Soak white beans for 6 hours in 1-quart of water; pour beans with soaking liquid into stock pot.
Bring to a boil and add garlic, onions and celery.
Cook 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender; add chicken broth, tomatoes, liquid Butter Buds, wine, basil, oregano, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling; add potatoes in their jackets, green beans and carrots.
Reduce heat to simmer; cook 30 to 45 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add macaroni and serve.

title: pistachio (watergate) salad
directions: Soften Cool Whip.
Add undrained pineapple and mix well.
Add dry pudding mix and stir well.
Add rest of ingredients.
Stir until well mixed. Refrigerate.

title: martha washington candy
directions: Sift sugar.
Pour in milk and oleo.
Mix well and add nuts. Flour your hands with powdered sugar and roll mixture into balls. Melt paraffin and chocolate chips.
Dip balls into chocolate mixture.
Cool on wax paper.

title: crockery barbecued beef
directions: Combine cola, Worcestershire, vinegar, garlic, bouillon, mustard, chili powder and cayenne.
Reserve 1/2 cup of sauce for later. Trim excess fat from beef; place in crock-pot along with onions. Pour liquid sauce over and cook on low for 10 to 12 hours or on high for 5 to 6 hours.
Combine 1/2 cup reserved liquid sauce with catsup and margarine and bring to boil.
Transfer meat to cutting surface and shred.
Discard cooking liquid.
Serve on buns, pita bread or tortillas with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and cheese.

title: chop steak
directions: Mix ingredients.
Shape into patties and cook until done.
Mix brown gravy to package specifications and pour over patties. Yield:
6 to 8 patties.

title: no-fat super carrot raisin salad
directions: In a serving bowl, combine yogurt, honey, lemon juice and cinnamon into a smooth dressing.
Add carrots, raisins and pineapple and stir gently.
Cover and chill 15 minutes.
Toss again before serving.

title: red hot pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in a large container that can be covered.
Cover cucumbers with vinegar and cover container and set aside for 6 weeks.
After 6 weeks pour off vinegar and slice or cut up cucumbers.

title: onion shortcake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Butter 2 1/2-quart baking dish. In large skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add onions; cook until softened, 5 to 6 minutes. Remove from heat. Stir in half of cheese, sour cream, dill and salt until just combined. Set aside in bowl. Lightly beat egg. Stir in muffin mix, corn, milk and Tabasco sauce. Spread in baking dish. Top with cheese mixture. Sprinkle with remaining cheese. Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until top is golden and mixture is bubbly without baking.

title: italian sauce with meat balls
directions: Boil together for sauce:
tomato paste, tomato sauce, tomato soup, tomatoes, salt, pepper, oregano and Worcestershire sauce. Cook together.

title: creamy potato salad
directions: In a covered saucepan, cook potatoes in boiling, salted water for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender; drain well.
Peel and cube potatoes.
Transfer to a large bowl.
Add celery, onion and sweet pickle.
Combine mayonnaise, sugar, celery seed, vinegar, prepared mustard and salt.
Add mayonnaise mixture to potatoes.
Toss lightly to coat potato mixture.
Carefully fold in the chopped eggs.
Cover and chill thoroughly.
Makes 8 servings.

title: quick barbecue chicken
directions: Heat the oil in a large skillet. Add onion. Stir in ketchup, water, vinegar, brown sugar, Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and celery seed.
Bring to a boil.
Add chicken and spoon sauce over chicken pieces. Cover the skillet and cook for about 30 minutes.
Turn chicken over and simmer until done.

title: fruit roll-ups
directions: Use apples, peaches, pears or nectarines.
Fruit may be in any stage of ripeness.
If using canned fruit, drain well.
Peel and core fruit; blend until smooth.
Cook in saucepan, 5 to 10 minutes over moderate heat.
If watery, drain well.
While cooking, add 1 teaspoon honey for each piece of fruit used.
You may cook one piece or a dozen of the same type at one time.
Lay out clear plastic wrap for each piece of fruit cooked, on cookie sheet. Spoon cooked fruit onto wrap, staying away from edge.
Spread as thin as possible.
Place tray in oven at lowest possible heat or just pilot light.
Leave 6 to 8 hours overnight.
Check to see if it is dry.
If not, wait a while longer.
When dry, remove from oven and roll fruit up like a jellyroll.

title: mushroom souffle
directions: Saute mushrooms with celery, green peppers and onions.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When sauteed, mix with mayonnaise.
Place 4 or 5 slices cubed bread (soft) at bottom of casserole.
Cover with mushroom mixture.
Add 3 to 4 slices of cubed bread.
Beat 2 eggs with 1 1/2 cups of milk and pour over casserole.
Refrigerate overnight.
In morning, add mushroom soup (undiluted) over mixture. Now add 2 or 3 slices bread (cubed) and refrigerate until ready to use.
Now sprinkle with Parmesan cheese before baking for 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: ham-filled party rolls
directions: Take party rolls and scoop out centers. Combine all other ingredients and fill rolls with mixture. Bake for 8 minutes at 350°. Can be frozen.

title: apple bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat the oil, sugar and eggs.
Stir in the apples, vanilla and the combined dry ingredients.
Mix in the nuts and pour into 2 greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour. Let stand about 10 minutes then remove from pans and cool on wire rack.

title: irish italian spaghetti
directions: Brown onion in oil. Add meat and seasoning and cook until meat is done.
Drain fat.
Add soups.
Simmer on low heat with cover.

title: no-bake cheesecake
directions: Beat cream cheese until smooth; gradually beat in sugar. Blend in sour cream and vanilla; fold in whipped topping, blending well.
Spoon into crust; chill until set at least 4 hours. Garnish with fresh strawberries if desired.
Preparation time, 15 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Pour into buttered casserole and bake at 350° until brown,
45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pecan squares
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 12-inch baking pan.
Sift flour and sugar together.
Cut in butter using 2 knives or rub in, until fine crumbs form.
Pat crusts into baking pan.
Bake for 20 minutes.
Remove from oven.

title: lasagna florentine
directions: In large pan, cook onion and garlic in oil.
Add tomato sauce and simmer 15 minutes.
In bowl, mix Ricotta, spinach, 1 cup Mozzarella, Parmesan and eggs.

title: dilly green beans
directions: Wash one peck of green beans.
String, but do not break.
Cook beans 15 minutes in clear water.
Pack in pint jars.
Place a spray of dill in each jar (you may substitute 1/2 teaspoon dill seed) and a clove of garlic in bottom of each jar and pack tightly with beans.
Bring vinegar, water and salt to a boil; pour over beans.
Seal jars.

title: molded salad
directions: Tear up lettuce.
Open and drain black olives.
Using the tablespoon of shortening, grease a large bowl (preferably glass or metal) thoroughly, then line the bowl with plastic wrap.
For best results, tear 2 long sheets of wrap and overlap edge a couple of inches, then line bowl.
Put about 1/4 cup black olives in the center of bowl and press in place.
Starting from edge of bowl, run strips of ham and cheese alternately side by side down to the center of bowl.
Next, line tomatoes the same way and follow with the cucumbers.
Repeat this process again, ham and cheese, then tomatoes, then cucumbers.
Next, fill center with bibb lettuce, pressing into the center as full as you can get it, ending with a mound higher than the bowl.
Cover tightly with plastic wrap and place in refrigerator with a weight on top.
(A large can or a gallon of milk, as long as it's heavy, this will press your salad firmly.)
Keep refrigerated overnight.
When ready to serve, remove from refrigerator and peel off top plastic wrap.

title: hamburger and tomato pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup tomato sauce, crumbs, beef, onion, green pepper, 1/2 teaspoon salt and oregano; mix well.
Put in bottom of 9-inch pie pan.
Combine remaining ingredients except 1/2 cup cheese, pour into meat crust.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes; uncover and bake for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add combined dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Press half of crumb mixture into greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Spread with the preserves. Sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Cool; cut into bars.

title: jelled waldorf salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water; add lemon juice.
Combine cold water and ice to make 2 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until slightly thickened.
Remove unmelted ice.
Whisk in mayonnaise. Chill until thickened.
Fold in apples, celery and nuts.
Pour into 5-cup mold which has been sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Chill until firm (about 4 hours).
Unmold.
Makes 10 servings.

title: seafoam lime mold
directions: Dissolve lime gelatin in boiling water; add cold water and lemon juice.
Gradually add to softened cream cheese, mixing until well blended.
Chill until almost firm; fold in marshmallows, pineapple and nuts.
Pour into a 1-quart mold; chill until firm.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Melt butter; blend in flour and seasonings.
Add milk and cornstarch.
Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 1 cup of cheese and stir until melted.
Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Combine with sauce in greased baking dish.
Top with remaining cheese and bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 25 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.
